snippet.title: Having Radical Faith - Rica McRoy
snippet.description:
In this video, Rica McRoy is sharing about having radical faith and what it means to enter into God's story. Having radical faith through the Holy Spirit is a transformative experience that can turn your life upside down in the best possible way. It means abandoning yourself to the power and guidance of the Holy Spirit, and allowing yourself to be moved by the divine force of love that flows through all of creation. 

With radical faith, you can move mountains and accomplish the impossible. You become fearless in the face of adversity, knowing that you are not alone but accompanied by the Holy Spirit who gives you strength and wisdom to overcome any obstacle. 

Radical faith through the Holy Spirit also means living a life of joy and purpose. It means finding your true calling and living it out with passion and conviction, knowing that you are doing the work of God and making a positive impact on the world. 

It's not always an easy path, but having radical faith through the Holy Spirit is a journey worth taking. It will challenge you, transform you, and ultimately lead you to a deeper connection with God and a life filled with meaning and purpose. So if you're ready to step out in faith and experience the power of the Holy Spirit, get ready for a wild and wonderful ride!

snippet.title: How to Share God's Love and Gospel with the World - Brooke Anderson
snippet.description:
Do you have a burning desire to share God's love and the Gospel with the world? Are you seeking to become a radical messenger for God and spread His message of grace and truth to those around you? Look no further!

Becoming a radical messenger for God requires a deep commitment to His word and a willingness to step out of your comfort zone to share His message with others. However, the rewards are immeasurable. By sharing God's love and gospel with the world you can change lives, heal broken hearts, and bring hope to those who need it most.

As someone who share's God's love, you will have the chance to use your unique gifts and talents to share God's message in ways that are creative and impactful. Whether you are an artist, musician, writer, or speaker, there are countless ways to share His truth with the world.

But being a radical messenger is not only about sharing the Gospel with others. It's also about living out God's love and grace in your own life. By embodying the values of forgiveness, compassion, and kindness, you can be a shining example of God's love in the world.

If you're ready to become a radical messenger for God and share His love and message with the world, then let's get started! With your passion and dedication, and God's love and guidance, together we can change the world one message at a time.

snippet.title: Breakfast by the Sea
snippet.description:
As we wrap up our series, we explore Jesus' third appearance to His disciples after His resurrection. This encounter by the sea is a pivotal moment, reminding us of the significance of seeking God, no matter the time or place. Through the lens of John 21, we delve into how Jesus' simple breakfast with His disciples was more than a meal – it was a moment of restoration, reaffirmation, and a call to continue the mission He set forth.

Our sermon reflects on how we, like the disciples, may find ourselves drifting away from our spiritual commitments but are always called back by Jesus. The breakfast by the sea symbolizes a new beginning, a restoration of faith, and a reminder that Jesus never forsakes us.

snippet.title: The Miracle of the Loaves and Fish: Trusting in God’s Provision
snippet.description:
Today’s message celebrates God’s gift of another Sabbath and the miracle of Jesus feeding 5,000 people with just five loaves of bread and two fish. We explore how this story teaches us about faith, sharing, and trusting in God’s provision. This sermon highlights the importance of faith, trust, and recognizing Jesus’ sufficiency in our lives.

Join us for a heartfelt sermon, a beautiful prayer and the holy act of Communion. Let’s learn together how Jesus can do great things with even the smallest offerings.

snippet.title: Embracing Faith Amid Life's Storms
snippet.description:
Today, we continue our sermon series, "Summer by the Sea," reflecting on Jesus’ miracles and his powerful presence in our lives.

This week's message takes us back to the Sea of Galilee, where we witness Jesus walking on water, revealing his divine identity amidst a storm. Just as the disciples faced turbulent seas and found solace in Jesus, we too encounter storms in life where our faith is tested. As we navigate through these challenging times, remember that Jesus is our eternal lifeguard, ready to save us when we call out to him.

Join us as we explore the significance of having a lifeguard for our faith, the importance of reaching out to Jesus in our weakest moments, and the comfort of knowing that he is always there to rescue us from the depths of despair. Let's come together in prayer, reflection, and worship, and find strength in the presence of our Savior.

snippet.title: Discovering Jesus by the Sea of Galilee
snippet.description:
Today we're sharing the powerful lesson of Simon's calling by Jesus by the Sea of Galilee. We're reminded of the transformative love and grace of God, which calls us into a deeper relationship with Him.

Join us as we dive into Luke 5:1-11, exploring how Jesus' love and grace can take hold of our lives, just as it did with Simon. Let the Spirit of the Living God fall afresh on you today, melting, molding, and filling you with His presence.

May you be blessed by this message and feel God's embrace wherever you are in your faith journey. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content. God bless you!

snippet.title: God's Deliverance at The Red Sea
snippet.description:
In this powerful message, we'll explore the miraculous parting of the Red Sea, a story not just of ancient history but one that continues to hold deep significance for us today. We'll reflect on how God's mighty acts of deliverance can inspire and guide us through the 'Red Seas' in our own lives – those seemingly insurmountable obstacles that we face.

🔍 Sermon Highlights:

- Understanding the historical and spiritual importance of the Red Sea event.
- How God's deliverance then mirrors His ability to rescue us from our own challenges today.
- Insights from modern science that affirm the possibility of this miraculous event.
- The ultimate power of faith and the presence of God in our lives.

Let’s gather together, whether in the sanctuary or online from around the world, to find encouragement and strength in God's word. Stand firm, be still, and witness the deliverance of the Lord.

snippet.title: Jesus is the True Vine
snippet.description: Explore the profound spiritual truths of Jesus as the 'true vine' in John 15, where he teaches the importance of abiding in him to bear spiritual fruit. This connection is vital because, apart from Jesus, we can do nothing. By remaining in Christ, we produce the fruits of the Spirit, with love being the most significant evidence of a life intertwined with Jesus. Reflect on your relationship with Jesus and how it manifests in your daily life, ensuring that your faith journey is one of active engagement and abundant fruitfulness.

snippet.title: Moses: A Journey Beyond Doubt
snippet.description: Dive into the story of Moses and the burning bush with our latest video, where we uncover the essence of faith and our response to God's call. This biblical narrative is not just a tale from the past but a guiding light for our spiritual journey, inviting us to consider the nature of our own faith. Discover the significance of removing barriers to connect with the divine, the relational nature of God, and the importance of trusting in His vision for our lives. Learn about the sacred calling of 'I AM' and how to live a life fully committed to God. Join us as we explore the meaning of standing on holy ground and embracing our calling within God's divine plan. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more enriching content!

snippet.title: The Power of Mustard Seed Faith
snippet.description: Ever considered the power of a tiny seed? 🌱 This message emphasizes the beauty of small beginnings and how your mustard seed faith can grow into something extraordinary. In this message we explore the beauty of small beginnings and highlight the transformative power of God, who makes everything beautiful in its time. The parable of the mustard seed illustrates that the kingdom of God often starts small, and we are encouraged to take tangible steps to nurture our faith, like daily scripture reading and prayer, recognizing that even the smallest acts can have a significant impact in God's kingdom.

snippet.title: The Parable of the Sower
snippet.description: What kind of soil is your heart? In this message we're exploring the profound lessons of the Parable of the Sower, where Jesus teaches about the conditions of the human heart through the metaphor of soil. Discover how the seed, representing God's word, fares differently on the path of the hard heart, the rocky ground of the shallow heart, among the thorns of the crowded heart, and in the good soil of the fruitful heart. This message will challenge you to reflect on your own spiritual receptivity and consider how to cultivate a heart that embraces and bears the fruits of God's message.

snippet.title: Living a Grace-Filled Life | Rev. Chris McClain
snippet.description:
Discover the transformative power of God's grace in our latest sermon, "Living a Grace-Filled Life." Drawing from the story of Abram and his covenant with God, this sermon reveals how, despite our sins, we are offered a new covenant through Jesus Christ. Learn about the significance of baptism, Holy Communion, and the resurrection as we explore what it means to live as redeemed children of God. Whether you're struggling with your past or seeking a deeper understanding of salvation, this message is for you. Join us and be inspired to embrace the grace-filled life that awaits. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video for more uplifting content! 

#gracefilledlife  #Covenant #Forgiveness #Salvation #ChristianSermon #EasterSeries #Baptism #HolyCommunion #Resurrection #Redemption #ChurchFamily #GodsLove #JesusChrist

snippet.title: Embracing Grace: A Post-Easter Reflection
snippet.description:
This week, we're embracing grace as we gather for a powerful post-Easter reflection that explores the transformative 40 days Jesus spent on Earth after His resurrection. Discover the profound message of grace and redemption as we share about the poignant encounter between Jesus and Peter, where forgiveness and duty intertwine. This sermon will inspire you to embrace God's grace and commit to your Christian responsibilities. Whether you're seeking spiritual growth, understanding forgiveness, or looking to deepen your faith, this message is for you. 
 
#jesus #Resurrection #Grace #Forgiveness #ChristianDuty #Easter #WoodlandsChurch #Faith #SpiritualGrowth #BibleStudy #John21 #Peter #Sermon #Worship #ChristianLife #GodsLove #AmazingGrace

Drawing from the story of Abram and his covenant with God, this sermon reveals how, despite our sins, we are offered a new covenant through Jesus Christ. snippet.title: God's Sovereignty: A Life Filled with Grace
snippet.description:
Living a life filled with grace also means embracing God's sovereignty. Dive into the biblical story of Joseph and learn how God's grace can turn trials into triumphs. This message will challenge you to see God's hand in every aspect of your life and to trust in His sovereignty. Whether you're facing adversity or celebrating success, this sermon will encourage you to live a grace-filled life. Don't miss this powerful exploration of faith, forgiveness, and divine purpose.

#GraceFilledLife #JosephsJourney #GodsSovereignty #ChristianFaith #InspirationalSermon #BiblicalWisdom #TrustInGod #DivinePlan #WoodlandsMethodistChurch

snippet.title: Recognizing Your Identity in Christ
snippet.description:
In this message we'll dive into the story of Esther and learn the importance of recognizing your royal identity in Christ, exercising your God-given authority, and interceding for others in times of crisis. Discover how Esther's courageous actions to save her people exemplify the Christian calling to partner with God through prayer and action. This message will inspire you to embrace your calling "for such a time as this" and to live out your faith with boldness and conviction. Don't miss this transformative message that will challenge you to step into your spiritual authority and make a difference in the world. Subscribe to our channel for more uplifting sermons and join our community of faith.

 
#GraceFilledLife #ChristianIdentity #RoyalPriesthood #Intercession #WoodlandsMethodistChurch #FaithInAction #BibleSermon #ChristianLiving #SpiritualAuthority #ForSuchATimeAsThis

snippet.title: The Power of Grace
snippet.description:
Discover the power of transformative grace in this enlightening sermon drawing from Psalm 100 and the life-changing experience of the Apostle Paul on the road to Damascus. Join us as we dive into the story of Saul's transformation into Paul and consider how God's grace might be calling you to a new path. This sermon explores the joy of worship, the importance of thankfulness, and the various types of grace that influence our spiritual journey. Whether you're seeking inspiration, looking to deepen your faith, or curious about the impact of God's grace, this sermon offers valuable insights into how God's love can dramatically alter our lives.  Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video with those who might find hope and encouragement in its message.

#TransformativeGrace #ApostlePaul #ChristianFaith #SpiritualJourney #MethodistChurch #Worship #Thankfulness #GodsLove #RoadToDamascus #GraceOfGod #SpiritualGrowth #ChurchSermon #BibleStudy #FaithInAction #WoodlandsMethodistChurch

snippet.title: Empowering Grace - The Power of the Holy Spirit
snippet.description:
Experience the power of the Holy Spirit with our latest sermon, 'Empowering Grace'. Dive into the historical and spiritual significance of the Holy Spirit's descent and its impact on the early Church. Understand the true meaning of God's grace and how the Holy Spirit's empowerment transformed ordinary disciples into bold apostles. Learn the importance of waiting on God and inviting the Holy Spirit into your life. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking spiritual growth, empowerment, and a deeper relationship with God. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages and join us on a journey of faith, grace, and empowerment.

#Pentecost #HolySpirit #Grace #Church #Faith #Empowerment #ChristianLiving #SpiritualGrowth

snippet.title: The Significance of Lent
snippet.description: Join us as we journey into the sacred journey of Lent, exploring the depths of reflection, prayer, and spiritual renewal. In today's message, Pastor Margarita reflects on the significance of Lent from her childhood memories to the profound understanding she gained through faith in Jesus and seminary education. She unpacks the scripture passage from Luke 5, highlighting Jesus' compassionate touch and intentional prayer life and shares practical insights that invite viewers to join in a deeper communion with God.

snippet.title: How do we prepare for life's challenges?
snippet.description:
How do we prepare for life's challenges? This message will encourage you to explore the theme of preparation, both in Jesus' ministry and in your own life. Reflect on the importance of being equipped for life's challenges and embracing disappointments as avenues for divine blessings. As we journey through Lent, let's prepare our hearts to embrace the fullness of life promised by God.

Join us as we uncover lessons from Jesus' prayerful preparation as he approached the cross. We'll look at how Jesus, despite knowing his impending death, sought solace in communion with his Father. Discover the pivotal moment when Jesus challenges his disciples with the question: "Who do you say I am?" and the significance of Peter's declaration.

snippet.title: Rest and Renewal
snippet.description: In this message, we'll discuss the importance of rest and renewal during the Lenten season, drawing from the Gospel of Mark and the story of Jesus inviting his disciples to rest. We'll share about the need for spiritual rest and the biblical perspective on the Sabbath, highlighting how Jesus offers a deeper rest than the law could provide. The message also touches on modern society's struggle with rest and the various methods people use to achieve it, ultimately pointing to Jesus as the ultimate source of rest for the weary. Discover how unplugging from the world and surrendering to God's grace can lead to profound spiritual healing and inner peace.

snippet.title: Embracing Joy and Sorrow
snippet.description: Today we're talking about the bittersweet nature of life and faith in this moving sermon, reflecting on Jesus' emotional journey during Holy Week. As you watch, you'll learn about the importance of embracing both joy and sorrow, seeking solace in God, and the value of community support through grief. This sermon will inspire you to open your heart to Jesus to find the peace he offers, avoiding the regret of "if only." Whether you're experiencing grief or searching for deeper meaning, this message is for you. Join us in exploring the transformative power of Jesus' love and the hope of eternal life. Don't forget to subscribe for more uplifting sermons and spiritual guidance.

snippet.title: Building a Solid Life
snippet.description: Today we're talking about building a solid life using the timeless "blueprint" God gives us in His word. In this powerful message, discover the secrets of a strong foundation, drawing parallels between life's challenges and the construction of a sturdy structure. Sometimes life feels like a roller coaster but we can navigate the ups and downs with resilience and purpose. Learn from the insightful analogy of building on rock versus sand, and uncover the timeless teachings found in Matthew's gospel, chapter 7. Join us on this profound exploration of faith, wisdom, and the timeless blueprint that guides us in living a life built on Christ, the solid rock.

snippet.title: Blueprint for Living: The Beatitudes
snippet.description: Today we're exploring the timeless wisdom of the Beatitudes in our series, "Blueprint for Living." In this message we'll talk about the profound teachings of Jesus from the Sermon on the Mount, uncovering the keys to living a truly blessed life amidst the challenges of the world. Join us as we decode each beatitude, contrasting it with the world's standards, and discover how to cultivate a life of spiritual richness, peace, and fulfillment. Don't miss out on this transformative journey towards understanding the essence of true happiness and fulfillment.

snippet.title: Generosity and the Church
snippet.description: Join us as we reflect on the church's DNA of generosity, and look at how it defines the church and shapes its identity. Whether you're attending in person at Woodlands Methodist Church or joining us online from anywhere in the world, this message invites you to consider the seven forms of generosity and the joyous blessings it brings, both to givers and recipients.

snippet.title: The Gospel of Jesus Christ is Generous
snippet.description: The Gospel of Jesus Christ is generous. Join us as we examine how this generosity shapes our lives and inspires us to respond to the boundless love of God. We'll look into the scriptures that illuminate the true motivation for God's generosity, rooted in love, and gain insights into the profound meaning behind God's generous gift of Jesus Christ and how it extends to the abundance and beauty of the world around us. Discover the difference between being a believer and a disciple, and be inspired to embark on a journey of growth in faith. Whether you're considering saying yes to Jesus or moving from belief to discipleship, find guidance on responding to the generosity of God in Christ Jesus.

snippet.title: Embracing Generosity
snippet.description: As we begin our stewardship series this week, we're embracing generosity. Join us as we explore the significance of stewardship beyond finances, focusing on what it means to be a guided, grateful, growing, and generous church.  Don't miss this enlightening discussion on generosity, inspired by 2 Corinthians 9, as we learn to live the generous life that reflects the Gospel's inherent generosity. Plus, hear a heartwarming story from one of our church families about their journey at The Woodlands Methodist Church.

snippet.title: Is it truly more blessed to give than to receive?
snippet.description: Join us as Pastor Brent explores the age-old question: Is it truly more blessed to give than to receive? Drawing inspiration from Acts 20:35, where Paul quotes Jesus, Pastor Brent dives into the profound impact of generosity on our lives. Discover the Greek word "Makários," meaning happy, and how living a life of generosity can lead to true happiness. Explore the correlation between the condition of our hearts and our financial choices, and how Jesus emphasized this in Matthew 6:21 and learn the scientific benefits of generosity, including increased happiness, lowered stress, improved relationships, and an extended life. Don't miss real-life stories of transformed lives through generosity and the exciting giving challenge ahead. Join us in the journey of discovering the joy and blessings that come from living a life of giving.

snippet.title: Navigating Life's Challenges with Jesus as Our Compass
snippet.description:
In the midst of life's challenges, Jesus is our compass. In today's message, we're exploring the concept of being a guided church, drawing inspiration from the timeless teachings of Jesus. Discover the importance of having a clear direction and keeping the main thing, Jesus, at the center of your life. We'll talk about how being a guided church means ministering to the world, meeting community needs, and following the path that Jesus modeled for us. Be inspired to invest your deepest treasures in heavenly pursuits and find your way home, guided by the unchanging symbol of our faith – the cross. Don't miss this transformative message that encourages us to navigate life's challenges with Jesus as our unwavering compass. 

#GuidedChurch #Sermon2024 #JesusAsCompass

snippet.title: Life's Unexpected Challenges
snippet.description: Join us for an exhilarating journey as we explore the parallels between a thrilling whitewater rafting trip and life's unexpected challenges. In this engaging sermon we'll discover how being guided by scripture can help you navigate the rapids of health, relationships, and more. Understand the transformative power of God's Word in shaping our lives as we explore faith, purpose, and the promises of God in the midst of life's turbulent waters.

snippet.title: Where is your treasure? | Matthew 6
snippet.description: Today we're exploring the profound message from Matthew 6. Discover the importance of where your treasure lies, how your focus shapes your life, and the significance of having open hands in service to God. Don't miss the valuable insights shared in this stewardship series, guiding you to live a life filled with purpose and guided by the eternal truth of God's word.

snippet.title: Navigating the Journey of Faith | Guided Church
snippet.description: When we're navigating the journey of faith, it's important to have a clear guide. This week we're talking about being a guided church, the importance of having a clear guide in life, finding inspiration in biblical teachings, and embracing a life of generosity. Dive into the discussion on being led by a higher purpose and allowing the Lord to be your shepherd as we explore what it truly means to be a guided church in the year ahead.

snippet.title: Being a Grateful Church
snippet.description: This week we're talking about being a grateful church as we explore the theme of gratitude in stewardship. Discover how, like Zacchaeus, we can experience a transformative encounter with Jesus, leading to a profound shift in our perspectives and actions. Be inspired to embrace a life of gratitude and generosity. Watch, reflect, and consider your own spiritual journey as we embark on this third week of our stewardship campaign.

snippet.title: The Power of Gratitude
snippet.description: Today we're sharing about the power of gratitude, generosity, and the profound impact it can have on our lives. We'll dive into the life-changing encounter of Zacchaeus with Jesus and explore how blessings flow when we embrace an attitude of gratitude. Learn valuable lessons on stewardship, holistic wealth, and the true meaning of being a grateful church. Don't miss this powerful testimony of how those blessed by God become blessers for God.

snippet.title: The Transformative Power of Gratitude
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of gratitude as we delve into Luke 17 and discover the importance of living a life marked by thankfulness. Join us in this insightful sermon, where we discuss the goals we set in various aspects of life and emphasize the ultimate goal of hearing 'well done, my good and faithful servant' from Jesus. Learn how gratitude not only connects us with God but also positively impacts our mental and emotional well-being. Discover practical ways to cultivate a heart of gratitude and why it's key to becoming a church that is truly grateful. Don't miss this inspiring message on building a life worthy of God's commendation.

snippet.title: A Growing Church | Acts 2:42
snippet.description: In this inspiring sermon based on Acts 2:42, we explore what makes up a growing church—devotion to the apostles' teaching, breaking of bread, and prayer. Discover the significance of genuine fellowship and the transformative power of worship in building a growing church. As Pastor Drew reflects on the biblical model, we are challenged to deepen our devotion and trust in God. Be part of this dynamic community striving to be a growing church in today's world. Don't miss the insights into church growth, generosity, and living out our faith together.

snippet.title: Transformative Lessons from the Early Church
snippet.description: Today we're diving into the transformative lessons from the early church in Acts 2:42, exploring the keys to a thriving church and spiritual growth. Join us as we uncover the characteristics that fueled the explosive growth of the early church and learn how to apply them in today's context. Discover the importance of being devoted to God's word, fostering genuine fellowship, and living a shared life that leads to daily worship and prayer. Whether you're a seasoned believer or new to the faith, these timeless principles are sure to inspire and guide you on your spiritual journey. Don't miss out on the fullness of life that God has for you – hit subscribe and let's explore the path to a flourishing and devoted church together!

snippet.title: Are you growing?
snippet.description: Are you growing? Not just in the superficial sense, but in the areas of life that truly matter. The sermon takes you on a journey through the themes of generosity, guidance, gratitude, and now, growth. Discover insightful reflections on how we can grow both spiritually and in everyday life as individuals and as the church. We'll look at practical ways to embrace growth, build meaningful relationships, and live a life aligned with God and His purposes. If you're wanting to become more generous, guided, grateful, and learn more about how God can help you do this, this video is for you.

snippet.title: TWMC Christmas Special
snippet.description: Gather your whole family and join us on Christmas morning for a time of music and worship with Bristol House and a short devotional with Bishop Hayes.

snippet.title: Hark the Herald Angel Sing | Bristol House Music
Oh Come All | Bristol House Music
Go Tell It | Bristol House Music
All Hail King Jesus | Bristol House Music
Have Yourself A Merry Little Christmas | Bristol House Music
Angels We Have Heard On High | Bristol House Music
Prince of Heaven | Bristol House Music
I Wonder - Advent "The Wonder of it All"
snippet.description: In the hustle and bustle of our fast-paced lives, it has become all too easy to speed through Christmastime rather than anticipate and celebrate the true miracle of the season — the promise of love and joy captured in Jesus’ birth. Anticipation is not only a countdown to a day on the calendar, but also a journey of the heart. This holiday season, we invite you to pause, take a deep breath and rediscover The Wonder of It All.

snippet.title: The Gift of Hope - Advent
snippet.description:
The Christmas season is upon us. Lights, trees, presents, parties and stress abound. It’s so easy to get caught up in the busyness of this season that we can miss the beauty of it all. That’s why this Advent, we’re seeking to recapture the childlike wonder of Christmas. For children, this season is
marked by presents wrapped under the tree, and over the next four weeks, we’ll see how Jesus’ birth is a gift to our weary world. Because God put on flesh and was born in a manger in Bethlehem, we receive the gifts of hope, joy, peace and love. Whether this season is filled with wonder or filled with weariness for you, we’re glad that you’ve joined us at Loft!

snippet.title: The Wonder of It All: The Prophecy
snippet.description:
There is an unexplainable mystery that proclaims the seasons of Advent and Christmas, a story so steeped in simplicity and awe that it transcends everything we thought we knew about the God we serve. Mankind has always sought God in many unusual ways, but the Christmas story is about God
pursuing us, and on the night a child was born in the city of Bethlehem, God found us. Since then, our world has not been the same. Prophets, angels, shepherds and wise men heralded the good news,
and their message declared the greatest wonder of all: “Emmanuel — God is with us!” It is a story that never grows old, and we are delighted you are here to experience Advent and Christmas once again and to celebrate The Wonder of It All.

snippet.title: Waiting in Hope - Advent
snippet.description: We will be approaching the next several Sundays through the eyes of a child. I invite you to open your heart and mind to the possibly unexpected ways that God will reveal hope, love, joy and peace to you. Whether you are a member of our church, an invited guest or a curious visitor, my prayer is you will join us in the wonder of Jesus’ arrival to our community, especially in this Christmas season.

snippet.title: God's Promises of Love and Salvation
snippet.description: As we continue to explore the promises God made throughout history, leading us to the birth of Jesus, we focus on Isaiah's prophecy and the assurance of a Messiah who brings love and salvation. In this message, Bishop Hayes reflects on the timeless promise of a Messiah, tracing God's plan through the Old Testament prophets to the birth of Jesus. Learn how God's promises are not only declarations but tangible expressions of His love and the gift of salvation.

snippet.title: The Wonder in the Waiting | Advent
snippet.description: This Advent season, is the wonder really in the waiting? We all face moments of anticipation and uncertainty, and in this message, we explore how to find God's wonder and purpose in those seasons of waiting. We'll learn how Mary's faith in the midst of her waiting can inspire us to hold onto belief, embrace community, and experience the deeper waters with God. Hope you'll join us!

snippet.title: How to Find Joy in Unexpected Places
snippet.description: Today we're talking about finding joy in unexpected places. Join us as we explore the true meaning of joy and how, like the shepherds in Luke Chapter 2, we can discover lasting joy even in unexpected circumstances. If you've ever found yourself wondering how you can hold on to joy in midst of difficult times, this message is for you.

snippet.title: Love in Action: An Advent Reflection
snippet.description: Today we're continuing on our journey of waiting and anticipation during the season of Advent. Discover how the Holy Spirit empowers us not just to come together but to go out into the world and spread love. As we prepare for Christmas, let's extend the love we've received to those who are waiting.

snippet.title: Finding Peace in the Story of Christmas
snippet.description: Peace – it's a longing that echoes through the ages. In this message, we'll talk about how the biblical perspective on peace differs from the world's definitions, and learn more about the Hebrew concept of Shalom. Understand how Jesus, the Prince of Peace, brings completeness and restoration to our past, present, and future, and walk with us through the profound words of Isaiah, exploring the promise of a child born to bring everlasting peace. Discover how the Holy Spirit provides a supernatural peace, transcending our reality and transforming our daily lives.

snippet.title: The Wonder of Christmas: Searching for Joy
snippet.description: Christmas is full of wonder if we just have the eyes to see it. Dive into the message where we unravel the significance of the Magi's search for the newborn King and discover the joy that comes from pursuing Jesus. From childlike wonder to the depths of waiting, each step in our journey unfolds a greater understanding of God's promises. Embrace the darkness, acknowledge the messiness of the world, and find the light that leads to everlasting joy. Don't miss this inspiring exploration of The Wonder of it All, as we celebrate the season with worship and reflection.

snippet.title: Preparing for the King: The Wonder of Advent
snippet.description: Join Pastor Drew Essen as he explores the theme of preparation during the Advent season. Discover the true motivation behind your holiday preparations as we continue our series, The Wonder of it All. From personal reflections to the biblical story of John the Baptist, learn how to prepare your heart with joy, peace, and hope for the coming of the King. Don't miss this insightful message that encourages us to go beyond the surface of the holiday rush and embrace the deeper meaning of Christmas.

snippet.title: Finding Peace during Christmas
snippet.description: For some of us, Christmas can be anything but peaceful. However, there is hope! Learn how the journey towards peace involves grappling with grief, forgiveness, and understanding the true meaning of Shalom. We'll look at the timeless message that amidst life's troubles, we can find a deep and lasting peace in Jesus. Don't miss this insightful exploration of The Wonder of Christ, and discover the peace that surpasses all understanding.

snippet.title: A Joyful Christmas Celebration - Youth/Children Led Service
snippet.description: Get ready for a joyful Christmas celebration led by our youth and children! This service is not just for adults and we invite our young friends to participate actively and experience the joy of Christmas. Discover the wonderful gift we've received this Christmas season and explore the joy that only Jesus can bring into our lives. Get ready to be inspired and uplifted!

snippet.title: The Cast of Christmas: Behind the Scenes of the Greatest Story Ever Told
snippet.description:
In this special Christmas sermon, we'll explore the behind-the-scenes moments that led to the birth of Jesus and discuss the timeless significance of this extraordinary event. Share in the wonder and beauty of the Christmas story as we reflect on the characters who, though often overlooked, played crucial roles in God's divine plan. Be prepared to be inspired and reawakened to the joy of Christmas!
As we approach Christmas 2023, let's become the extras in God's story, living out the Christmas message of love, kindness, and joy every day.

snippet.title: Finding Peace in the Unexpected
snippet.description: God can show up in the most unexpected places sometimes, and it's there that we can also find peace. Share in the wonder of the season and understand that even in the midst of challenges, the message of peace and hope is for everyone. As we journey through the shepherds' perspective, Pastor Pierce highlights the transformative power of encountering God's message and how it can bring us peace that surpasses understanding.

snippet.title: What is True Love?
snippet.description: What is true love? In this message, Pastor Daniel leads us through a thought-provoking exploration of what true love really means and how it goes beyond mere feelings. Pastor Daniel challenges the common misconception that love is solely a feeling and reveals how the Christian faith provides a unique perspective on love. Discover the biblical definition of love, rooted in the concept of agape – a selfless, sacrificial love that mirrors God's love for us. Learn why love is not just a sentiment but a choice, a pursuit, and a commitment. Gain insights into the profound nature of God's love and understand why receiving His love is crucial for a fulfilled life.

snippet.title: Storm Warnings: Finding Hope in the Midst of Fear
snippet.description:
In this message, we're talking about fear and about how you can find hope in the midst of fear. We'll explore the story from the Book of Acts, where a group of people faced a terrifying storm and how they found hope and guidance. We'll talk about dealing with fear and doubt and discover how God sends help in unexpected ways.

Remember, even in the most challenging moments, God is with us, providing support and direction. When you're in the middle of a storm, don't forget to look around and see who God has placed in your path to help you through.

Join us on this spiritual journey as we learn to weather life's storms and emerge stronger on the other side. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this message with your friends and family.

snippet.title: How do we resist temptation?
snippet.description:
How do we resist temptation in the middle of life's storms? In this message we'll explore the biblical wisdom that helps us stay strong when temptations come knocking. We'll also discover the valuable lessons from the temptations Jesus faced in the wilderness.

Join us as we dive into the power of God's Word and find out how it can be our anchor in the stormy sea of life. Remember, you're not alone in this journey – we're here with you every step of the way.

snippet.title: Gratitude in the Storm: Finding Blessings Amidst Life's Challenges
snippet.description:
How do we find gratitude in the midst of life's storms? Join us for a message of hope, gratitude, and faith as we explore the importance of maintaining a posture of gratitude, even when faced with the unpredictable storms of life.

🙏 Pastor Mark Sorensen leads us through a powerful reflection on the story of Jesus and the ten lepers, illustrating how gratitude can bring healing and wholeness. Whether you're facing challenges, uncertainties, or simply seeking inspiration, this message is for you.

snippet.title: When God Says No: Understanding God's Response
snippet.description:
Have you ever wondered why God sometimes says "no" to our prayers? You're not alone! In this series, we'll uncover the wisdom behind God's responses to our petitions.

In today's message, we explore the powerful story of the Apostle Paul and how he responded when God denied his request. It's a message of hope, humility, and discovering God's amazing grace in our trials.

#prayer #whengodsaysno #answeredprayers #unansweredprayers

snippet.title: Take This Cup From Me: When God Says No
snippet.description:
Our current sermon series, “When God Says No,” continues this week as we are taken to the Garden of Gethsemane to hear Jesus’ words of agony: “Take this cup from me.” 

What is the cup that Jesus refers to, and why would He make such a request of His Heavenly Father? But what is even more puzzling is why would God not grant permission in the final hours of His only Son’s life? These are the questions that we will address in this message - the answers might surprise you! Join us as we reflect on the significance of Jesus' sacrifice and learn to understand what it means when God says no to our requests.

snippet.title: When God says No, His Grace says Yes
snippet.description:
In this sermon, we reflect on how even when God says no, His grace always says yes. We learn from the story of Moses, a revered figure in the Old Testament, who, despite his close relationship with God, was denied entry into the Promised Land. Explore the reasons behind God's decision and the valuable lessons we can apply in our own lives.

👉 Key Takeaways:

- Breaking faith with God.
- Recognizing God's power and glory.
- The importance of humility in our journey.
God's blessings vs. our self-reliance.
Join us as we uncover the profound message of faith, humility, and God's incredible grace that applies to us today.

snippet.title: Survival of the Fittest: Discovering Strength in Faith | Romans Sermon Series
snippet.description:
Join us for our traditional worship service where we explore the profound teachings of the Book of Romans in a new sermon series titled "Survival of the Fittest." Delve into the powerful truths of God's word as we discuss topics such as righteous judgment, renewal, faith, and more. This series is designed to equip and prepare us as believers to face the challenges of the world and strengthen our faith in Christ. Don't miss out on this opportunity to grow spiritually and find inspiration in God's word.

#romans #survivalofthefittest #thewoodlandsmethodist #onlinechurch #strengthinfaith

snippet.title: Faith, Hope, and God's Love: A Journey Through Romans
snippet.description:
Today, we continue our series, "Survival of the Fittest," where we explore the Book of Romans, digging into faith, righteousness, and what it means to be spiritually fit. Last week, we talked about righteous judgment. This week, we'll delve deeper into faith, a crucial aspect of our spiritual journey.

But here's a little story for you! While Bishop Hayes was preparing this sermon, he stumbled upon a hidden treasure - a clay coaster with a profound quote: "Faith is to believe what you do not yet see; the reward for faith is to see what you believe." 🙌✨ Talk about a God moment!

So, what does faith mean to you? How large is your faith? 🤔 Today, we'll explore these questions and dive into the incredible faith journey of Abraham, as explained by the Apostle Paul in Romans.

As we go through this message, remember that faith isn't just about believing in Jesus; it's about trusting in His promises, even in the face of adversity. When we embrace suffering and affirm the resurrection, our faith expands, making us more like Christ.

So, join us as we explore faith, hope, and God's incredible love in today's sermon. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more inspiring content. 

🔔 Stay tuned for more uplifting messages and worship services! God bless you all. 🙏

#romans #survivalofthefittest #faith #faithhopeandlove

snippet.title: God's Master Plan | Romans 9-11
snippet.description:
Join us as we unravel the mystery of God's master plan in the book of Romans chapters 9-11. We're here to learn, grow, and find our way through life's challenges together.

In today's message:
🌿 Learn how God orchestrates His divine plan through history.
🌟 Discover the importance of being grafted into God's family.
🕯️ Be inspired to be the light for the coming generation.

Join our church family as we explore the wisdom of Romans together 🙌  and don't forget to hit that thumbs-up button, subscribe, and ring the notification bell to stay updated with our messages every week.

snippet.title: Sacrifice and Renewal: Romans 12 and 13
snippet.description:
Join us as we dive into the Word and discover how God's will may require a sacrifice from us. Learn how to put on Christ, take up your cross, and lay aside the works of darkness as we explore Romans 12 and 13. Let's live a life of love and sacrifice that brings renewal to our hearts and hope to the world.

Enjoy this message? Don't forget to hit that like button, subscribe, and share this message with your friends and family. 

#sacrifice #renewal #romans12 #romans13 #survivalofthefittest #onlinechurch

snippet.description:
Join Pastor Margarita McCarthy as she shares a powerful message about our identity in Christ, taken from Ephesians 2:1-7. In this sermon, she explores how God’s grace transforms our lives and how we can find our true power and purpose in Christ. Learn how to pray with authority and victory as we partner with Jesus, and discover the amazing love and grace that God has for each one of us. 

Don’t miss this inspiring message that will encourage and uplift your faith journey with Jesus!

snippet.title: The Significance of Lent
snippet.description: Join us as we journey into the sacred journey of Lent, exploring the depths of reflection, prayer, and spiritual renewal. In today's message, Pastor Margarita reflects on the significance of Lent from her childhood memories to the profound understanding she gained through faith in Jesus and seminary education. She unpacks the scripture passage from Luke 5, highlighting Jesus' compassionate touch and intentional prayer life and shares practical insights that invite viewers to join in a deeper communion with God.

snippet.title: Discovering Jesus by the Sea of Galilee
snippet.description:
Today we're sharing the powerful lesson of Simon's calling by Jesus by the Sea of Galilee. We're reminded of the transformative love and grace of God, which calls us into a deeper relationship with Him.

Join us as we dive into Luke 5:1-11, exploring how Jesus' love and grace can take hold of our lives, just as it did with Simon. Let the Spirit of the Living God fall afresh on you today, melting, molding, and filling you with His presence.

May you be blessed by this message and feel God's embrace wherever you are in your faith journey. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content. God bless you!

snippet.title: Divine Interruptions: A Day in the Life of Jesus
snippet.description: Join us for this powerful message from The Woodlands Methodist Church's traditional worship service. Discover how Jesus used divine interruptions to reveal His power and authority, and how we can navigate the interruptions in our own lives with faith and trust. Don't miss this inspiring sermon that reminds us of God's presence in the midst of life's disruptions.

snippet.description:
In today's sermon, Pastor Drew shares an inspiring story from the Old Testament about a guy named Joseph. He had some amazing dreams that changed his life and taught him valuable lessons about faith, perseverance, and God's calling. 🌟

Join us as we explore Joseph's journey and discover how God's dreams can lead us to an incredible destiny! Don't forget to hit the "Like" button, subscribe to our channel, and share this message with your friends. Let's spread hope and faith together! 🌞

snippet.description: Join us as we reflect on the story of Jacob wrestling with God and how hymns can speak to our deepest emotions and struggles. We'll explore themes of regret, fear, and finding grace in unexpected places, ultimately reminding us that we are not alone in our struggles.

snippet.title: Hymns of Our Fathers: Celebrating Father's Day and Worshiping God
snippet.description: Join us for a heartwarming Father's Day service filled with uplifting hymns and a powerful sermon. In this special sermon titled "Hymns of Our Fathers," we explore the profound impact of hymns that speak to our heavenly Father. Discover how these beautiful songs have shaped our understanding of God and influenced our lives. Experience the warmth of Christian love and hospitality as we come together in worship. Whether you're a father, mentor, or simply seeking spiritual inspiration, this service is for you.

snippet.title: The Power of the Holy Spirit and Jesus' Promise
snippet.description:
In this message, we're talking about the power of the Holy Spirit in the church and how it gives us power in our lives.  The church, which is not just a building but a community of people, needs to stay connected to the Holy Spirit to have strength and power. This message reminds us that Jesus is always with us, and through the Holy Spirit, we can have peace and the power to overcome challenges.

snippet.title: The Promised Holy Spirit
snippet.description: Join us for an engaging message about the promised Holy Spirit and the joyous inheritance that awaits us. Discover why Paul's enthusiasm is contagious as we explore the significance of belief, being marked by the Holy Spirit, and the blessings that come with it. Get ready to be inspired and find hope in this message!

snippet.title: Model Citizen: Joseph of Arimathea - The Secret Disciple
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

When we use the term “model citizen,” we most often think of a person living an exemplary life, possessing such qualities as honesty, integrity and truth. Individuals who demonstrate these characteristics usually stand out in a crowd and are easily recognized. However, the New Testament is full of model citizens who walked in Jesus’ footsteps but were not always given the notoriety many other disciples received. Not only were they strong in their faith, but their influence and contribution to the early church was significant. This sermon series reveals a few lesser-known followers of our Lord who serve as an inspiration to us, reminding us that we all have unique gifts to offer as we walk in the footsteps of Christ.

snippet.description:
In this inspiring message, as part of our series "Model Citizen", we explore the importance of living a life that honors God through kindness and selflessness. Through serving others, we become the light bearers that destroy darkness and bring hope to a dark world. We are reminded to never tire of doing good, as God never tires of blessing us. By cultivating a life of selfless giving and caring for others, we can become the model citizens that inspire others to follow in our footsteps. Join us in this journey of faith and discover how the love and grace of Jesus Christ can bring salvation to a world in need.

snippet.description:
What legacy do you want to leave when you're gone? What legacy do you want to leave for future generations? Will it be something based on yourself and your own accomplishments? Or will it be a legacy of faith based on all that God has done in and through you?

In this video, we're talking about the life of Timothy and the influences he had that shaped his life as a disciple of Christ. You'll see how powerful living out your faith in front of others can be in leaving a legacy of faith for the next generation.

snippet.title: Forgiveness and Respect: Lessons from the Book of Philemon
snippet.description:
Forgiveness and respect are something often talked about in the Bible. In this message, Bishop Hayes shares about a lesser-known book in the Bible called Philemon. The book is a letter written by the Apostle Paul to Philemon, a fellow Christian, about forgiveness and the relationship between a master and a slave. However, the story of Philemon is important because it reveals the nature of God, forgiveness, and the inherent dignity and respect for all humanity. Philemon is a model citizen who shows that forgiveness can only be found when one follows Christ. The book is also a reminder that we should treat everyone with respect and dignity. Overall, the book of Philemon teaches us important lessons about forgiveness, respect, and treating others as equals.

snippet.title: The Power of Encouragement: Barnabas, the Son of Encouragement
snippet.description:
There is so much power in encouragement. Join us as we explore the inspiring story of Barnabas, a remarkable figure in the early Christian church known as the "son of encouragement." In this message, Pastor Mark shares the powerful lessons we can learn from Barnabas's life and his impact on others. Discover the importance of being an encourager, standing up for others, and finding grace in difficult situations. Through Barnabas's example, we learn how small acts of kindness and words of encouragement can make a significant difference in the world. Get ready to be inspired and learn how you can become a model citizen like Barnabas!

Key Takeaways:

Barnabas was known as the "son of encouragement" and made a significant impact in the early Christian church.
Encouragement is a powerful tool that can bring hope and positivity to others.
Barnabas stood up for Saul (later known as Paul) when others doubted him, showing the importance of supporting and believing in others.
The early church in Antioch demonstrated unity and cared for one another, exemplifying the true spirit of Christianity.
We are called to be encouragers in a world that can be dark and broken, spreading the message of love and hope through our actions and words.
Join us in exploring the inspiring life of Barnabas and learn how you can become a model citizen by being an encourager in your own community.

snippet.title: Ash Wednesday 2023 | 12:00 p.m. | Traditional Service
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship
 
There is a road that leads from Ash Wednesday to Easter, and it is called Lent. It is the 40-day journey that enables us to enter into a deeper relationship with God as we remember the sacrifice Jesus made on our behalf that ended at the cross on a hill called Calvary. It is a solemn and holy season, symbolized by the ashes that remind us of our own mortality
and our need to deny ourselves and follow Him. Travel along this road demands something of us. It is only through prayer, confession, self-examination and sacrifice that we are able to arrive at that destination where we fully understand the hidden possibilities that lie dormant within each of us. The Scriptures remind us “from dust we came, and to dust we shall return.” Come, journey with us as we die unto our sins so we may celebrate the resurrection and the promise of eternal life with the One who died for us and gave Himself as a living sacrifice for all.

snippet.title: Ash Wednesday 2023 | 7:00 p.m. | Contemporary Service
snippet.description:
Contemporary Worship

Welcome to our Ash Wednesday worship service. During the Lenten season, we reflect on the sacrifice of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. I encourage you to deepen your faith in these 40 days through the many opportunities offered at The Woodlands Methodist Church. Our 40 days of prayer, Wednesday noon prayer services, Bible studies, Connect classes and small groups are ways for us to journey to the
cross in a meaningful and life-transforming way. I invite you to join me and others in our community of faith as we embark on this journey together.

snippet.title: Ash Wednesday 2024
snippet.description: Welcome to our Ash Wednesday service in 2024! Join us in this time of prayer, reflection, and community as we surrender our burdens, repent of our sins, and renew our commitment to follow Christ. Let us journey together towards the joy of Easter, where we celebrate the victory of life over death through the resurrection of Jesus Christ.

snippet.title: As You Wish: Abiding Is Better
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Rev. Dr. Jeff Olive  

Throughout Jesus’ ministry, one remarkable truth stands out: He never imposed Himself upon any of the people He encountered. Jesus recognized the fact that God gave human beings free will and, in doing so, gave them the freedom to choose to abide in the true love of God or continue in another direction. In several instances Jesus is quoted as saying, “As you wish” or “As you choose,” knowing that the choices that are made can be the first step toward change. But when our wishes and choices take precedence over God’s plan for us, the consequences can be destructive. This sermon series will focus on us making the right choices that will help us abide in the true love God offers us.
