snippet.title: Missions Sunday - Pastor Karen Tyler
snippet.description:
Join us for a special Missions Sunday service with Pastor Karen Tyler. Today is a unique day in the life of our church as we gather to learn, be inspired, and embrace the missions that are at the heart of our community. Pastor Karen has a powerful message to share about spreading the love of Jesus and making a difference in the world.

In this video, we'll dive into the book of Acts and explore how early believers, just like us, were called to share their faith boldly, no matter the challenges they faced. We'll also hear incredible stories of real people who are changing lives through their unwavering commitment to the mission.

Whether you're a longtime member or just curious about our missions, we're excited to have you with us today!

snippet.title: Making a Difference: Missions and the Power of God's Love
snippet.description:
Today, we explore the power of God's love and how we can make a real impact in the world through missions and spreading the good news of Jesus.

Rev. Karen Tyler, our missions pastor, shares personal stories and insights about how her father's influence and a four-year-old's question ignited a fire in her heart for missions. We learn how we, as a church and as individuals, can respond to God's call to make a difference. It's a message that will inspire you to take action.

Don't forget to subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content, and if you enjoy this video, give it a thumbs up and share it with your friends and family. Let's spread the love of Jesus together!

snippet.title: Why Your Life Matters: Making a Difference with Jesus
snippet.description:
Have you ever wondered if your life can make a real difference or have a desire for your life to really matter? Well, you're not alone! Today, we're talking about how we can make our lives count and share some inspiring stories along the way. 

🔥 In this video, we'll explore:

The significance of our lives and how we can leave a lasting impact.
- Jesus' final words and what they mean for us today.
- Keeping the fire burning for others to experience Jesus' love.
- We've got a powerful story about one of our amazing ministry partners and how he's spreading the gospel, even in challenging circumstances. You won't want to miss it!

snippet.title: The Power of Sharing Jesus: Making a Difference in the World
snippet.description:
In today's message, we explore the profound impact we can make by sharing the love of Jesus with the world. Join us as we discuss the importance of reaching out to others and spreading the Gospel, reflecting on our mission to make a difference and bring hope to those in need. Discover how we can all play a part in this beautiful journey of faith and love.

Join us for this inspiring sermon and be motivated to be a part of something bigger than yourself. Let's make a lasting difference in the lives of those around us!

snippet.title: Choose Grace: How to Start the New Year Right
snippet.description: How can we choose grace in the new year? Whether you're setting spiritual goals, seeking greater joy, or desiring a closer walk with God in 2024, this message is for you. Join us on this transformative journey, choosing grace over offense and making 2023 a year of spiritual breakthroughs. Don't miss out on the opportunity to live unoffendably, positively impacting your life and those around you.

snippet.title: Extraordinary Devotion: Growing in Grace
snippet.description:
In this message, Pastor Karen explores the theme of "Extraordinary Devotion" and discusses what it means to be a growing church in the grace of Jesus Christ.

🌟 Highlights:
- Discover the significance of devotion to God's word, fellowship, breaking bread, and prayer in a growing church.
- Learn how ordinary people, when encountering an extraordinary God, can impact their communities.
- Explore the compassionate and caring nature of a growing church, making a positive difference in the lives of others.
- Celebrate the gift of Jesus Christ and the transformative power of gratitude.

snippet.title: The Love Language of Service
snippet.description: Today we're talking about the love language of acts of service and its biblical significance during Palm Sunday. Learn from the example of Mary's anointing of Jesus and how to serve others with a pure heart, just as Jesus washed His disciples' feet. This message will inspire you to worship God with complete devotion and to serve others without seeking anything in return.

snippet.title: Trust in God's Plan - Rev. Karen Tyler
snippet.description:
Discover the profound lessons of faith, perseverance, and God's unwavering faithfulness amidst life's trials. Joseph's journey from favored son to slave, and then prisoner, teaches us the importance of trusting in God's plan, even when faced with injustice and adversity. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking encouragement and strength during challenging times. Don't miss the opportunity to deepen your understanding of perseverance as a spiritual gift and learn how to maintain joy in your faith journey. Subscribe to our channel for more uplifting messages and be sure to hit the notification bell to stay updated on our latest sermons. 
#faith #perseverance #JosephsStory #TrustInGod #SpiritualGrowth #BibleLessons #ChristianLiving #WoodlandsMethodistChurch

snippet.title: Understanding God's Grace Through Sacrificial Living
snippet.description: Discover the transformative power of God's grace in our latest message, 'Understanding God's Grace Through Sacrificial Living'. Dive into the biblical story of Ruth and Naomi and learn how 'hesed', the Hebrew concept of loving kindness, is demonstrated through their lives. This sermon unpacks the importance of living sacrificially as a reflection of God's grace and how it leads to an abundant life in Christ. Don't miss out on understanding how everyday acts of obedience can have an extraordinary impact.

snippet.title: Living a Spirit-led Life
snippet.description: Explore the essence of living a Spirit-led life with our latest message, where we dive into the significance of the Holy Spirit's guidance in our daily lives. Learn how to embrace change and new responsibilities within your spiritual community by trusting in God's direction. This video offers insights into the biblical narrative of the Exodus and the early church's reliance on the Holy Spirit, providing a blueprint for our own journeys. Discover practical steps to discern the Holy Spirit's voice and cultivate a closer relationship with God. Join us as we explore how to dedicate each day to the Spirit, create a heart open to God, and commit to obedience, anchoring our identity in Christ for a fulfilling Spirit-led life.

Christ was always moving forward, and so must we. “Follow me” is still the call to abundant life, and it is our prayer we will accept His invitation to live out our faith and learn to extend the gifts He gives to others.

snippet.title: God’s Promises: It Goes Deeper Than Imagined | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
* Traditional Worship eBulletin: https://bit.ly/ebulletin-traditional

Traditional Worship | Pierce Drake

Blessed assurance! Living in uncertain and unpredictable times is nothing new for God’s people. From the beginning of creation until this present day, believers have always had to contend with fear, doubt, despair and failure. At times it seems our faith is tested beyond our ability to cope, but in those moments when all seems hopeless, we would do well to remember the promises God has made to us. Let us focus on the great promises God has given us – knowing that whatever happens, God will be with us!

snippet.title: Putting Christ in His Rightful Place | Pentecost | Psalm 27
snippet.description:
In this powerful sermon on Pentecost, Pastor delivers a heartfelt message about putting Christ in His rightful place, the beauty of God, and the power of the Holy Spirit. Drawing from Psalm 27, he emphasizes the importance of beholding the beauty of God and seeking Him in His temple. Discover the significance of the Trinity and the indwelling of the Holy Spirit as Pierce Drake encourages us to embrace the beauty of God and live in awe of His glory. Join us for this Pentecost message that will inspire and uplift your spirit.

#pentecost #pentecostsunday #holyspirit #godspresence

snippet.title: Rediscovering the Power of Hymns
snippet.description: Join us as Pastor Pierce takes us on a journey through his personal connection to the traditional worship service and the profound impact of hymns in his life. We'll talk about the story of Paul and Silas in Acts, where they found solace in singing hymns even in the darkest of times. Learn how the power of praise and joyful sacrifice can create saved and sanctified communities. This message will inspire you to rediscover the timeless wisdom and beauty found in hymns and their ability to strengthen our faith. Don't miss out on this powerful reminder of God's grace and the transformative power of music.

snippet.title: The Antidote to Greed
snippet.description: Join us for the fifth week of our summer series on the seven deadly sins. In this sermon, we explore the sin of greed and how it distorts the virtue of generosity. Discover the antidote to greed and learn how to be rich toward God. This message will challenge you to examine your heart and priorities as we seek to live according to God's kingdom values.

snippet.title: Discovering Jesus: The Supreme Creator and Redeemer
snippet.description: In this message, we’ll explore the powerful words from the book of Colossians, where the Apostle Paul reminds us of Jesus’ supreme role as the Creator and Redeemer. We”ll learn how Jesus created all things and how His sacrifice on the cross redeemed us, bringing us back into a loving relationship with Him. Let’s dive into the message and discover the heart of the Gospel!

snippet.title: How to Live like Jesus
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore Colossians chapter 3 and discover how we, as God's beloved children, can live like Jesus. In this sermon, we learn about a holy posture that includes a rooted identity, setting our hearts and minds on godly things, and engaging in holy warfare against things that separate us from Jesus. Let's strive to look more like Jesus each day and embrace the beauty of Christ in our lives.

🙏 Join our church community and grow in faith together! 🙏
Subscribe to our channel for more uplifting sermons and Bible teachings. In this message, you'll find guidance on how to live a life that reflects Christ's love and grace.

📖 Scripture: Colossians 3:1-17

snippet.title: How to Live a Meaningful Life through Prayer
snippet.description:
In this last message in our series on Colossians, we explore how we can live a meaningful life through prayer, vulnerability, and sharing the gospel with others. Learn how to rest in Jesus and step into a life of purpose and meaning. Be encouraged to embrace holy discomfort and grow closer to God as we journey together in faith. 

Don't forget to like and subscribe for more great content each week!

#prayer #meaningfullife #sharingthegospel #colossians

snippet.title: Finding Delight in God | Isaiah 58
snippet.description:
In this series, we've been exploring the beauty of the Sabbath, and today's message focuses on the concept of delight. We're diving deep into the Word of God from Isaiah 58, exploring the theme of finding delight in our Creator and His Word. We believe that delight is how we honor God, and today, you'll learn practical ways to do just that. Join us on this journey of faith, and together, let's find our unique ways to delight in God's presence.

#delight #sabbath #Isaiah58 #rest #restingod #godsword

snippet.title: Sabbath, Worship, and New Beginnings
snippet.description:
Join us for a special gathering where we delve into the essence of Sabbath, worship, and new beginnings. In this heartfelt discussion, we reflect on the culmination of recent events, including the conclusion of our Shabbat series and the launch of Bristol House's first album. We also share insights from the New Room Conference and explore the significance of taking time to rest, connect, and listen to the heartbeat of God.

Our pastors and worship leaders open up about their own experiences and challenges in observing Sabbath. We also learn about the power of worship songs and how they can deeply impact our spiritual journey.

Discover the importance of giving away what you have to offer, as we discuss the vulnerability and beauty of sharing our unique gifts within the church community. We conclude with a meaningful communion service, reminding us of Jesus's sacrifice and our call to be a fragrance of love and light in the world.

snippet.title: The Holy Spirit is Our Comforter
snippet.description: In this video, we continue our incredible series on the Holy Spirit talking about how the Holy Spirit is our comforter. Maybe you haven't even realized it was the Holy Spirit at work, but looking back, you can see His presence during moments of healing, comfort, and incredible power. Join us for an inspiring message and a powerful reminder of God's love and presence. 📖🙏

snippet.title: Embracing God's Call: Ananias and the Transformation of Saul
snippet.description: Join us for a powerful message that encourages us to embrace God's call in our own lives and continue to be obedient no matter what God asks us to do. In today's message, we're looking at the story of Ananias and the transformation of Saul. Specifically, the obedience and faith of Ananias, a disciple whose simple "yes" to God's call played a crucial role in shaping history. Discover how God calls us into His story, inviting us to be faithful and obedient, trusting in His sovereignty.  This sermon is part of our series "Don't Blink," where we discover the profound impact of fleeting moments in the kingdom of God.

snippet.title: The Wonder in the Waiting | Advent
snippet.description: This Advent season, is the wonder really in the waiting? We all face moments of anticipation and uncertainty, and in this message, we explore how to find God's wonder and purpose in those seasons of waiting. We'll learn how Mary's faith in the midst of her waiting can inspire us to hold onto belief, embrace community, and experience the deeper waters with God. Hope you'll join us!

snippet.title: Finding Peace in the Unexpected
snippet.description: God can show up in the most unexpected places sometimes, and it's there that we can also find peace. Share in the wonder of the season and understand that even in the midst of challenges, the message of peace and hope is for everyone. As we journey through the shepherds' perspective, Pastor Pierce highlights the transformative power of encountering God's message and how it can bring us peace that surpasses understanding.

snippet.title: Our Identity in God | A Journey Through Genesis
snippet.description: We're going on a journey through the Genesis story, unveiling the profound truth about our identity in God. Join us as we explore the significance of being formed by God's hand, carrying His image, and breathing in His life-giving breath. Discover how understanding these foundational truths can reshape your perspective on life, purpose, and fulfillment. Don't miss out on the transformative message that reminds us of our intimate connection with the Creator.

snippet.title: The Message of Genesis: Creation, Temptation, Redemption
snippet.description: In this sermon we're diving deep into the message of Genesis. We'll unpack the rich tapestry of Genesis, exploring themes of creation, temptation, and redemption. Join us as we journey through the Word, unraveling its layers and uncovering the divine truths within. Discover the significance of the Tree of Life and the Tree of Knowledge of Good and Evil, as we navigate the complexities of human nature and God's unwavering love. Through thoughtful analysis and heartfelt dialogue, we invite you to engage with scripture in a meaningful and transformative way. Whether you're seeking spiritual guidance or simply curious about the mysteries of faith, our channel offers a sanctuary for exploration and enlightenment. Join our community as we embark on a quest for deeper understanding and connection with the divine. Subscribe now and embark on a journey of discovery with us.

snippet.title: Unwavering Faith and Ordinary Obedience | Altars
snippet.description: In today's message, we'll discover how Abram's (later called Abraham) ordinary obedience and unwavering faith helped him navigate through uncertainty and into God's promises. We'll look at the significance of altars in Abram's story, unpacking their symbolism and relevance in our lives today. Altars signify not just worship, but a declaration of citizenship in the Kingdom of Heaven amidst earthly uncertainties. Join us as we unravel the layers of Abram's encounter with God as he embarks on a journey of faith and obedience.

snippet.title: God's Promises in our Trials
snippet.description: Today we're exploring how God's promises intersect with our most challenging trials. Discover the power of unwavering faith, as Abraham's obedience leads to divine provision. Learn how to trust in God's unfailing love even in the face of uncertainty. This message will equip you to walk boldly in faith, knowing that God is always faithful to His promises. Tune in to strengthen your spiritual journey and witness the transformative power of faith.

snippet.title: Encountering God with Expectancy
snippet.description: Join us as we look a the life of Jacob from Genesis and learn more about his transformative journey from self-reliance to building altars of worship and submission to God. We'll share about the importance of expectancy in worship, remembering God's faithfulness, repenting from idols, and returning to true worship. This message will inspire you to build your own pillars of commitment to God, just as Jacob did. Whether you're feeling distant or seeking a deeper connection with God, this sermon is for you.

snippet.title: The Essence of Faith
snippet.description:
Explore the core elements of Christian faith with our latest sermon on the essence of faith. Discover the significance of the resurrection of Jesus, the Kingdom of God, the Holy Spirit, and our mission as God's witnesses. This sermon unpacks the simplicity of our calling and how to live out our faith with purpose. If you're searching for spiritual growth, understanding the Holy Spirit, or seeking to deepen your belief in Jesus' resurrection, this video will guide you. Join us in embracing our unique role in God's tapestry and learn how to let the light of Christ shine through you. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages and share this video to spread the word of God's love and salvation.

#ChristianFaith #Resurrection #HolySpirit #KingdomOfGod #GodsMission #ChurchLife #SpiritualGrowth #Witnessing #GospelTruth #Salvation

snippet.title: Unity in the Body of Christ
snippet.description: What does unity truly look like in the body of Christ? Join us as we consider the courageous example of Stephen in the book of Acts and the transformative power of a united church in the world. We'll look at how our commitment to oneness is not just a reflection of our faith, but a beacon of hope to the world. We'll explore the critical importance of unity within the Christian community, as it reflects the core message of reconciliation in the Gospel. Unity is not just an ideal; it's a reflection of our relationship with God, made possible through Christ, and it serves as a powerful witness to the world of God's love.

snippet.title: God's Relentless Love and the Power of Baptism
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of God's love and the significance of baptism in this insightful discussion. Learn about the early church's perseverance, Philip's evangelistic encounter with the Ethiopian eunuch, and the importance of scriptural guidance. Witness Saul's life-changing conversion and Ananias's faithful response to God's call. This video looks at the universal call to faith and the impact of God's grace on our lives. Join us in reflecting on how we can share Jesus's love and truth, and be inspired to live out the Gospel in every aspect of life.

snippet.title: Finding God in Every Moment: How to Live Faithfully
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore how to live a life faithful to King Jesus, learning to handle every moment with wisdom and grace. In this sermon, Pastor Pierce Drake shares insights from the Book of Acts and how we can be expectant of God’s spoken word in our daily lives. 

Discover how to recognize and respond to God’s presence and guidance, ensuring that we reflect His love and truth in every situation. 

Whether you’re dealing with a crisis or just navigating everyday moments, this message will encourage and equip you to live faithfully sent by King Jesus.

snippet.title: Prepare Your Heart: The Call to Radical Holiness
snippet.description:
In this powerful sermon, we explore the deep message of God’s call to radical holiness. As we journey through Revelation, we are reminded of the churches that received both praise and rebuke. What does it mean to be lukewarm, and how does God’s rebuke reflect His love for us? 

This message will challenge you to reflect on your own life and encourage you to embrace a life of holiness, knowing that God’s correction is a sign of His love and presence. 

Let’s open our hearts to His call and prepare for the coming of His Kingdom.

snippet.title: God’s Promises: God is Always With Me | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Dr. Edmund W. Robb III

Blessed assurance! Living in uncertain and unpredictable times is nothing new for God’s people. From the beginning of creation until this present day, believers have always had to contend with fear, doubt, despair and failure. At times it seems our faith is tested beyond our ability to cope, but in those moments when all seems hopeless, we would do well to remember the promises God has made to us. Let us focus on the great promises God has given us – knowing that whatever happens, God will be with us!

snippet.title: Faith We Sing: And Can It Be | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

So many of the convictions we hold and the truths we believe are captured in the songs we sing! The reality is, we are singing people, and music, as seen throughout the Bible, trains us in the practice of remembering who God is and what God has done for us. In the book of Psalms, we are encouraged to “Sing to him, sing praise to him; tell of all his wonderful acts” (105:2). Through the gift of music, God has united art with truth and a way for the gospel message to sink itself into our hearts through singing and sharing our faith in song.

snippet.title: Walk with God | The Woodlands Methodist Young Adults
Hello, My Name Is…: Worrywart | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

William Shakespeare asked the famous question, “What’s in a name?” Names are important for our identity. There are names we are given at birth, names we use to connect or remember others, and names we use to label ourselves. In this series, we are going to look at some of the labels we wear, but we will also celebrate how Jesus can change those labels and give us a new name! Join us as we celebrate our connection to each other and say, “Hello, my name is ...”

snippet.title: Easter: They Rested! | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

Welcome to Easter Sunday — the most important day of our Christian faith! On this day death was defeated with the Resurrection of our Lord and Savior, Jesus Christ, and we are delighted you have joined us to celebrate and worship. Here at The Woodlands Methodist Church, everything we do is rooted in the Good News of Jesus Christ. May you feel God’s presence as you encounter the risen Lord through the traditional music, prayer and spoken word. If you are a visitor, I encourage you to stop by Connection Point in the Atrium to obtain more information about our church. Again, thank you for being with us!

snippet.title: Easter: Death and Life - Loft TWMC
snippet.description:
Loft Worship | Daniel Lumpee

Welcome to Loft, and Happy Easter! 

Today is a day we remember that death does not have the final say. We celebrate the historical fact that Jesus’ tomb was empty and that He is risen. And because Jesus is risen, when you receive Him into your life, the power of the resurrected Christ lives in you. Easter promises us that if Jesus is our Lord, we can experience abundant life on this side of the grave, and eternal life forevermore. We’re so grateful you are celebrating with us today, and we hope to see you again soon. He is risen!

snippet.title: Easter: Idle Tale or Invincible Truth?
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

“He is risen!” This was the shout from the women and the disciples as they arrived at the tomb of Jesus and found it empty on that first Easter morning. Today, over 2,000 years later, our response and affirmation can be nothing less than “He is risen indeed!”

Welcome to Easter Sunday — the most important day of our Christian faith. We are delighted that you have joined us to celebrate our Lord’s victory over sin and death. May you feel God’s presence as you encounter the risen Savior through the music, prayers, Scriptures and spoken word. 

Everything we do is rooted in the Good News of Jesus Christ. Again, thank you for being with us — you are welcome here!

snippet.title: Doors to Open: Door of Guilt
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

The 40-day season of Lent is a time when Christians all over the world renew their loyalty to our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ through acts of repentance. The word Lent means “spring,” and it signals the reawakening of our souls, of God’s renewing love that breaks through our waywardness and sins. For us to get to the glorious resurrection that awaits us, there are doors to open so this sacred season can have
meaning and purpose. Our series, Doors to Open, is an opportunity for us to enter into the new life that awaits us, for “if anyone is in Christ, they are a new creation; the old has gone, the new has come!” (2 Corinthians 5:17)

snippet.title: God Didn’t Say That: What God Didn’t Say About Happiness | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

How sure are you when it comes to knowing what God said or didn’t say in the Bible? Let’s face it—even the most knowledgeable Christians have difficulties distinguishing fact from fiction and truth from nontruth. How good are you at being able to identify misleading quotes and stories that have somehow filtered into the mainstream of God’s Word and teachings? It is truly amazing how the “accumulated baggage” of not knowing what God said has weighed us down as modern-day disciples. This three-week sermon series is designed to open our eyes and better our understanding of what God did and didn’t say about happiness, the burdens we bear, and yes, money! You don’t want to miss this entertaining and enlightening series!

snippet.title: Our Future is Bright! | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description: The Woodlands Methodist Church has been faithfully responding to God's call for 45 years. This is an historic moment as the church looks to the future and is uniquely positioned to identify, train, and send ministry leaders out to expand the mission of the Church. There is a true move of God in our nation as Gen Z rises up and we are unashamedly helping to steward this next generation of leaders. The future is bright for the people called Methodists!

snippet.title: Growing Together: Vision 2022 | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
State of the Church | Rev. Mark Sorensen

When God created the “heavens and the earth,” every living thing that was made was designed to grow. It is the natural order and cycle of life. But growth can be both physical and spiritual, and this is where the summons of Jesus comes to us, inviting us to become more like Him by choosing an intentional path that leads to life. When we cultivate our faith, love for each other and our neighbor, we discover the true meaning of life, and we discover more about ourselves. Join us as we accept Christ’s invitation to grow together, thereby fulfilling God’s great design that every living thing should have life in all of its abundance.

snippet.title: Searching for Christmas: Searching for the Unexpected | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Rev. Daniel Lumpee 
 
Have you ever thought about how much time we spend searching for things like our car keys, a special restaurant, or that hard-to-find ingredient for the next recipe? Little do we realize that on a deeper level, we are also searching for direction, happiness, comfort, peace and the answers to life’s problems. During this Advent season, we invite you to join us as we begin a journey that will help us find what we are looking for, and our search ends at a cradle in Bethlehem where our Savior Jesus Christ is born!

snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

Our Christmas Eve worship services are some of the most cherished and beautiful gatherings in the life of our church. These services signal that we have reached our limits with the busyness of the season—the gift buying is over, our families are together, and we can finally focus on celebrating the birth of our Savior, Jesus Christ! This Christmas Eve, we go in search of the light that illumines our world and our lives, and our presence here tonight proclaims that no matter how dismal things may be, the light of Christ shines in the midst of our darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it.

snippet.title: Doors to Open: Door of Obedience | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Rev. Susan Kent

The 40-day season of Lent is a time when Christians all over the world renew their loyalty to our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ through acts of repentance. The word Lent means “spring,” and it signals the reawakening of our souls, of God’s renewing love that breaks through our waywardness and sins. For us to get to the glorious resurrection that awaits us, there are doors to open so this sacred season can have meaning and purpose. Our series, Doors to Open, is an opportunity for us to enter into the new life that awaits us, for “if anyone is in Christ, they are a new creation; the old has gone, the new has come!” (2 Corinthians 5:17)

snippet.title: Hello, My Name Is … : Broken | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Rev. Susan Kent

William Shakespeare asked the famous question, “What’s in a name?” Names are important for our identity. There are names we are given at birth, names we use to connect or remember others, and names we use to label ourselves. In this series, we are going to look at some of the labels we wear, but we will also celebrate how Jesus can change those labels and give us a new name! Join us as we celebrate our connection to each other and say, “Hello, my name is ...”

snippet.title: Becoming: Accepted
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

The essence of our sermon series, Becoming, is best captured by the pen of Dr. Gardner Taylor. He writes, “There hangs over each of us the awareness of moving toward something, of becoming something far finer than we have ever been. Ah, we may wince, but we are never for long free of that yearning to become better, that instinctive squirming to be let loose from some imprisoning and crippling web in which we are caught. This sense of inward struggle toward something, of awareness of some huge, approaching wonder forms the basis for the earth’s finest literature, informs and indwells the world’s worthiest crusades and fashions the splendor, the most glorious splendor of humanity.”

snippet.title: Understanding the Seals of Revelation: God’s Plan Unfolds
snippet.description:
In this message, we dive into the fifth and sixth seals from the Book of Revelation, exploring what these seals represent and how they connect to Matthew 24. We’ll uncover the meaning behind the horsemen and their significance in God’s plan for redemption. Learn how the unfolding of these events is a part of God’s grand design and why we can trust that He is in control. 

This teaching reminds us that even in challenging times, God is on the throne, and we are sealed by His Spirit.  Join us as we seek to understand and stand firm in our faith.

snippet.title: Unlocking Revelation: Exploring the Throne Room of God
snippet.description:
In this powerful sermon, we dive into Revelation chapters 4 and 5, discovering the awe-inspiring vision John had of the throne room of God. Imagine seeing a grand throne surrounded by dazzling lights and colors, where heavenly beings worship God day and night. This message explores how these chapters reveal the majesty and authority of God and the Lamb who is worthy to open the scrolls. 

Whether you’re new to the Bible or have been studying it for years, join us as we explore these crucial chapters and their significance for us today. You’ll be encouraged to see how your prayers and worship fit into this grand vision and how God is still on the throne, no matter what challenges we face.

snippet.title: Prepare Your Heart: The Call to Radical Holiness
snippet.description:
In this powerful sermon, we explore the deep message of God’s call to radical holiness. As we journey through Revelation, we are reminded of the churches that received both praise and rebuke. What does it mean to be lukewarm, and how does God’s rebuke reflect His love for us? 

This message will challenge you to reflect on your own life and encourage you to embrace a life of holiness, knowing that God’s correction is a sign of His love and presence. 

Let’s open our hearts to His call and prepare for the coming of His Kingdom.

snippet.title: Revelation Unveiled: Jesus’ Message to the Suffering Church
snippet.description:
In this sermon, we dive into the Book of Revelation and explore Jesus’ powerful message to the church of Smyrna — a church enduring intense suffering and persecution. Jesus reminds them that He knows their tribulations and encourages them to stand firm in their faith. 

As we study this passage, we learn how to apply these truths to our lives today, finding hope and strength in the midst of our own trials. 

Join us as we unpack the lessons from Smyrna and discover how Jesus walks with us through every challenge, offering comfort and promise to those who remain faithful.

snippet.title: Revelation: Hope and Renewal in the New Kingdom
snippet.description:
Join us as we embark on a transformative journey through the Book of Revelation, exploring a vision of a restored humanity and a new earth. Imagine a world where every tear is wiped away, and death is no more. In this Revelation, we find the promise of Jesus' return, bringing hope and renewal.

In this 14-week series, leading up to Thanksgiving, Pastor Mark will guide us through the final book of the Bible, helping us understand its profound messages and how they apply to our lives today. We'll dive into the narratives, symbols, and prophecies, uncovering the deeper meanings and preparing our hearts and minds for the triumphant return of our King.

Whether you're new to studying Revelation or have journeyed through it before, this series aims to reframe and demystify its messages, encouraging us to live out our faith with renewed passion and purpose. Revelation is not about predicting the future but preparing for it, reminding us that we are on the welcoming committee for Jesus' return, not the planning committee.

Join us each week as we lift our eyes and hearts to the hope found in Jesus Christ, embracing the joyous promise of His eternal glory and unending peace. Don't miss this opportunity to deepen your understanding and strengthen your faith.

snippet.title: Finding Joy in Faith and Trials
snippet.description:
Join us as we conclude our series on Acts and prepare to embark on a new journey through the Book of Revelation next week. We'll explore the unstoppable, Spirit-empowered plan God has for us, and how we're called to be faithful even in trials.

Let’s worship together, pray, and commit to living out our faith with joy and purpose. Remember, our story is part of the ongoing Acts of the Apostles—how will you write your chapter?

Highlights:

*Embracing change and finding joy in the journey
*Reflections on the Book of Acts and the power of the Holy Spirit
*Encouragement to be faithful in trials and share the good news of Jesus

Thank you for being a part of our community. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more uplifting messages!

snippet.title: Finding God in Every Moment: How to Live Faithfully
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore how to live a life faithful to King Jesus, learning to handle every moment with wisdom and grace. In this sermon, Pastor Pierce Drake shares insights from the Book of Acts and how we can be expectant of God’s spoken word in our daily lives. 

Discover how to recognize and respond to God’s presence and guidance, ensuring that we reflect His love and truth in every situation. 

Whether you’re dealing with a crisis or just navigating everyday moments, this message will encourage and equip you to live faithfully sent by King Jesus.

snippet.title: Embracing Crisis as Opportunity: Paul's Unstoppable Mission
snippet.description: Join us today as we dive deep into the Book of Acts, exploring the powerful mission and unwavering faith of the Apostle Paul. Discover how crises can become turning points for growth and divine opportunities, just as Paul’s journey to Jerusalem demonstrates. From dramatic encounters to profound lessons, this sermon will inspire you to see your own challenges through the lens of faith and transformation. Don't miss out on this uplifting and empowering message. Let's grow together in our understanding and love for Jesus Christ!

snippet.title: Wake Up and Trust in God's Plan
snippet.description:
In today's message, we dive into the unwavering faithfulness of God, even during the peaks and valleys of our lives. We remind ourselves that Jesus Christ is the same yesterday, today, and forever. Join us in celebrating His goodness and exploring the powerful call to "wake up" and stay alert to God's work in the world and within us.

📖 Scripture Focus:

Acts 20: Paul’s journey and the importance of gathering together

Revelation 3: The call to the Church of Sardis to strengthen what remains

✨ Key Points:

*Faith in All Seasons: Whether on the mountaintop or in the valley, God's faithfulness never wavers.
*Wake Up Call: An urgent message for the church to stay awake and be vigilant in our faith.
*Prayer and the Word: The power of prayer and scripture in guiding and strengthening us.
*Community and Gathering: The irreplaceable value of gathering together as a church family.

Don't miss any of our messages! Subscribe and hit the notification bell to stay updated with our latest messages.

Let's wake up to the calling of Christ and live out our faith boldly!

snippet.title: Taking Our Faith Beyond the Church Walls
snippet.description:
In this week's message, we reflect on the profound joy and necessity of taking our faith beyond the walls of the church. Moments of collective worship are powerful, but our calling extends into the community, especially during times of disaster and hardship.

Join us as we dive into:

The importance of worshiping in the marketplace, inspired by Paul's example.

The resilience and joy found in worshiping even in the midst of power outages and challenges.

How our attitudes and actions during difficult times can be a powerful testimony to those around us.

This message is a reminder that no matter the storms we face, we can find strength and peace in praising God. It’s a call to be the hands and feet of Jesus in our communities, spreading His love and hope.

🙏 Prayer: "Father, may we be bringers and breathers of peace in a chaotic world. Use us to share Your love and hope with those around us. Thank You for the opportunity to worship together and to take Your light into the world. Amen."

📖 Scriptures Referenced:

Psalm 46:10
Romans 12:9
James 1:2-4
Matthew 6:34

snippet.title: The Power of Jesus in the Midst of Trials
snippet.description: Join us as we dive into the trials and triumphs of the Christian journey, exploring Acts 13 and 14. Learn how Paul and Barnabas navigated persecution and continued to spread the Gospel with unwavering faith. Be inspired to endure hardships, strengthen your soul, and find encouragement in the truth that Jesus is worth every single step.

snippet.title: Peace and Freedom Through Prayer
snippet.description:
As we dive into the story of Peter in Acts, we see the church's role in bringing peace and freedom through earnest prayer. The power of prayer can set captives free and bring peace that surpasses all understanding.

This message also touches on the personal struggles many face, including feelings of inadequacy and fear. We are reminded that being vulnerable and honest before God and others can lead to profound healing and freedom.

Join us in this journey of learning what it truly means to be the church—a place to come, be, breathe, and be activated. Let us embrace the rhythm of prayer and unity, knowing that through our prayers, the kingdom of God expands, and lives are transformed.

snippet.title: The Power of God's Inclusive Love
snippet.description: Discover the power of God's inclusive love, a cornerstone of Christian faith that invites everyone into a relationship with Jesus Christ. Reflect on the biblical stories of Cornelius and Peter, and Jesus's parables of the lost, which emphasize the breaking down of barriers and the joyous celebration of every soul's return. Challenge yourself to confront prejudice and extend hospitality, embodying the church's mission to be a welcoming home for all.

snippet.title: God's Relentless Love and the Power of Baptism
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of God's love and the significance of baptism in this insightful discussion. Learn about the early church's perseverance, Philip's evangelistic encounter with the Ethiopian eunuch, and the importance of scriptural guidance. Witness Saul's life-changing conversion and Ananias's faithful response to God's call. This video looks at the universal call to faith and the impact of God's grace on our lives. Join us in reflecting on how we can share Jesus's love and truth, and be inspired to live out the Gospel in every aspect of life.

snippet.title: Unity in the Body of Christ
snippet.description: What does unity truly look like in the body of Christ? Join us as we consider the courageous example of Stephen in the book of Acts and the transformative power of a united church in the world. We'll look at how our commitment to oneness is not just a reflection of our faith, but a beacon of hope to the world. We'll explore the critical importance of unity within the Christian community, as it reflects the core message of reconciliation in the Gospel. Unity is not just an ideal; it's a reflection of our relationship with God, made possible through Christ, and it serves as a powerful witness to the world of God's love.

snippet.title: Sent by King Jesus - Brian McCormack
snippet.description: Discover the transformative call to live a life sent by King Jesus, characterized by peculiar unity, powerful proclamation, and the readiness to face opposition with courage. Embrace a life of purpose and mission, demonstrating radical generosity and love, and anticipate divine assistance in the face of challenges. Find joy in being part of God's redemptive work, despite the cost, and step into a week filled with opportunities to reflect Jesus's love in your community. Join us in discovering the priceless joy of being part of something greater.

snippet.title: Living with Boldness and Conviction
snippet.description:
Discover how the early church's boldness and conviction can inspire our modern lives. Learn how to keep Christ at the center, experience the miraculous, and respond to God's call with courage. Join us as we discuss the importance of being a witness in today's world, embracing God's interruptions, and living with the spirit of the early church. Don't miss out on this powerful message—subscribe and share with others who are looking for hope and guidance in their faith journey.

#Faith #Christianity #Boldness #Miracles #EarlyChurch #Witness #Conviction #ChristCentered #GodsPresence #SpiritualGrowth

snippet.title: The Power of Pentecost
snippet.description:
Join us as we discover the significance of Pentecost and the power of the Holy Spirit in our latest sermon. Discover the meaning behind the wind, fire, and tongues experienced by the disciples and how this event continues to shape our faith today. This sermon explores the role of the Holy Spirit in the church's mission and in our personal lives. Whether you're seeking understanding of the Trinity, looking to learn more about the Holy Spirit, or curious about the origins of the church, this video provides insights into living a life guided by the Holy Spirit. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages and explore how you can walk in the Spirit's power every day.

#HolySpirit #Pentecost #Church #Faith #Gospel #ChristianLiving #SpiritualGrowth #Trinity #Unity #Hope #Sermon

snippet.title: The Essence of Faith
snippet.description: Explore the core elements of Christian faith with our latest sermon on the essence of faith. Discover the significance of the resurrection of Jesus, the Kingdom of God, the Holy Spirit, and our mission as God's witnesses. This sermon unpacks the simplicity of our calling and how to live out our faith with purpose. If you're searching for spiritual growth, understanding the Holy Spirit, or seeking to deepen your belief in Jesus' resurrection, this video will guide you. Join us in embracing our unique role in God's tapestry and learn how to let the light of Christ shine through you. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages and share this video to spread the word of God's love and salvation.

snippet.title: Joseph - The Purpose Behind Life's Detours
snippet.description: Join us for a powerful sermon on the story of Joseph from Genesis, where we learn about the importance of trusting God's plan, even when He seems silent. Discover the significance of dreams, the purpose behind life's detours, and the value of taking a long-term perspective on God's work in our lives. Whether you're facing challenges or seeking direction, this message will inspire you to hold onto the dreams God has given you and to trust in His presence and purpose.

snippet.title: Trust in God's Plan - Rev. Karen Tyler
snippet.description: Discover the profound lessons of faith, perseverance, and God's unwavering faithfulness amidst life's trials. Joseph's journey from favored son to slave, and then prisoner, teaches us the importance of trusting in God's plan, even when faced with injustice and adversity. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking encouragement and strength during challenging times. Don't miss the opportunity to deepen your understanding of perseverance as a spiritual gift and learn how to maintain joy in your faith journey. Subscribe to our channel for more uplifting messages and be sure to hit the notification bell to stay updated on our latest sermons.

snippet.title: How to Trust God in The Midst of Trails
snippet.description: Discover the transformative power of perspective in our latest sermon, "Not Forgotten: Trusting God in the Midst of Trials." Join us as we explore the biblical stories of Joseph in prison and the Apostle Paul's teachings on rejoicing in hardship. Learn how to shift from a 'glass half empty' mindset to one of hope and expectancy, even when you feel overlooked by the world. This sermon will inspire you to remember God's presence, believe in His plan, pray with sincerity, wait with anticipation, and praise Him in every season. Whether you're facing personal valleys or standing on mountaintops of joy, there's a fresh revelation waiting for you. Don't miss this powerful message that will strengthen your faith and help you see that you are never forgotten by God.

snippet.title: How to Face Your Past and Find Forgiveness
snippet.description: If you have ever struggled with facing your past and are looking for ways to find forgiveness, this message is for you. Join us for a powerful message on the story of Joseph and his brothers from Genesis 42, where we explore the themes of guilt, shame, and redemption. Travel with us through Joseph's emotional journey as he confronts his brothers after years of separation, leading to a poignant discussion on the importance of facing our past and seeking forgiveness. This message is a must-watch for anyone struggling with the weight of past mistakes and looking for a way to find freedom and healing. Discover how confession, community support, and prayer can transform your life. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video with those who need to hear about God's grace and mercy.

snippet.title: The Power of Forgiveness
snippet.description:
In this moving message focusing on the life of Joseph and the power of forgiveness, discover how Joseph's story teaches us to overcome guilt and shame, and how to use the freedom we receive from God's forgiveness to extend grace to others. Learn from Jesus' teachings in Matthew 18 about the boundless nature of forgiveness and the importance of forgiving others as we have been forgiven. This message is not only a call to reflection but also a call to action, inviting us to live out the freedom and peace that comes from a forgiving heart. Whether you're struggling with letting go of past hurts or seeking to understand the depth of God's grace, this sermon will guide you towards a life of forgiveness and reconciliation.

 #Forgiveness #JosephsStory #ChristianLiving #Grace #Communion #GenesisSeries #ChurchSermon #BibleTeaching #SpiritualGrowth #FaithInAction

snippet.title: God's Unchanging Promises
snippet.description: In this message, we uncover the challenges and triumphs of the faith journey, navigating through unexpected twists and turning points with unwavering trust in God's unchanging promises. We'll explore the parallels between Abram's journey and our own experiences, finding encouragement to step out in faith even when faced with uncertainty. Be encouraged to anchor your faith in God's unchanging promises and engage in spiritual warfare with confidence and victory.

snippet.title: Unwavering Faith and Ordinary Obedience | Altars
snippet.description: In today's message, we'll discover how Abram's (later called Abraham) ordinary obedience and unwavering faith helped him navigate through uncertainty and into God's promises. We'll look at the significance of altars in Abram's story, unpacking their symbolism and relevance in our lives today. Altars signify not just worship, but a declaration of citizenship in the Kingdom of Heaven amidst earthly uncertainties. Join us as we unravel the layers of Abram's encounter with God as he embarks on a journey of faith and obedience.

snippet.title: Finding Peace and Purpose in Chaos
snippet.description: Join us as we continue our series looking at the Altars of Genesis in Genesis chapter 13, exploring the profound significance of the Altar of Peace and Prayer. In this powerful message, we uncover timeless truths that still resonate with us in 2024, revealing how the decisions we make can shape our journey towards peace amidst chaos. From Abram's journey of faith to the lessons we can glean from his struggles, we discover the importance of seeking God's guidance in every aspect of our lives. Don't miss out on this insightful exploration of biblical wisdom and its relevance to our modern-day challenges.

snippet.title: God's Promises in Our Trials
snippet.description: Today we're exploring how God's promises intersect with our most challenging trials. Discover the power of unwavering faith, as Abraham's obedience leads to divine provision. Learn how to trust in God's unfailing love even in the face of uncertainty. This message will equip you to walk boldly in faith, knowing that God is always faithful to His promises. Tune in to strengthen your spiritual journey and witness the transformative power of faith.

snippet.title: Faith, Adversity, and Leaving a Spiritual Legacy
snippet.description: In today's message, we're exploring the powerful themes of faith, adversity, and leaving a spiritual legacy in this inspiring sermon based on the life of Isaac from Genesis 26. We'll talk about how to resist temptation, embrace God's presence, and build altars in your life that honor Him. Whether you're facing personal challenges or seeking to deepen your faith, this message will encourage you to dig new wells of spirituality for future generations. Join us for a journey through scripture that will strengthen your walk with God and inspire you to climb the summits He has prepared for you.

snippet.title: Encountering God with Expectancy
snippet.description: Join us as we look a the life of Jacob from Genesis and learn more about his transformative journey from self-reliance to building altars of worship and submission to God. We'll share about the importance of expectancy in worship, remembering God's faithfulness, repenting from idols, and returning to true worship. This message will inspire you to build your own pillars of commitment to God, just as Jacob did. Whether you're feeling distant or seeking a deeper connection with God, this sermon is for you.

snippet.title: Our Identity in God | A Journey Through Genesis
snippet.description: We're going on a journey through the Genesis story, unveiling the profound truth about our identity in God. Join us as we explore the significance of being formed by God's hand, carrying His image, and breathing in His life-giving breath. Discover how understanding these foundational truths can reshape your perspective on life, purpose, and fulfillment. Don't miss out on the transformative message that reminds us of our intimate connection with the Creator.

snippet.title: The Message of Genesis: Creation, Temptation, Redemption
snippet.description: In this sermon we're diving deep into the message of Genesis. We'll unpack the rich tapestry of Genesis, exploring themes of creation, temptation, and redemption. Join us as we journey through the Word, unraveling its layers and uncovering the divine truths within. Discover the significance of the Tree of Life and the Tree of Knowledge of Good and Evil, as we navigate the complexities of human nature and God's unwavering love. Through thoughtful analysis and heartfelt dialogue, we invite you to engage with scripture in a meaningful and transformative way. Whether you're seeking spiritual guidance or simply curious about the mysteries of faith, our channel offers a sanctuary for exploration and enlightenment. Join our community as we embark on a quest for deeper understanding and connection with the divine. Subscribe now and embark on a journey of discovery with us.

snippet.title: Embracing the Wonder of Christmas
snippet.description: In the hustle and bustle of our fast-paced lives, it has become all too easy to speed through Christmastime rather than anticipate and celebrate the true miracle of the season — the promise of love and joy captured in Jesus’ birth. Anticipation is not only a countdown to a day on the calendar, but also a journey of the heart. This holiday season, we invite you to pause, take a deep breath and rediscover The Wonder of It All.

snippet.title: The Wonder in the Waiting | Advent
snippet.description: This Advent season, is the wonder really in the waiting? We all face moments of anticipation and uncertainty, and in this message, we explore how to find God's wonder and purpose in those seasons of waiting. We'll learn how Mary's faith in the midst of her waiting can inspire us to hold onto belief, embrace community, and experience the deeper waters with God. Hope you'll join us!

snippet.title: The Wonder of Christmas: Searching for Joy
snippet.description: Christmas is full of wonder if we just have the eyes to see it. Dive into the message where we unravel the significance of the Magi's search for the newborn King and discover the joy that comes from pursuing Jesus. From childlike wonder to the depths of waiting, each step in our journey unfolds a greater understanding of God's promises. Embrace the darkness, acknowledge the messiness of the world, and find the light that leads to everlasting joy. Don't miss this inspiring exploration of The Wonder of it All, as we celebrate the season with worship and reflection.

snippet.title: Finding Peace in the Unexpected
snippet.description: God can show up in the most unexpected places sometimes, and it's there that we can also find peace. Share in the wonder of the season and understand that even in the midst of challenges, the message of peace and hope is for everyone. As we journey through the shepherds' perspective, Pastor Pierce highlights the transformative power of encountering God's message and how it can bring us peace that surpasses understanding.

snippet.title: The Holy Spirit is Our Helper
snippet.description:
In today's service, we're starting a new series about the Holy Spirit, focusing on the Holy Spirit as our Helper. Imagine having a guide like when you visit a new place. The Holy Spirit is like that, guiding us to understand the beauty of Jesus and His work.

We'll explore passages from the Bible and how the Holy Spirit has been a Helper throughout history. So, grab your Bibles, sit back, and let's dive into this exciting journey together.

snippet.title: Sanctification and the Holy Spirit
snippet.description:
Today, we're exploring what it means to pursue sanctification with the guidance of the Holy Spirit. Get ready to be empowered!

In this message, we discuss:

- The inspiring journey of Jeremiah Lere
- The Holy Spirit's desire to work within us
- The process of sanctification and pursuing holiness
- The Holy Spirit's role in convicting the world of sin, righteousness, and judgment

Join us as we learn how to live a heavenly life in a challenging world and discover the transformative power of the Holy Spirit. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell to stay updated with our uplifting content!

snippet.title: How does the Holy Spirit guide us?
snippet.description: Today, we dive into the topic of the Holy Spirit as your guide in life. Join us as we explore the ways the Holy Spirit speaks to us and how we can discern God's will in our everyday experiences. We'll also discuss how the Holy Spirit guides us through scripture. You'll discover that the Holy Spirit is here to lead you in the right direction and help you make choices that honor God's will. 📖

snippet.title: How do I experience the Holy Spirit? | Dr. Jeff Olive
snippet.description:
If you've ever asked yourself, "How do I experience the Holy Spirit?" or "What's my spiritual gift?" this video is for you. In this video, we're going to explore the exciting journey of experiencing the power of the Holy Spirit in our lives. We'll also discuss the difference between knowing about the Holy Spirit and experiencing His presence. 

Don't forget to subscribe, like, and hit the notification bell to stay updated with our future messages!

snippet.title: The Holy Spirit is Our Comforter
snippet.description: In this video, we continue our incredible series on the Holy Spirit talking about how the Holy Spirit is our comforter. Maybe you haven't even realized it was the Holy Spirit at work, but looking back, you can see His presence during moments of healing, comfort, and incredible power. Join us for an inspiring message and a powerful reminder of God's love and presence. 📖🙏

snippet.title: Holy Spirit Stories: Judges Chapter 6
snippet.description:
As we wrap up our series on the Holy Spirit, we're diving into Judges Chapter 6, exploring the captivating stories of the Holy Spirit at work throughout history. Discover the unexpected ways God uses ordinary people to accomplish extraordinary feats. If you're facing battles and challenges, remember, you are not alone, and God has a word of hope just for you.

🙌 Join our church community by subscribing for more inspiring messages and uplifting worship. If you're new here, consider this a virtual high-five – we're thrilled to have you with us!

snippet.title: Sabbath Rest and Reflection
snippet.description:
In this message, Pastor Mark Sorensen takes us on a journey as we discover what the Sabbath is all about. You'll hear about the beauty of God's rest, the origins of Sabbath, and why it matters to both the Old and New Testament. Plus, get ready for a powerful definition of Sabbath that will inspire you to make space for rest and reflection.

So, sit back, relax, and enjoy this inspiring message. Don't forget to hit the like button, subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content, and share this video with your friends and family. Let's spread the message of Sabbath and the importance of finding rest in God's presence.

#sabbath #shabbat #rest #reflection #churchonline

snippet.title: How to Rest in a World that Never Stops
snippet.description:
How do we rest in a world that never seems to stop? Today's message delves into the significance of the Sabbath, the need to break free from the stronghold of perfectionism, and the powerful truth that, in God's eyes, we are more than enough just as we are. We're reminded that the idea of abiding in God's presence is not only simple but also profoundly transformative. In our busy, overworked lives, it's easy to lose sight of the rest and stillness that God offers us.

Don't forget to tap the "Like" button, share this profound message with your friends and family, and subscribe to our channel to stay connected with our church family.

🔗 Links mentioned in the sermon:

Last week's sermon on the origin of Sabbath: https://youtu.be/ShWM7jZDX_Y?si=NGwOvEu4rylud_46

#onlinechurch #livechurch #shabbat #restwithjesus #sabbath

snippet.title: Resting with Jesus
snippet.description:
We're so glad you could join us today as we delve into the beautiful concept of Sabbath and what it means to truly rest in our busy lives. Join us as we learn about the rest that Jesus offers, the kind that can calm the storms of our lives and bring peace to our souls. We hope that by the end of this service, you'll feel like you've just taken the greatest nap of your life, refreshed and renewed.

Don't forget to hit that like button, subscribe, and ring the notification bell to stay updated with our latest content!

snippet.title: Find Delight in God's Presence: Isaiah 58
snippet.description:
As we continue our series on Sabbath, we dive into Isaiah 58 and explore how to find delight in God's presence, even in our busy lives. Discover ways to connect with God, appreciate His unique design for each of us, and enjoy His presence in community. Let's grow together!

Don't forget to hit the like button, subscribe to our channel, and ring the notification bell so you never miss an encouraging message. Share this video with friends and family to spread the love and joy of the Lord! 🙌

Like this video? Stay tuned for more uplifting content as we continue our Shabbat series.

snippet.title: A Lifestyle of Worship
snippet.description: Worship isn't just a Sunday event but a lifestyle that can transform your entire life. In this message, we're continuing our series on Sabbath by exploring the essence of worship from both a heavenly and personal perspective. We'll take a journey through the book of Revelation, unlocking a breathtaking vision of worship in the presence of God.  Join us on this journey of worship to draw closer to our Heavenly Father together.

snippet.title: Sabbath, Songs, and Sacred Moments
snippet.description:
In this message, we explore the beauty of Sabbath, the power of worship, and the sacred moments that shape our faith journey as our pastors and worship leaders share their personal experiences, struggles, and insights in a relatable way. Plus, we discuss the joy of giving away our gifts to the community and the world.

🌟 Highlights:

Sabbath: Discover the importance of taking a day to rest, worship, and listen to God's heartbeat.

Songs of Worship: Hear from our talented worship team about the inspiration behind our latest album release from Bristol House. 

New Room Conference: Explore the insights and blessings from this year's conference, and how the Holy Spirit is moving.

If you enjoy this message don't forget to hit that like button, subscribe to our channel, and share this video with your friends. Let's spread the love of Christ and inspire others on their spiritual journey. 🙏

snippet.title: Discovering Jesus: The Supreme Creator and Redeemer
snippet.description: In this message, we'll explore the powerful words from the book of Colossians, where the Apostle Paul reminds us of Jesus' supreme role as the Creator and Redeemer. We'll learn how Jesus created all things and how His sacrifice on the cross redeemed us, bringing us back into a loving relationship with Him. Let's dive into the message and discover the heart of the Gospel!

snippet.title: Keeping Jesus as the King of our Lives: Colossians 2
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore the incredible journey of John Sung, a man who blazed a trail of Methodist Ministry across China and Southeast Asia. In this heartwarming and inspiring story, you'll discover how John Sung's passion for the Lord and his academic excellence led him to a life-transforming encounter with Jesus. From drifting away to a powerful transformation, John became a devoted preacher of the Gospel, touching the lives of thousands as he traveled and preached the message of Christ's loving and liberating hand.

In this service, we'll also explore the message of Colossians 2:6-10 and learn how to keep Jesus as the one and only King of our lives. Discover the importance of living in God's Kingdom, not conforming to the pressures of the world, and finding true completeness in Christ alone.

snippet.title: Becoming More Like Jesus Every Day
snippet.description:
As we continue our sermon series on Colossians, we're diving into how we can become more like Jesus. Discover what it means to live a life that reflects Jesus and how we can root ourselves in a holy posture with Him. As we grow in our faith, we learn to set our hearts and minds on things above, embracing a life filled with love, forgiveness, compassion, and kindness. Let's journey together towards becoming more like Jesus every day!


Web:  https://www.twmc.org/harvest

snippet.title: Deepen your Prayer Life and Confidently Share the Good News
snippet.description:
Don't miss this opportunity to delve into the heart of God's Word and learn how to deepen your prayer life and confidently share the good news. Join us for an inspiring message as Pastor Pierce wraps up our Colossians series talking about the power of prayer and reaching the world for Christ. We explore the power of vulnerability in our relationship with Jesus, the significance of dedicated prayer, and the call to share the gospel with the world around us can make a difference. 

Next week, we'll start a new series "Shabbat," focusing on resting with Jesus in the midst of life's challenges. It's a message we all need to hear. We hope you'll join us!

snippet.title: Envy: Learning to Be Happy with What You Have
snippet.description: Are you envious of others, or are you happy with what you have? Join us as we explore the topic of envy in this week's sermon. We'll learn about the dangers of comparing ourselves to others and wanting what they have. Through relatable examples and stories, we'll discover how to be content with who we are and what we have. Come and find out how we can overcome envy and embrace a more joyful and grateful life.

snippet.title: Understanding the Sin of Sloth: The Fourth Deadly Sin
snippet.description: Join us as we continue our series on the Seven Deadly Sins as we explore the sin of sloth and its impact on our lives. Discover the biblical definition of sloth and how it goes beyond mere laziness. Dive into Scripture and learn what Jesus has to say about this deadly sin. Find out how sloth affects our relationships with God, ourselves, and others. Gain insights into the virtue of sloth and how we can live a purposeful life. Don't miss this powerful message that reminds us of the freedom and abundant life found in Christ.

snippet.title: Overcoming Greed and Embracing Generosity
snippet.description: How can we overcome greed and embrace generosity? Join us for the latest message in our summer sermon series on the seven deadly sins. In this fifth week, we delve into the topic of greed and its implications for our spiritual lives. Our guest speaker shares a powerful quote that challenges us to examine our hearts: "You cannot be full of the Holy Spirit and full of the love of God if you are full of yourself." Through an exploration of scripture and real-life examples, we uncover the distortions caused by greed and discover the antidote to this deadly sin. Don't miss this opportunity to gain a deeper understanding of how we can be rich toward God and live a life of generosity.

snippet.title: Finding Contentment and Freedom from Sin - Understanding Gluttony
snippet.description: Jon us as Pastor Mark Sorensen shares his insights on finding contentment and freedom from sin, specifically focusing on the topic of gluttony. Discover how indulging in excess can lead to spiritual separation and how God offers true satisfaction and fulfillment. We'll explore the topic of gluttony and its impact on our lives and learn how to find contentment in Christ and embrace His all-satisfying love. This message will encourage and challenge you to live a life pleasing to God.

snippet.title: The Seven Deadly Sins: A Journey to Freedom
snippet.description:
Join Mark Sorensen as he introduces this powerful series on the seven deadly sins. Discover where these sins originated and why it's important to understand them. Explore how these sins can affect our lives and learn about the virtues that counteract them. Get ready for an exciting journey of self-discovery and freedom! 

#sevendeadlysins #thewoodlandsmethodist #harvest #onlinechurch #freedom

snippet.title: Understanding and Resolving Anger
snippet.description: Understanding and resolving anger in our lives isn't easy. Join us for an insightful message as Pastor Mark shares a personal story that leads into a powerful message about anger. In this engaging talk, he delves into biblical references, including Genesis 4 and Matthew 5, to explore the roots of anger and its impact on our relationships with others and with God. Discover practical steps to resolve anger, seek reconciliation, and embrace forgiveness and gain valuable insights and find peace in your heart.

snippet.title: Overcoming Lust
snippet.description: Join us as we wrap up our series on The Seven Deadly Sins and Pastor Mark Sorensen delves into the topic of lust, shedding light on its detrimental impact in our lives. Discover the dangers of idleness and the critical need to protect our thoughts. We'll explore the liberating power of Jesus and learn practical strategies to break free from the stronghold of lust. Through heartfelt prayer, honest confession, and grounding ourselves in God's Word, we can find lasting victory. Don't miss this opportunity to deepen your faith, cultivate purity, and embrace true freedom from sin.

snippet.title: How to Share God's Love and Gospel with the World - Brooke Anderson
snippet.description:
Do you have a burning desire to share God's love and the Gospel with the world? Are you seeking to become a radical messenger for God and spread His message of grace and truth to those around you? Look no further!

Becoming a radical messenger for God requires a deep commitment to His word and a willingness to step out of your comfort zone to share His message with others. However, the rewards are immeasurable. By sharing God's love and gospel with the world you can change lives, heal broken hearts, and bring hope to those who need it most.

As someone who share's God's love, you will have the chance to use your unique gifts and talents to share God's message in ways that are creative and impactful. Whether you are an artist, musician, writer, or speaker, there are countless ways to share His truth with the world.

But being a radical messenger is not only about sharing the Gospel with others. It's also about living out God's love and grace in your own life. By embodying the values of forgiveness, compassion, and kindness, you can be a shining example of God's love in the world.

If you're ready to become a radical messenger for God and share His love and message with the world, then let's get started! With your passion and dedication, and God's love and guidance, together we can change the world one message at a time.

snippet.title: Embracing our Mission as Followers of Jesus - Carolyn Moore
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore the powerful message of being the church and embracing our mission as followers of Jesus. In this inspiring talk, we learn how God can transform our lives and use us to bring hope, healing, and freedom to others. Through stories from the Bible and real-life examples, we discover that we are called to be the Tabernacle of God, carrying His presence wherever we go. From the Old Testament to the New Testament, we see a trail of God's love and power, culminating in Jesus, who showed us how to proclaim the Kingdom of God and bring light to a world in need.

Key Takeaways:

1) God can turn our struggles and challenges into opportunities for growth and sharing with others.
2) The Tabernacle in the Bible represents the dwelling place of God, and now, as followers of Jesus, we become His Tabernacle.
3) Jesus fulfilled the prophecy of Jeremiah, bringing the law of God into our hearts and empowering us to live in freedom.
4) We are called to carry the power of God and the message of the Kingdom, bringing healing and freedom to those in need.
5) Embracing our mission as followers of Jesus means taking risks, stepping out of our comfort zones, and being bold in sharing His love and truth.
6) The Kingdom of God is unshakable, and as followers of Jesus, we have the privilege to participate in advancing His Kingdom on Earth.

Come and discover how you can be part of this radical mission of love and transformation. Get ready to experience the power of God's presence and embark on a life-changing adventure as a follower of Jesus.

snippet.title: Beholding the Beauty: Pentecost and Putting Christ in His Rightful Place
snippet.description: Pentecost is a holy day where Christians celebrate the Holy Spirit coming to dwell with us and in us. In this message, Pierce Drake shares about the importance of recognizing the beauty and glory of God, emphasizing the significance of Pentecost and the role of the Holy Trinity in our lives. snippet.title: Walk by Faith: Heavenly Home | Harvest at The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Luann Riley

Let’s get on a walking program! There are many Scriptures that tell us how to walk. Enoch walked faithfully, the paralyzed man was told to “get up and walk,” and Peter walked on water. 2 Corinthians 5:7 tells us to walk by faith and not by sight. That seems like a hard assignment, especially in a world where we like to “see it to believe it.” Join us each week as we study what the Apostle Paul wrote to the church to teach them how to walk by F.A.I.T.H.

snippet.title: A Growing Church | Acts 2:42
snippet.description: In this inspiring sermon based on Acts 2:42, we explore what makes up a growing church—devotion to the apostles' teaching, breaking of bread, and prayer. Discover the significance of genuine fellowship and the transformative power of worship in building a growing church. As Pastor Drew reflects on the biblical model, we are challenged to deepen our devotion and trust in God. Be part of this dynamic community striving to be a growing church in today's world. Don't miss the insights into church growth, generosity, and living out our faith together.

snippet.title: The Ways of Jesus | Harvest at The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Mark Sorensen

We all love a “How To” book or podcast because we long to be stronger, smarter or better, but how do we learn to be more like Jesus? The 40 days of Lent is a journey towards the Resurrection of Easter day and towards learning how to follow Jesus. This Lent we will immerse ourselves in the ways Jesus lived through spiritual practices that will create a framework for our own formation. If you’ve ever wanted to learn “how to” be like Jesus, we invite you to join us in learning the ways of Jesus.

snippet.title: Making a Difference: Missions and the Power of God's Love
snippet.description:
Today, we explore the power of God's love and how we can make a real impact in the world through missions and spreading the good news of Jesus.

Rev. Karen Tyler, our missions pastor, shares personal stories and insights about how her father's influence and a four-year-old's question ignited a fire in her heart for missions. We learn how we, as a church and as individuals, can respond to God's call to make a difference. It's a message that will inspire you to take action.

Don't forget to subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content, and if you enjoy this video, give it a thumbs up and share it with your friends and family. Let's spread the love of Jesus together!

Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen, Susan Kent and Brenna Bullock

Psalm 22:3 says, “Yet you are enthroned as the Holy One; you are the one Israel praises.” We will be diving deep in our Worship in the Word series and learning the value of why our worship matters to God. Join us as we read through Scripture, hear personal stories and build our faith together. When we worship, He inhabits our praises, transforms us in His presence, and equips us to carry His love to the World.

snippet.title: Legacy: Relationships
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Stew Grant

Are we leaving a legacy? In Psalm 145:4, the psalmist declares, “One generation shall commend your works to another, and they shall declare your mighty and remarkable acts.” A lasting legacy is one that declares the works of God and passes that on from generation to generation. In this Harvest series, we’re going to look at five church markers that don’t just make an impact for Christ but leave a legacy that impacts generations to come.
