snippet.title: Lights Out: Forgotten Love
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen 

On a Sunday morning, the disciple John is living his days out in exile on the island of Patmos and goes into a cave to worship. I don’t think he’s prepared for what happens next: Jesus pays him a visit with an urgent request. Seven churches have lost their way, and Jesus wants John to send words of both encouragement and correction on behalf of the Lord to those seven churches. Let’s look at the words sent to those churches on behalf of Jesus in Revelation and ask the question, “Does this still apply to the church today?”

snippet.title: Influencers: Influencing With Encouragement
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen

Let me make a bold statement - you are an influencer! Our world tries to convince us that only people with millions of followers and celebrity status are influencers, but the truth is that you and I have been given a platform that can change lives. God can start a chain reaction of transformation through one word, one act of kindness or one prayer. In this series we’re going to identify unlikely influencers from the Bible, learn how God used them and discover the influential power of our own lives.

snippet.title: The Art of Rest: Rest for a Weary Soul
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen

In Matthew’s gospel, Jesus makes an invitation to all who are weary and carrying heavy burdens to come to Him. What awaits? Jesus says, “Rest for your souls.” Is real rest even possible today living in a world that offers anything BUT rest? In this Lenten series, we’re going to look at what it means to take Jesus up on His offer of rest and explore the need for reclaiming true sabbath in our lives. Let’s all take a breath and see where the Holy Spirit leads us in this season of Lent.

snippet.title: Ignite: The Spirit Within
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen 

Light breaks through darkness. As we enter a new year and look to a brighter tomorrow, we need that light to shine bright. We know it is the light of Christ, the power of the Holy Spirit that ignites within us, equipping us to reflect our faith and God’s grace. Once we experience this spark of light, we are inspired to share it with others and to create something bold and new. In our stewardship series, we’ll
learn how God’s light ignites our passion for ministry, our spirit of generosity and our reach to the world so we can have hope for the future.

snippet.title: Hope Revealed: Presence
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen 

More than the perfect present or Christmas decoration, there is really only one gift we need each year and that is HOPE. As we celebrate this season of Advent, it is the Hope Revealed through the gift of Jesus which reminds us we have a God who hears our prayers, fulfills His promises and surrounds us with His presence. Hope is the light which guides us and lifts us up no matter our circumstances. This Christmas, come and receive the gift of hope that Jesus offers to our weary world.

snippet.title: Generations: Intergenerational | Harvest Live at The Woodlands UMC
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Miriam Swaffield Swanson |

In the New Testament letter of 1 John, the author takes a few verses to speak some words of encouragement into the different generations to whom he is writing. To each generation, there was a word of inspiration and something to be gleaned. To the children, “I write to you because your sins are forgiven.” To the young people, he reminds them that, “they are strong.” To the parents, “I write to you because you have known the One who has existed from the beginning.” In this Harvest series, let’s see where the Word speaks into the generations present in our world today.

snippet.title: Generations: From One Generation to the Next
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen and Mark Swayze

In the New Testament letter of 1 John, the author takes a few verses to speak some words of encouragement into the different generations to whom he is writing. To each generation, there was a word of inspiration and something to be gleaned. To the children, “I write to you because your sins are forgiven.” To the young people, he reminds them that, “they are strong.” To the parents, “I write to you because you have known the One who has existed from the beginning.” In this Harvest series, let’s see where the Word speaks into the generations present in our world today.

Instagram:  https://instagram.com/HarvestTWUMC

snippet.title: Forged: The Battle for Formation | Mark Sorensen
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen

Ever heard of the phrase, “forged in fire”? The process is defined as the “making or shaping of a metal object through the process of heating it in a fire or furnace and beating or hammering it.” In this series, we’re looking at the story of Daniel in the Old Testament. Set in a time of Babylonian captivity, this story is one of remembering that, in uncertain times, God’s hands are not absent on the circumstances of our lives. We learn that even in the midst of the forging, there’s beauty and strength to be found in the art of formation.

snippet.title: TKO - How to Fight Fair: Humility | Mark Sorensen
snippet.description:
Harvest Worship 

Featuring Mark Sorensen

Let’s be honest: conflict is inevitable. Our fallen nature is prone to failings, fallouts and false assumptions. Though a life lived in Christ does not guarantee the absence of conflict, maybe there’s something deeply transformational within our disagreements. In this series, TKO, we’re going to look at Matthew 18 and examine what Jesus had to say regarding humility, honesty, and forgiveness and where those truths meet us today.

snippet.title: Experiencing the Risen Christ Every Day
snippet.description: What if you could experience the risen Christ right here right now? Discover how the Apostle Paul's message in 1 Corinthians 15 challenges us to live with the risen Christ at the forefront of our faith. Experience the story of the disciples on the road to Emmaus and learn how to recognize Jesus in every aspect of our lives. Witness the transformative power of the Holy Spirit through the life of Paul and be encouraged to pray fervently for one another. This sermon will reignite your passion for Christ and deepen your understanding of His love. Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more uplifting messages.

snippet.title: How to Experience the Love of God
snippet.description: Discover the power of the Holy Spirit and learn how to experience the love of God in a profound and daily way. We'll go through the teachings from Ephesians 3 and 1 Corinthians 13, revealing the challenges and beauty of living a life rooted in divine love. This message is not just for those seeking spiritual growth but for anyone looking to understand the depth of God's love. Whether you're struggling with faith, seeking comfort, or looking to deepen your relationship with Jesus, this message offers a powerful prayer for strength and understanding. Don't miss this opportunity to transform your life with the love of Christ.

snippet.title: The Power of God's Love: Unity and Reconciliation
snippet.description: In today's message we'll explore the transformative power of God's love and the Christian calling to unity and reconciliation. Discover how we can impact the world by embodying the love and unity that Jesus prayed for in John 17 and how Paul's prayer in Ephesians 3 can guide us to be rooted in love. This message challenges us to consider our true desire for a relationship with Jesus and to become ambassadors of reconciliation, as described in 2 Corinthians 5. Whether you're seeking inspiration, spiritual growth, or a deeper understanding of your faith, this sermon offers valuable insights into living as a new creation in Christ.

snippet.title: How to Love Like Jesus Did
snippet.description: Join us as we explore the depth and transformative power of God's love. Discover how love goes beyond feelings and becomes an action that reflects Christ's love through us to others. This message will bring to life Galatians 2:20, encouraging us to live by faith in Jesus and to share His love with the world. Whether you're looking to deepen your faith or understand how to better embody Christ's love in your daily life, this sermon will guide you on your spiritual journey. Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more uplifting messages.

snippet.title: A New Creation in Christ
snippet.description:
In this week's message, we'll dive into the Apostle Paul's teachings and learn how accepting Jesus into your life leads to becoming a new creation, where Christ lives within you. Explore the struggle between living by the flesh and by the Spirit, and find out how to embrace the fruits of the Spirit in your daily life. This inspiring message will guide you to experience God's love deeply and allow it to transform your life.

 #GodsLove #NewCreation #ApostlePaul #SpiritualTransformation #ChristianLiving #ChurchSermon #LoveOfChrist #FruitsOfTheSpirit #BibleTeaching #FaithJourney #TransformedByLove

snippet.title: How To Live an Authentic Faith
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of Christ's love with our latest message. Dive into Paul's timeless message to the Ephesians and discover how to live out your faith with authenticity. This sermon unpacks the importance of being known for our faith and love, rather than just rules or achievements. Learn how Paul's prayer for the church can strengthen your heart and grasp the vastness of Christ's love. Whether you're seeking spiritual growth, understanding of the Gospel, or ways to embody an authentic faith in Jesus, this sermon offers insights for a life transformed by faith. Don't miss out on this powerful message—perfect for those searching for Christian living, spiritual transformation, or the essence of Paul's teachings.

snippet.title: Lent and the Essence of Love
snippet.description: In this message we're exploring the essence of love and faith as we explore the profound connections between Ash Wednesday, Valentine's Day, and Lent. Join us as we reflect on the significance of baptisms, the power of prayer, and the challenges of living out our faith in a world filled with distractions.

snippet.title: The Power of Words in our Lives | Luann Riley
snippet.description: In today's message we're exploring the profound power of words in our lives. We'll dive into the timeless wisdom of Dr. Gary Chapman's "The Five Love Languages" and focus on the language of love: words of affirmation. Discover how verbal compliments, appreciation, and encouragement not only strengthen relationships but also nourish the soul. From insightful anecdotes to scientific insights, learn how positive words can transform our brains and uplift our spirits. Whether you're seeking to deepen your understanding of love or grow in your relationship with God, this message offers practical wisdom and inspiration for everyone.

snippet.title: Quality Time with God
snippet.description: In this message, Bishop Hayes shares powerful insights on the importance of finding quality time with God. Drawing from Psalms and personal reflections, we'll highlight the significance of prioritizing spiritual connection amidst life's hectic routines. Discover how to carve out moments of silence, listening, and prayer to enrich your relationship with God. Join us as we explore the transformative impact of embracing quality time with the Divine. Don't miss out on this uplifting message that promises to inspire and guide you on your spiritual journey.

snippet.title: The Five Love Languages and Our Relationships
snippet.description: Today we're continuing our series exploring the five love languages from a biblical perspective. In this message, Pastor Brent explores Gary Chapman's Love Languages, revealing how understanding these languages can transform relationships and deepen connections with God. From understanding the five love languages to exploring the significance of stewardship, this message offers insights into building stronger relationships and enriching our spiritual lives. Join us on this transformative journey as we learn to love more deeply and live more authentically.

snippet.title: The Five Love Languages: Physical Touch
snippet.description:
As part of our series on the five love languages, we're talking about the transformative power of physical touch. Learn how Jesus used touch to heal, comfort, and bless, and how we can incorporate this love language into our lives in a positive and respectful way. Whether you're seeking to deepen your relationships or understand the impact of physical touch, this sermon offers biblical wisdom and practical advice. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video! 

#lovelanguages #PhysicalTouch #ChristianLiving #JesusHealing #BiblicalTeaching #ChurchSermon #FaithInAction #SpiritualGrowth #Oxytocin #HumanConnection

snippet.title: The Love Language of Service
snippet.description: Today we're talking about the love language of acts of service and its biblical significance during Palm Sunday. Learn from the example of Mary's anointing of Jesus and how to serve others with a pure heart, just as Jesus washed His disciples' feet. This message will inspire you to worship God with complete devotion and to serve others without seeking anything in return.

snippet.title: Pentecost and the Holy Spirit
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore the power of the Holy Spirit in this Pentecost reflection. Witness the extraordinary descent of the Holy Spirit upon the early worshippers and understand its significance for our faith today. Discover how the Holy Spirit creates a welcoming space for all believers and learn about the Apostle Paul's dramatic transformation. We'll look at the Book of Acts and see how the church in Antioch models a vibrant, Spirit-led community. This sermon will inspire you to rekindle your spiritual fire and live in harmony with the Holy Spirit's guidance. Don't miss out on this powerful message—subscribe and share this message with others.

 #pentecost #spiritualgrowth HolySpirit #ChurchGrowth #ApostlePaul #SpiritualFire #ChristianFaith #Transformation #EarlyChurch #Worship #FaithCommunity

snippet.title: What We Value: Part 1
snippet.description: Today we're talking about what we value as a church and the importance of breaking free from life's routines and embracing a new rhythm that aligns with faith. We'll explore the significance of personal consecration to the Lord and the impact it can have on our daily lives. Join us in conversations about family, stewardship, and the core values shaping our church community.

snippet.title: What We Value: Part 2
snippet.description: As we continue to explore our core values in this series, What We Value, we'll unravel the layers of biblical wisdom intertwined with personal stories, highlighting the importance of living faithfully, loving compassionately, and embracing integrity and accountability in our daily lives. Discover how these timeless values resonate with the challenges and triumphs we encounter in our journey of faith.

snippet.title: A Walk Through Romans: Romans 1
snippet.description:
Join us as we embark on a journey through the book of Romans, exploring each chapter and uncovering what Paul had to say to the early church that is still relevant to us today. In this first chapter, we discuss the importance of community and being a part of the church, and how it can strengthen us as a collective force. We also set some ground rules for our study and ask for patience as we navigate this thick, theologically dense book that has informed much of Christendom. Let's dive into the first chapter of Romans together and discover what it means for us today.

Key takeaways:

- Being part of a Christian community is important for our faith
- The book of Romans is a complex but important book that has shaped Christian theology
- We should be patient with ourselves and each other as we explore this book together
- We should form our own theology based on the word of God, rather than simply accepting what someone else tells us to believe.

snippet.title: Discovering God's Love: Exploring Romans 5
snippet.description:
Join us as we continue our journey through the Book of Romans as we explore the teachings of Paul in Romans Chapter 5. Discover the surprising message that goes beyond rules and emphasizes God's goodness, love, and how it makes us righteous. Learn how suffering can lead to perseverance and hope, and find encouragement in God's unwavering love for all of us.

Web: https://www.twmc.org/woodforest
Church Online: https://woodforest.online.church/

#romans5 #romans #suffering #godslove #godsgoodness #onlinechurch #livechurch

snippet.title: Romans 6: The Amazing Story of God's Love and Our Choices
snippet.description: Join us as we continue our journey through Romans in Romans chapter 6 as we explore the incredible story of God's love and the choices we make in life. Discover how God's grace and forgiveness can transform our hearts and bring us hope even in difficult times. Dive into the story of Adam and Eve, their decision, and its consequences, and learn how Jesus came to reconcile us with God and offer us a new way of living. Find out the two different stories we can choose from and the amazing freedom found in following Jesus.

snippet.title: Romans 7 - The Two Ways of Living: Adam vs. Jesus
snippet.description: In this message, we're going through Romans 7 and looking at two different ways of living: the Adam life and the Jesus life. These two ways of living are opposite and cannot be mixed or switched conveniently. The way of Jesus is about love and downward mobility, rather than striving to be good or righteous by our own efforts. Join us as we continue exploring this powerful way of living that can transform our lives!

snippet.title: Romans 8 - From Believing and Behaving to Beholding and Becoming | JD Walt
snippet.description:
Join JD Walt as he shares an important message about the two halves of the Gospel. We'll look at how understanding and embracing the full message of Jesus can lead to personal and spiritual awakening. Come with us on a journey from "believing and behaving" to "beholding and becoming", and see how it can transform your life and relationships.

Throughout this video, JD shares insights from the book of Romans and highlights the pivotal moment where the Apostle Paul proclaims freedom from condemnation for those in Christ Jesus. Prepare to be inspired and challenged as we learn about the power of the Holy Spirit and the call to live a life filled with love for God and others.

Whether you're new to the Christian faith or have been a believer for years, this message will encourage you to go deeper in your walk with God. 

Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more uplifting content. Let's dive into this life-transforming message together! #AwakeningToTheGospel #TransformationJourney #DeepenYourFaith

snippet.title: Romans 9 - Meeting with Jesus at Church
snippet.description: Are you on a search for the right church? In this inspiring message, Pastor Brent reminds us that finding the right fit is all about meeting with Jesus. It's not about the music, the preacher, or the programs—it's about encountering the Lord and fulfilling our deep longing for Him. Join us as we explore Romans 9 and discover the amazing love and grace of God. Don't miss out on this important part of the journey!

snippet.title: Romans 10: Understanding God's Love and Grace
snippet.description: Join us as we continue our insightful study on the book of Romans as we look at Romans 10. In this week's chapter, we dive into the importance of understanding that God's love cannot be earned by following rules. Pastor Brent shares Paul's message to the believers in Rome and how it still resonates with us today. Discover the transformative power of accepting Jesus and His fulfillment of our deepest needs. Don't miss out on this enriching journey through the Scriptures!

snippet.title: Understanding Romans 9-11: God's Mercy and Grace
snippet.description: Welcome to our church's journey through the book of Romans! In this video, we dive into chapters 9, 10, and 11, exploring the themes of God's mercy, grace, and the inclusion of both Jews and Gentiles in His plan. Join us as we uncover the foundational truths of our faith and discover the depth of God's wisdom and knowledge. Don't miss out on the good stuff God has in store for you through daily readings and reflections. Get ready to be inspired and curious about what the Word of God has to say!

snippet.title: Living Sacrifice: Unity, Prayer, and Sacrificial Living | Romans 12
snippet.description: Join us for an inspiring sermon delivered by Thomas Lake, the Youth Shepherd at The Church at Woodforest. In this powerful message, Thomas shares his personal journey and highlights passages from Romans 12 about the importance of unity, prayer, and living sacrificially in the body of Christ.  Learn what it means to be a Living Sacrifice in today's world and how it can transform lives. Don't miss this transformative message!

snippet.title: Love and Sacrifice: Exploring Romans 12-13
snippet.description: Join us as we dive deep into the book of Romans, focusing on chapters 12 and 13. Uncover the profound meaning behind living a sacrificial life and embracing the commandment to love our neighbors. We'll also discuss the importance of surrendering to God's authority and walking in the light of Christ. Don't miss this opportunity to experience the life-changing impact of God's Word!

snippet.title: Loving One Another: Unity Over Disputable Matters | Romans 14
snippet.description: Hey there, friends! Welcome to our church gathering! Today, we're diving into Romans Chapter 14, where we learn about the importance of unity and love among believers. It's like this: we may have some playful differences, just like when we talk about colleges, but what really matters is how we treat and care for one another. In this message, we explore how we can focus on the main thing - loving one another - and let go of arguments over disputable matters. Let's come together, find unity, and be inspired by God's love! If you're new here, no worries! You can catch up on what we've been studying, or you can join us on this journey. Don't forget to hit that "like" button, subscribe to our channel, and share this message with others. Thank you for being a part of our church family! God bless you all!

snippet.title: Romans 15: A Message of Unity and Strength
snippet.description:
Welcome to our church community at Woodforest! We're so excited to have you join us for this inspiring sermon on Romans 15. In this message, our guest speaker Bishop Hayes shares insights into the Book of Romans, written by the Apostle Paul, and how it applies to our lives today.

Join us as we explore the meaning and message behind Romans 15, where Paul emphasizes the importance of helping others, especially those who are weak in faith. Let's discover how we can work together to build God's Kingdom and bring positive change to the world.

snippet.title: Romans 16 | Generational Faith
snippet.description:
Join us for the conclusion of our 16-week journey through the Book of Romans! As we wrap up this powerful series, we'll discover the significance of passing on the gospel message and building strong relationships in the way of Jesus. Don't miss this inspiring message that will deepen your understanding of faith and encourage you to make it your own!

snippet.description:

Good morning, neighbor! I’m glad you are here to worship God with our church family, and I trust they have already made you feel welcome. Whether you are a member of our church, an invited guest or a curious visitor, my prayer is you will find an unexplainable joy welling up in your spirit as you realize God has also arrived to meet with you here. We love having children with us in worship. We invite them forward at offering time, and then, before the sermon, they are invited to join Children’s Church. If your child (5th grade and younger) would like to attend Children’s Church, get them checked in before service. Please be sure to stop by our First Timer table or come and say hi to me on your way out. God bless you and thanks for coming!

snippet.title: Domino Effect: Jesus Christ Ascended | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Thomas Lake

Have you ever poured out dominoes, lined them up in formation and experienced the joy of watching them fall down by simply tipping the first one over? Maybe you accidentally tipped a domino over and watched your hard work topple prematurely. For the Sundays between Easter and Memorial Day weekend, we are going to unpack how God sent His Holy Spirit to accomplish a very different “domino effect” as we walk through the book of Colossians. We will see how the Holy Spirit works to exponentially grow God’s Kingdom, and we will recommit ourselves to being one of the “dominoes” in the line.


Web: https://www.twmc.org/woodforest
Church Online: https://woodforest.online.church/

snippet.title: Christoform: Made for This | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

From the moment we began a relationship with Jesus, we have been on a journey of shaping our lives into the image of Christ. From the way we think and act, to the way we love others, each day is an opportunity to align our lives to the ways and purposes of Jesus. During the 40 days of Lent, between Ash Wednesday and Easter, we will be focusing our attention on living A Jesus-Shaped Life. Join us as we consider the obedience, relationships, courage, justice, and mission of Jesus.

snippet.title: Searching for Christmas: Searching for More Hope | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Daniel Lumpee

More. We want more! But what is it that we really want more of? At this time of year, with advertisements and commercials aplenty, we could easily be lured into wanting more of the stuff that we already have — newer or bigger and better versions. Yet, most of us have lived long enough to recognize that this never has, and never will, satisfy the deepest longings of our hearts. What we really are looking
for, far more than anything else, is more joy, hope, love and peace in our lives. Between now and Christmas, our church family will be digging into God’s word to see how the coming of Jesus can bring with it these things that we so deeply need.

Web: https://www.twmc.org/woodforest

snippet.title: Are You Listening? What is Prayer and Why We Should Do It | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

Prayer is one of the most intimate acts of faith for those who believe. Not only are we talking to God, but we are hearing from Him too. What we say to God often expresses our deepest longings. We ask things of God, say things to God, and bring the needs of others to God, all in the hopes that He will respond to us with help and with greater understanding of the mysteries of life. In this series, we will take the common
themes of our prayers and unpack what the Scriptures reveal about how God has answered the prayers of His people.

snippet.title: Wish You Were Here: Bring A Friend
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

As we return home from our summer vacations and try to get back into the school year rhythm, we will surely reminisce about the great times we had in our favorite places. In so many ways, a lot of us are returning to the things of life that we have missed so dearly. We are eager to step back into some of the things that we love the most – church included. Worshipping together, drinking coffee together, learning
about the love of God together and serving together have a strange way of making us whole again. If you haven’t joined us yet, just know that we wish you were here!

snippet.title: Ordinary Time: Finding God Every Day
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

In Tish Warren’s Liturgy of the Ordinary, we find the invitation to “become aware of God’s presence in surprising ways” as we walk through the ordinary parts of our daily lives. Throughout this series, we will figuratively walk through the everyday stuff of waking up and making our beds, of checking emails and gathering around our dinner tables at the end of a day, and then looking for the opportunities to
find God “hiding” within the ordinariness of it all. Our hope is that each of us will find a new rhythm that seeks to make our ordinary life more extra-ordinary. Let’s start this morning.

snippet.title: Come Together: We Need Each Other
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

After more than a year of being told that we should stay at home away from others, many of us have settled into the unfamiliarity of loneliness and isolation. Even the church building has become a place where we have been encouraged to beware of getting too close to others. In fact, the church has always existed to be more than simply the place you go to on a Sunday morning for worship. The Church exists to be the people of God who live life together. Let’s uncover the many opportunities that we have to live this life together in Christian community.

snippet.title: Our Lord’s Prayer: Our Father In Heaven, Hallowed Be Thy Name
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

The Lord’s Prayer has been recited by individuals and groups of Christians all over the world for a couple thousand years. Whether it is worship, on a retreat, or as a family prayer before bedtime, the words Jesus taught His earliest followers to pray have been uttered countless times by countless persons. The “Our Father,” as some have called it, was likely one of the first prayers you ever heard, and possibly the first scripture you were taught to memorize. But, why do we pray it? Why did Jesus teach it to His disciples? What do we mean when we pray it anyway? Glad you asked! And, glad you’re here to unpack it with us each week through Easter.

snippet.title: Unlocking the Mind of Christ: Lessons from Paul on True Worship and Unity
snippet.description:
In this uplifting sermon, we dive into how we can truly engage in worship and live with the mind of Christ. Drawing from Psalm 103 and the Apostle Paul's letter to the Philippians, we explore what it means to fully surrender to God and embrace unity and love in our lives. Discover how Paul, even while imprisoned, found joy and contentment through his relationship with Christ. 

Join us as we learn to reflect Jesus’ humility, love, and purpose in our daily lives. Whether you're in church or watching from home, this message is for anyone seeking a deeper connection with God and a stronger sense of community.

snippet.title: Humility: The Hidden Power in a Christian’s Life
snippet.description:
Discover what the Bible teaches about this often misunderstood virtue and how it can transform your life. Learn why true humility isn't about thinking less of yourself, but about thinking of yourself less. 

Through Scripture, stories, and the wisdom of Christian leaders, we explore how embracing humility can bring you closer to God and free you from the burdens of pride and self-centeredness. 

Perfect for anyone looking to grow in their faith and understanding of God's Word.

snippet.title: Wisdom and Love: God’s Greatest Rewards
snippet.description:
In this sermon from The Woodlands Methodist Church, Bishop Bob Hayes explores the powerful connection between God’s love and true wisdom. Through the story of Solomon, who chose wisdom over wealth, we learn that real wisdom comes from understanding God’s love. 

Join us as we unpack how love and wisdom go hand-in-hand, shaping our lives and guiding our decisions. By embracing God’s love, we find peace, purpose, and the ultimate reward — a life that reflects Jesus. 

Let’s grow together in love and wisdom as we live out God’s calling.

snippet.title: Breakfast by the Sea
snippet.description:
As we wrap up our series, we explore Jesus' third appearance to His disciples after His resurrection. This encounter by the sea is a pivotal moment, reminding us of the significance of seeking God, no matter the time or place. Through the lens of John 21, we delve into how Jesus' simple breakfast with His disciples was more than a meal – it was a moment of restoration, reaffirmation, and a call to continue the mission He set forth.

Our sermon reflects on how we, like the disciples, may find ourselves drifting away from our spiritual commitments but are always called back by Jesus. The breakfast by the sea symbolizes a new beginning, a restoration of faith, and a reminder that Jesus never forsakes us.

snippet.title: The Miracle of the Loaves and Fish: Trusting in God’s Provision
snippet.description:
Today’s message celebrates God’s gift of another Sabbath and the miracle of Jesus feeding 5,000 people with just five loaves of bread and two fish. We explore how this story teaches us about faith, sharing, and trusting in God’s provision. This sermon highlights the importance of faith, trust, and recognizing Jesus’ sufficiency in our lives.

Join us for a heartfelt sermon, a beautiful prayer and the holy act of Communion. Let’s learn together how Jesus can do great things with even the smallest offerings.

snippet.title: Embracing Faith Amid Life's Storms
snippet.description:
Today, we continue our sermon series, "Summer by the Sea," reflecting on Jesus’ miracles and his powerful presence in our lives.

This week's message takes us back to the Sea of Galilee, where we witness Jesus walking on water, revealing his divine identity amidst a storm. Just as the disciples faced turbulent seas and found solace in Jesus, we too encounter storms in life where our faith is tested. As we navigate through these challenging times, remember that Jesus is our eternal lifeguard, ready to save us when we call out to him.

Join us as we explore the significance of having a lifeguard for our faith, the importance of reaching out to Jesus in our weakest moments, and the comfort of knowing that he is always there to rescue us from the depths of despair. Let's come together in prayer, reflection, and worship, and find strength in the presence of our Savior.

snippet.title: Jesus Calms the Storm
snippet.description:
Our ongoing sermon series, "Summer by the Sea," continues with this memorable story of Jesus calming the storm. Experience the tranquility and peace Jesus offers amidst life's sudden squalls and challenges.

In this reflection, we are reminded of God's sovereignty and love, even in the midst of trials. We learn that following Jesus doesn't exempt us from hardships, but it equips us to face them with faith and trust in His divine plan.

snippet.title: God's Deliverance at The Red Sea
snippet.description:
In this powerful message, we'll explore the miraculous parting of the Red Sea, a story not just of ancient history but one that continues to hold deep significance for us today. We'll reflect on how God's mighty acts of deliverance can inspire and guide us through the 'Red Seas' in our own lives – those seemingly insurmountable obstacles that we face.

🔍 Sermon Highlights:

- Understanding the historical and spiritual importance of the Red Sea event.
- How God's deliverance then mirrors His ability to rescue us from our own challenges today.
- Insights from modern science that affirm the possibility of this miraculous event.
- The ultimate power of faith and the presence of God in our lives.

Let’s gather together, whether in the sanctuary or online from around the world, to find encouragement and strength in God's word. Stand firm, be still, and witness the deliverance of the Lord.

snippet.title: Independence or Dependence?
snippet.description: Bishop Hayes concludes our powerful sermon series, "Faith Grows Here," with an inspiring message that ties together faith, patriotism, and the teachings of Jesus. Through the imagery of plants and nature, we explore how our faith can flourish when we trust in God, just as our nation has done throughout its history. Let us come together in prayer and gratitude, celebrating the divine providence that continues to guide and sustain us. As we gather to worship, may this service plant seeds of faith, hope, and unity in our hearts, reminding us of God's unwavering presence in our lives and our nation.

snippet.title: Jesus is the True Vine
snippet.description: Explore the profound spiritual truths of Jesus as the 'true vine' in John 15, where he teaches the importance of abiding in him to bear spiritual fruit. This connection is vital because, apart from Jesus, we can do nothing. By remaining in Christ, we produce the fruits of the Spirit, with love being the most significant evidence of a life intertwined with Jesus. Reflect on your relationship with Jesus and how it manifests in your daily life, ensuring that your faith journey is one of active engagement and abundant fruitfulness.

snippet.title: The Power of Mustard Seed Faith
snippet.description: Ever considered the power of a tiny seed? 🌱 This message emphasizes the beauty of small beginnings and how your mustard seed faith can grow into something extraordinary. In this message we explore the beauty of small beginnings and highlight the transformative power of God, who makes everything beautiful in its time. The parable of the mustard seed illustrates that the kingdom of God often starts small, and we are encouraged to take tangible steps to nurture our faith, like daily scripture reading and prayer, recognizing that even the smallest acts can have a significant impact in God's kingdom.

snippet.title: The Parable of the Sower
snippet.description: What kind of soil is your heart? In this message we're exploring the profound lessons of the Parable of the Sower, where Jesus teaches about the conditions of the human heart through the metaphor of soil. Discover how the seed, representing God's word, fares differently on the path of the hard heart, the rocky ground of the shallow heart, among the thorns of the crowded heart, and in the good soil of the fruitful heart. This message will challenge you to reflect on your own spiritual receptivity and consider how to cultivate a heart that embraces and bears the fruits of God's message.

snippet.title: In God We Trust
snippet.description:
Explore the power of praise and trust in God with our latest sermon, In God We Trust, inspired by Psalm 117 and the wisdom of Jeremiah. Discover the keys to spiritual growth and how to cultivate a life that bears fruit in every season. Learn how to deepen your roots in God's word and trust in His plan for you. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking to grow in faith and understanding. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages.

#spiritualgrowth #PraiseGod #TrustInGod #SpiritualGrowth #Faith #BibleWisdom #ChristianLife #Worship #DivineGardener #Scripture #GodsPlan

snippet.title: Empowering Grace - The Power of the Holy Spirit
snippet.description:
Experience the power of the Holy Spirit with our latest sermon, 'Empowering Grace'. Dive into the historical and spiritual significance of the Holy Spirit's descent and its impact on the early Church. Understand the true meaning of God's grace and how the Holy Spirit's empowerment transformed ordinary disciples into bold apostles. Learn the importance of waiting on God and inviting the Holy Spirit into your life. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking spiritual growth, empowerment, and a deeper relationship with God. Don't forget to subscribe for more inspiring messages and join us on a journey of faith, grace, and empowerment.

#Pentecost #HolySpirit #Grace #Church #Faith #Empowerment #ChristianLiving #SpiritualGrowth

snippet.title: The Power of Grace
snippet.description:
Discover the power of transformative grace in this enlightening sermon drawing from Psalm 100 and the life-changing experience of the Apostle Paul on the road to Damascus. Join us as we dive into the story of Saul's transformation into Paul and consider how God's grace might be calling you to a new path. This sermon explores the joy of worship, the importance of thankfulness, and the various types of grace that influence our spiritual journey. Whether you're seeking inspiration, looking to deepen your faith, or curious about the impact of God's grace, this sermon offers valuable insights into how God's love can dramatically alter our lives.  Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video with those who might find hope and encouragement in its message.

#TransformativeGrace #ApostlePaul #ChristianFaith #SpiritualJourney #MethodistChurch #Worship #Thankfulness #GodsLove #RoadToDamascus #GraceOfGod #SpiritualGrowth #ChurchSermon #BibleStudy #FaithInAction #WoodlandsMethodistChurch

snippet.title: God's Sovereignty: A Life Filled with Grace
snippet.description:
Living a life filled with grace also means embracing God's sovereignty. Dive into the biblical story of Joseph and learn how God's grace can turn trials into triumphs. This message will challenge you to see God's hand in every aspect of your life and to trust in His sovereignty. Whether you're facing adversity or celebrating success, this sermon will encourage you to live a grace-filled life. Don't miss this powerful exploration of faith, forgiveness, and divine purpose.

#GraceFilledLife #JosephsJourney #GodsSovereignty #ChristianFaith #InspirationalSermon #BiblicalWisdom #TrustInGod #DivinePlan #WoodlandsMethodistChurch

snippet.title: Embracing Grace: A Post-Easter Reflection
snippet.description:
This week, we're embracing grace as we gather for a powerful post-Easter reflection that explores the transformative 40 days Jesus spent on Earth after His resurrection. Discover the profound message of grace and redemption as we share about the poignant encounter between Jesus and Peter, where forgiveness and duty intertwine. This sermon will inspire you to embrace God's grace and commit to your Christian responsibilities. Whether you're seeking spiritual growth, understanding forgiveness, or looking to deepen your faith, this message is for you. 
 
#jesus #Resurrection #Grace #Forgiveness #ChristianDuty #Easter #WoodlandsChurch #Faith #SpiritualGrowth #BibleStudy #John21 #Peter #Sermon #Worship #ChristianLife #GodsLove #AmazingGrace

snippet.title: Where is Jesus? | Easter 2024
snippet.description:
Today, we're we're reflecting on the timeless message of Easter Sunday. Discover how the story of Mary's encounter with the risen Jesus prompts us to ask the profound question, "Where is Jesus?" Explore the relevance of this question in our lives today, especially in times of uncertainty, grief, and despair. Through insightful anecdotes and powerful storytelling, we learn how believing in the resurrection transforms our perspective on life's challenges.

Join us as we bridge the gap between merely celebrating Easter and truly believing in its life-changing power. Explore how embracing the resurrection message empowers us to navigate life's trials with unwavering faith and hope. Experience the profound truth that Jesus is not confined to the pages of history but is actively present in our lives, seeking to bring us comfort, renewal, and redemption.

Don't miss out on this enlightening discussion that will deepen your understanding of Easter and inspire you to live with renewed faith and purpose. Subscribe now and join our community as we journey together in faith, hope, and love.

snippet.title: Rest and Renewal
snippet.description: In this message, we'll discuss the importance of rest and renewal during the Lenten season, drawing from the Gospel of Mark and the story of Jesus inviting his disciples to rest. We'll share about the need for spiritual rest and the biblical perspective on the Sabbath, highlighting how Jesus offers a deeper rest than the law could provide. The message also touches on modern society's struggle with rest and the various methods people use to achieve it, ultimately pointing to Jesus as the ultimate source of rest for the weary. Discover how unplugging from the world and surrendering to God's grace can lead to profound spiritual healing and inner peace.

snippet.title: How do we prepare for life's challenges?
snippet.description:
How do we prepare for life's challenges? This message will encourage you to explore the theme of preparation, both in Jesus' ministry and in your own life. Reflect on the importance of being equipped for life's challenges and embracing disappointments as avenues for divine blessings. As we journey through Lent, let's prepare our hearts to embrace the fullness of life promised by God.

Join us as we uncover lessons from Jesus' prayerful preparation as he approached the cross. We'll look at how Jesus, despite knowing his impending death, sought solace in communion with his Father. Discover the pivotal moment when Jesus challenges his disciples with the question: "Who do you say I am?" and the significance of Peter's declaration.

snippet.title: Quality Time with God
snippet.description: In this message, Bishop Hayes shares powerful insights on the importance of finding quality time with God. Drawing from Psalms and personal reflections, we'll highlight the significance of prioritizing spiritual connection amidst life's hectic routines. Discover how to carve out moments of silence, listening, and prayer to enrich your relationship with God. Join us as we explore the transformative impact of embracing quality time with the Divine. Don't miss out on this uplifting message that promises to inspire and guide you on your spiritual journey.

snippet.title: Blueprint for Living: The Beatitudes
snippet.description: Today we're exploring the timeless wisdom of the Beatitudes in our series, "Blueprint for Living." In this message we'll talk about the profound teachings of Jesus from the Sermon on the Mount, uncovering the keys to living a truly blessed life amidst the challenges of the world. Join us as we decode each beatitude, contrasting it with the world's standards, and discover how to cultivate a life of spiritual richness, peace, and fulfillment. Don't miss out on this transformative journey towards understanding the essence of true happiness and fulfillment.

snippet.title: Building a Solid Life
snippet.description: Today we're talking about building a solid life using the timeless "blueprint" God gives us in His word. In this powerful message, discover the secrets of a strong foundation, drawing parallels between life's challenges and the construction of a sturdy structure. Sometimes life feels like a roller coaster but we can navigate the ups and downs with resilience and purpose. Learn from the insightful analogy of building on rock versus sand, and uncover the timeless teachings found in Matthew's gospel, chapter 7. Join us on this profound exploration of faith, wisdom, and the timeless blueprint that guides us in living a life built on Christ, the solid rock.

snippet.title: Being a Grateful Church
snippet.description: This week we're talking about being a grateful church as we explore the theme of gratitude in stewardship. Discover how, like Zacchaeus, we can experience a transformative encounter with Jesus, leading to a profound shift in our perspectives and actions. Be inspired to embrace a life of gratitude and generosity. Watch, reflect, and consider your own spiritual journey as we embark on this third week of our stewardship campaign.

snippet.title: Navigating Life's Challenges with Jesus as Our Compass
snippet.description:
In the midst of life's challenges, Jesus is our compass. In today's message, we're exploring the concept of being a guided church, drawing inspiration from the timeless teachings of Jesus. Discover the importance of having a clear direction and keeping the main thing, Jesus, at the center of your life. We'll talk about how being a guided church means ministering to the world, meeting community needs, and following the path that Jesus modeled for us. Be inspired to invest your deepest treasures in heavenly pursuits and find your way home, guided by the unchanging symbol of our faith – the cross. Don't miss this transformative message that encourages us to navigate life's challenges with Jesus as our unwavering compass. 

#GuidedChurch #Sermon2024 #JesusAsCompass

snippet.title: Generosity and the Church
snippet.description: Join us as we reflect on the church's DNA of generosity, and look at how it defines the church and shapes its identity. Whether you're attending in person at Woodlands Methodist Church or joining us online from anywhere in the world, this message invites you to consider the seven forms of generosity and the joyous blessings it brings, both to givers and recipients.

snippet.title: The Cast of Christmas: Behind the Scenes of the Greatest Story Ever Told
snippet.description:
In this special Christmas sermon, we'll explore the behind-the-scenes moments that led to the birth of Jesus and discuss the timeless significance of this extraordinary event. Share in the wonder and beauty of the Christmas story as we reflect on the characters who, though often overlooked, played crucial roles in God's divine plan. Be prepared to be inspired and reawakened to the joy of Christmas!
As we approach Christmas 2023, let's become the extras in God's story, living out the Christmas message of love, kindness, and joy every day.

snippet.title: God's Promises of Love and Salvation
snippet.description: As we continue to explore the promises God made throughout history, leading us to the birth of Jesus, we focus on Isaiah's prophecy and the assurance of a Messiah who brings love and salvation. In this message, Bishop Hayes reflects on the timeless promise of a Messiah, tracing God's plan through the Old Testament prophets to the birth of Jesus. Learn how God's promises are not only declarations but tangible expressions of His love and the gift of salvation.

snippet.title: The Wonder of It All: The Prophecy
snippet.description:
There is an unexplainable mystery that proclaims the seasons of Advent and Christmas, a story so steeped in simplicity and awe that it transcends everything we thought we knew about the God we serve. Mankind has always sought God in many unusual ways, but the Christmas story is about God
pursuing us, and on the night a child was born in the city of Bethlehem, God found us. Since then, our world has not been the same. Prophets, angels, shepherds and wise men heralded the good news,
and their message declared the greatest wonder of all: “Emmanuel — God is with us!” It is a story that never grows old, and we are delighted you are here to experience Advent and Christmas once again and to celebrate The Wonder of It All.

snippet.title: Overcoming Evil with Good
snippet.description:
Join us as we delve into the current sermon series, "Storm Warnings," with a focus on the red flag alert to the storm of evil. Learn how, as Christians, we can navigate through the challenges of life and stand strong against the winds of evil.

Join us on this journey of faith as we strive to live out our calling to be lights in a world that sometimes seems dark. Share this video with friends and family, and let's encourage one another to stand firm in the face of adversity.

snippet.title: All Saints Sunday: Weathering Life's Storms and Celebrating Loved Ones
snippet.description:
Welcome to our All Saints Sunday service at The Woodlands Methodist Church. Today, we have a heartfelt message for you. We'll be exploring the significance of this special day when we remember our loved ones who have passed away and celebrate the eternal connection we share with them.

In this video, you'll find comfort, inspiration, and a profound message of hope as we navigate the storms of life, including the ultimate challenge—death. Join us as we honor and remember those who have gone ahead of us and are now in God's presence, watching over us.

We'll also delve into the powerful words of the Apostle Paul, who, even from his prison cell, left us with an enduring legacy of faith and perseverance. Discover the true meaning of finishing the race and keeping the faith.

Don't miss this uplifting message that reminds us that, with God, we can weather any storm and celebrate the lives of those who have received their heavenly crown. If you're looking for guidance, comfort, and spiritual insight, this video is for you.

snippet.title: How do we resist temptation?
snippet.description:
How do we resist temptation in the middle of life's storms? In this message we'll explore the biblical wisdom that helps us stay strong when temptations come knocking. We'll also discover the valuable lessons from the temptations Jesus faced in the wilderness.

Join us as we dive into the power of God's Word and find out how it can be our anchor in the stormy sea of life. Remember, you're not alone in this journey – we're here with you every step of the way.

snippet.title: When God says No, His Grace says Yes
snippet.description:
In this sermon, we reflect on how even when God says no, His grace always says yes. We learn from the story of Moses, a revered figure in the Old Testament, who, despite his close relationship with God, was denied entry into the Promised Land. Explore the reasons behind God's decision and the valuable lessons we can apply in our own lives.

👉 Key Takeaways:

- Breaking faith with God.
- Recognizing God's power and glory.
- The importance of humility in our journey.
God's blessings vs. our self-reliance.
Join us as we uncover the profound message of faith, humility, and God's incredible grace that applies to us today.

snippet.title: Take This Cup From Me: When God Says No
snippet.description:
Our current sermon series, “When God Says No,” continues this week as we are taken to the Garden of Gethsemane to hear Jesus’ words of agony: “Take this cup from me.” 

What is the cup that Jesus refers to, and why would He make such a request of His Heavenly Father? But what is even more puzzling is why would God not grant permission in the final hours of His only Son’s life? These are the questions that we will address in this message - the answers might surprise you! Join us as we reflect on the significance of Jesus' sacrifice and learn to understand what it means when God says no to our requests.

snippet.title: When God Says No: Understanding God's Response
snippet.description:
Have you ever wondered why God sometimes says "no" to our prayers? You're not alone! In this series, we'll uncover the wisdom behind God's responses to our petitions.

In today's message, we explore the powerful story of the Apostle Paul and how he responded when God denied his request. It's a message of hope, humility, and discovering God's amazing grace in our trials.

#prayer #whengodsaysno #answeredprayers #unansweredprayers

snippet.title: Unity in the Church: Lessons from Romans
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore the powerful message of unity and faith in today's sermon. In this message, we'll discuss the lessons we can learn from the book of Romans and how they apply to our lives as followers of Jesus.

📖 Today's Scripture Reading: Romans 15:1-7

In this sermon, we'll dive into:

✝️ The importance of unity in the church
✝️ Overcoming divisions and finding common ground
✝️ Serving God in harmony, despite our differences
✝️ Embracing God's love and grace in our daily lives

Whether you're a long-time member of our congregation or a first-time visitor, we hope this message will inspire and uplift you. Let's come together as a church family and learn how to live out our faith in unity.

🙏 If you enjoy this sermon, please like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more inspirational messages and worship services. Don't forget to hit the notification bell so you never miss an update!

#unity #faith #unityinthechurch #romans

snippet.title: God's Master Plan | Romans 9-11
snippet.description:
Join us as we unravel the mystery of God's master plan in the book of Romans chapters 9-11. We're here to learn, grow, and find our way through life's challenges together.

In today's message:
🌿 Learn how God orchestrates His divine plan through history.
🌟 Discover the importance of being grafted into God's family.
🕯️ Be inspired to be the light for the coming generation.

Join our church family as we explore the wisdom of Romans together 🙌  and don't forget to hit that thumbs-up button, subscribe, and ring the notification bell to stay updated with our messages every week.

snippet.title: Faith, Hope, and God's Love: A Journey Through Romans
snippet.description:
Today, we continue our series, "Survival of the Fittest," where we explore the Book of Romans, digging into faith, righteousness, and what it means to be spiritually fit. Last week, we talked about righteous judgment. This week, we'll delve deeper into faith, a crucial aspect of our spiritual journey.

But here's a little story for you! While Bishop Hayes was preparing this sermon, he stumbled upon a hidden treasure - a clay coaster with a profound quote: "Faith is to believe what you do not yet see; the reward for faith is to see what you believe." 🙌✨ Talk about a God moment!

So, what does faith mean to you? How large is your faith? 🤔 Today, we'll explore these questions and dive into the incredible faith journey of Abraham, as explained by the Apostle Paul in Romans.

As we go through this message, remember that faith isn't just about believing in Jesus; it's about trusting in His promises, even in the face of adversity. When we embrace suffering and affirm the resurrection, our faith expands, making us more like Christ.

So, join us as we explore faith, hope, and God's incredible love in today's sermon. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more inspiring content. 

🔔 Stay tuned for more uplifting messages and worship services! God bless you all. 🙏

#romans #survivalofthefittest #faith #faithhopeandlove

snippet.title: Survival of the Fittest: Discovering Strength in Faith | Romans Sermon Series
snippet.description:
Join us for our traditional worship service where we explore the profound teachings of the Book of Romans in a new sermon series titled "Survival of the Fittest." Delve into the powerful truths of God's word as we discuss topics such as righteous judgment, renewal, faith, and more. This series is designed to equip and prepare us as believers to face the challenges of the world and strengthen our faith in Christ. Don't miss out on this opportunity to grow spiritually and find inspiration in God's word.

#romans #survivalofthefittest #thewoodlandsmethodist #onlinechurch #strengthinfaith

snippet.title: No Deposit, No Return: Making Meaningful Deposits for a Life of Faith
snippet.description:
In this week's sermon, we dive into the concept of "No Deposit, No Return" as we explore the importance of making meaningful deposits in our spiritual lives. Join us as we learn from the teachings of Jesus and discover how prayer, studying God's word, and following His path can lead to a life of significance, joy, and fulfillment. Don't forget to hit the like button, share with your friends, and subscribe to our channel to stay connected! 🙌

📖 Scripture Reading: Luke 14:27-33

snippet.title: Romans 15: Building God's Kingdom Together
snippet.description:
Today, we're diving into Romans 15, a powerful message from the Apostle Paul about serving others and working together to glorify God.

In this sermon, Bishop Hayes shares how the early church in Rome faced challenges and how we can learn from their experiences. We'll discover the importance of sound biblical doctrine and the relevance it holds in our lives today. Let's explore how we can be a supportive community, helping those who are weak and finding our purpose in serving God.

Come join us as we learn, grow, and strengthen our faith together. Let's leave our egos at the door and embrace the power of the Holy Spirit to make a positive impact in our lives and the world around us.

Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe to our channel for more messages and stay tuned as we continue our series on Romans. Thank you for being part of this journey with us. God bless you all!

snippet.title: Divine Interruptions: A Day in the Life of Jesus
snippet.description: Join us for this powerful message from The Woodlands Methodist Church's traditional worship service. Bishop Hayes takes us through a day in the life of Jesus, showing how even unexpected interruptions can become opportunities for God's work. Discover how Jesus used divine interruptions to reveal His power and authority, and how we can navigate the interruptions in our own lives with faith and trust. Don't miss this inspiring sermon that reminds us of God's presence in the midst of life's disruptions.

snippet.title: Patriotic Hymns: Connecting God and Country
snippet.description: In this message, we explore the deep connection between God and American patriotic songs, understanding how faith and freedom intertwine in our nation's history. Discover the stories behind these hymns and how they reflect our belief in God's providence and blessings. Let us come together  as we celebrate God and Country on this special day. Watch the message and be inspired to remember our nation's roots and the role of faith in shaping our identity.

snippet.title: Hymns of Our Fathers: Celebrating Father's Day and Worshiping God
snippet.description: Join us for a heartwarming Father's Day service filled with uplifting hymns and a powerful sermon. In this special sermon titled "Hymns of Our Fathers," we explore the profound impact of hymns that speak to our heavenly Father. Discover how these beautiful songs have shaped our understanding of God and influenced our lives. Experience the warmth of Christian love and hospitality as we come together in worship. Whether you're a father, mentor, or simply seeking spiritual inspiration, this service is for you.

snippet.title: The Promised Holy Spirit
snippet.description: Join us for an engaging message about the promised Holy Spirit and the joyous inheritance that awaits us. Discover why Paul's enthusiasm is contagious as we explore the significance of belief, being marked by the Holy Spirit, and the blessings that come with it. Get ready to be inspired and find hope in this message!

snippet.title: Forgiveness and Respect: Lessons from the Book of Philemon
snippet.description:
Forgiveness and respect are something often talked about in the Bible. In this message, Bishop Hayes shares about a lesser-known book in the Bible called Philemon. The book is a letter written by the Apostle Paul to Philemon, a fellow Christian, about forgiveness and the relationship between a master and a slave. However, the story of Philemon is important because it reveals the nature of God, forgiveness, and the inherent dignity and respect for all humanity. Philemon is a model citizen who shows that forgiveness can only be found when one follows Christ. The book is also a reminder that we should treat everyone with respect and dignity. Overall, the book of Philemon teaches us important lessons about forgiveness, respect, and treating others as equals.

snippet.title: Leave a legacy of faith
snippet.description:
What legacy do you want to leave when you're gone? What legacy do you want to leave for future generations? Will it be something based on yourself and your own accomplishments? Or will it be a legacy of faith based on all that God has done in and through you?

In this video, we're talking about the life of Timothy and the influences he had that shaped his life as a disciple of Christ. You'll see how powerful living out your faith in front of others can be in leaving a legacy of faith for the next generation.

snippet.title: Model Citizen: Joseph of Arimathea - The Secret Disciple
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

When we use the term “model citizen,” we most often think of a person living an exemplary life, possessing such qualities as honesty, integrity and truth. Individuals who demonstrate these characteristics usually stand out in a crowd and are easily recognized. However, the New Testament is full of model citizens who walked in Jesus’ footsteps but were not always given the notoriety many other disciples received. Not only were they strong in their faith, but their influence and contribution to the early church was significant. This sermon series reveals a few lesser-known followers of our Lord who serve as an inspiration to us, reminding us that we all have unique gifts to offer as we walk in the footsteps of Christ.

snippet.title: Easter: Idle Tale or Invincible Truth?
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

“He is risen!” This was the shout from the women and the disciples as they arrived at the tomb of Jesus and found it empty on that first Easter morning. Today, over 2,000 years later, our response and affirmation can be nothing less than “He is risen indeed!”

Welcome to Easter Sunday — the most important day of our Christian faith. We are delighted that you have joined us to celebrate our Lord’s victory over sin and death. May you feel God’s presence as you encounter the risen Savior through the music, prayers, Scriptures and spoken word. 

Everything we do is rooted in the Good News of Jesus Christ. Again, thank you for being with us — you are welcome here!

snippet.title: Road Trip: The Road That Leads to Calvary
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

There is a road that begins on Ash Wednesday and ends at Easter—it is called Lent. It is a 40-day journey that invites us to enter into a deeper relationship with God as we remember the sacrifice Jesus made on our behalf which led Him to the cross on a hill called Calvary. Lent is a solemn and holy season, and travel along this road demands something of us, for it is only through prayer, confession, self-examination and sacrifice that we can arrive at that destination where we fully understand the hidden possibilities that lie dormant within each of us. This road trip can become the most important journey we will ever take, for it summons us to die unto our sins so we may celebrate the Resurrection and the promise of eternal life with the One who died for us and gave Himself as a living sacrifice for all.

snippet.title: As You Wish: “Not my will, but yours...”
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

Throughout Jesus’ ministry, one remarkable truth stands out: He never imposed Himself upon any of the people He encountered. Jesus recognized the fact that God gave human beings free will and, in doing so, gave them the freedom to choose to abide in the true love of God or continue in another direction. In several instances Jesus is quoted as saying, “As you wish” or “As you choose,” knowing that the choices that are made can be the first step toward change. But when our wishes and choices take precedence over God’s plan for us, the consequences can be destructive. This sermon series will focus on us making the right choices that will help us abide in the true love God offers us.

snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

Welcome to 2023! We are so excited that you have joined us in worship, and we eagerly invite you to journey with us into this new year to see what God has in store for us. The month of January marks the 45th anniversary since our church held its first worship services in what was then a small community called The Woodlands. Since then, God has blessed us to be a “light set upon a hill for all to see,” and it is our prayer that your presence here will enable us to shine brighter than ever, all for the glory of God. We are glad you are here.

snippet.title: It’s (Not Always) a Wonderful Life: Finding Light in the Darkness | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

We now find ourselves in the season of Advent, a four-week period of preparation that culminates in the birth of Jesus. It should be a time of excitement and joy, of laughter and merriment. But for many, this season is a time of sadness, emptiness and frustration. Life should be wonderful, but how can it be when so many things take us away from the real joy of Christmas? How do we find light in the darkness, peace amid chaos and good news in a bad-news world? In this sermon series, “It’s (Not Always) a Wonderful Life,” we will rediscover the hope that comes from the faithful promises of God to bring peace through our Savior, Jesus Christ.

snippet.title: Signed, Sealed, Delivered: Suffering Is Not Forever! | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

In biblical times a seal and an insignia were often used to identify and protect anything confidential or of value. The seal specified to whom it belonged, preventing anyone else from tampering with its contents. In the book of Ephesians, the Apostle Paul compares the Holy Spirit to a seal, saying: “Having believed, you were marked in him with a seal, the promised Holy Spirit, who is a deposit guaranteeing our inheritance until the redemption of those who are God’s possession.” Once a soul has trusted in Christ, that soul is sealed and made secure in Him. In this sermon series, we will focus on the promises made on our behalf, given to us through the Father, Son and Holy Spirit, all of which have been Signed, Sealed and Delivered!

snippet.title: What Faith Makes Possible: Healed, But Not Whole! | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

The word “faith” has many meanings, but because we live in a world where most people have to “see” in order to “believe,” the idea of having faith in something for which there is no proof is difficult to accept. However, the New Testament book of Hebrews tells us that “faith is the assurance of things hoped for, the conviction of things not seen.” Jesus knew that faith was a gift from God that requires a human response. In this sermon series we will look at the stories of how faith allows us to believe in the unbelievable and make the impossible possible.

snippet.title: Invitation: Prodigal Parties | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes | 

The greatest invitation we will ever receive is to “follow” Jesus. Just as He called His first disciples to leave their nets and go with Him today, Jesus’ call is the same. He summons us to leave behind and let go of our busy and chaotic lives. He teaches us, empowers us, and offers us an opportunity to receive His salvation and go where He leads. Christ was always moving forward, and so must we. “Follow me” is still the call to abundant life, and it is our prayer we will accept His invitation to live out our faith and learn to extend the gifts He gives to others.

snippet.title: God’s Promises: God Always Wins! | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes  

Blessed assurance! Living in uncertain and unpredictable times is nothing new for God’s people. From the beginning of creation until this present day, believers have always had to contend with fear, doubt, despair and failure. At times it seems our faith is tested beyond our ability to cope, but in those moments when all seems hopeless, we would do well to remember the promises God has made to us. Let us focus on the great promises God has given us – knowing that whatever happens, God will be with us!

snippet.title: In the Name of God, Amen! | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

On this July fourth, Americans from “sea to shining sea” will mark the signing of the Declaration of Independence that happened 246 years ago. Our services will reflect the patriotism that accompanies this event by singing national hymns and honoring those who served to maintain our political freedoms and religious liberties. It is also a time for
us to remember that the scriptures say a lot about the freedom and liberty God provides. In Psalm 33:12, it says: “Blessed is the nation whose God is the Lord, the people He chose for His inheritance.” Let us remind ourselves that we have been a blessed people because God has always come first, and our independence is a direct result of our dependence upon God and the gift of Jesus Christ.

snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

So many of the convictions we hold and the truths we believe are captured in the songs we sing! The reality is, we are singing people, and music, as seen throughout the Bible, trains us in the practice of remembering who God is and what God has done for us. In the book of Psalms, we are encouraged to “Sing to him, sing praise to him; tell of all his wonderful acts” (105:2). Through the gift of music, God has united art with truth and a way for the gospel message to sink itself into our hearts through singing and sharing our faith in song.

snippet.title: Hello, My Name Is … : Perfectionist | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

William Shakespeare asked the famous question, “What’s in a name?” Names are important for our identity. There are names we are given at birth, names we use to connect or remember others, and names we use to label ourselves. In this series, we are going to look at some of the labels we wear, but we will also celebrate how Jesus can change those labels and give us a new name! Join us as we celebrate our connection to each other and say, “Hello, my name is ...”

snippet.title: Doors to Open: Door of Self-Examination | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

The 40-day season of Lent is a time when Christians all over the world renew their loyalty to our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ through acts of repentance. The word Lent means “spring,” and it signals the reawakening of our souls, of God’s renewing love that breaks through our waywardness and sins. For us to get to the glorious resurrection that awaits us, there are doors to open so this sacred season can have meaning and purpose. Our series, Doors to Open, is an opportunity for us to enter into the new life that awaits us, for “if anyone is in Christ, they are a new creation; the old has gone, the new has come!” (2 Corinthians 5:17)

snippet.title: God Didn’t Say That: What God Didn’t Say About Money | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

How sure are you when it comes to knowing what God said or didn’t say in the Bible? Let’s face it—even the most knowledgeable Christians have difficulties distinguishing fact from fiction and truth from nontruth. How good are you at being able to identify misleading quotes and stories that have somehow filtered into the mainstream of God’s Word and teachings? It is truly amazing how the “accumulated baggage” of not knowing what God said has weighed us down as modern-day disciples. This three-week sermon series is designed to open our eyes and better our understanding of what God did and didn’t say about happiness, the burdens we bear, and yes, money! You don’t want to miss this entertaining and enlightening series!

snippet.title: Growing Together: Outward Focus | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

When God created the “heavens and the earth,” every living thing that was made was designed to grow. It is the natural order and cycle of life. But growth can be both physical and spiritual, and this is where the summons of Jesus comes to us, inviting us to become more like Him by choosing an intentional path that leads to life. When we cultivate our faith, love for each other and our neighbor, we discover the true meaning of life, and we discover more about ourselves. Join us as we accept Christ’s invitation to grow together, thereby fulfilling God’s great design that every living thing should have life in all of its abundance.

But growth can be both physical and spiritual, and this is where the summons of Jesus comes to us, inviting us to become more like Him by choosing an intentional path that leads to life. When we cultivate our faith, love for each other and our neighbor, we discover the true meaning of life, and we discover more about ourselves. Join us as we accept Christ’s invitation to grow together, thereby fulfilling God’s great design that every living thing should have life in all of its abundance.

snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

Our Christmas Eve worship services are some of the most cherished and beautiful gatherings in the life of our church. These services signal that we have reached our limits with the busyness of the season—the gift buying is over, our families are together, and we can finally focus on celebrating the birth of our Savior, Jesus Christ! This Christmas Eve, we go in search of the light that illumines our world and our lives, and our presence here tonight proclaims that no matter how dismal things may be, the light of Christ shines in the midst of our darkness, and the darkness has not overcome it.

snippet.title: Searching for Christmas: Searching for the Obscure | The Woodlands Methodist Church
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Bishop Bob Hayes

Have you ever thought about how much time we spend searching for things like our car keys, a special restaurant, or that hard-to-find ingredient for the next recipe? snippet.title: Becoming: Converted
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

The essence of our sermon series, Becoming, is best captured by the pen of Dr. Gardner Taylor. He writes, “There hangs over each of us the awareness of moving toward something, of becoming something far finer than we have ever been. Ah, we may wince, but we are never for long free of that yearning to become better, that instinctive squirming to be let loose from some imprisoning and crippling web in which we are caught. This sense of inward struggle toward something, of awareness of some huge, approaching wonder forms the basis for the earth’s finest literature, informs and indwells the world’s worthiest crusades and fashions the splendor, the most glorious splendor of humanity.”

snippet.title: The Rest of the Story
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

The resurrection of Jesus on that first Easter morning goes to the heart of everything Christians hold dear and sacred. The empty tomb is the bedrock and foundation of our faith. As the Apostle Paul writes, “And if Christ has not been raised, our preaching is useless and so is your faith.” (1 Corinthians 15:14) However, if we view Easter as the conclusion of Jesus’ ministry, we run the risk of missing out on some of the most important appearances that He makes following His resurrection. His words and actions during those days represent another side of the resurrection story that even most well-intentioned Christians miss. Bishop Hayes covers the “Rest of the Story,” as he shares why those days still hold importance and significance for us.
