snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

For most people, the end of 2020 can’t get here fast enough! It has pushed us to our limits in every aspect of our lives—spiritually, emotionally, physically and mentally. It has been a year of bad news on top of bad news. However, the God we serve has been at work on our behalf, and in this Christmas season brings us the Good News that “unto us a child is born, unto us a Son is given!” It’s the very best news
we need to hear, for it represents the light we need that shines in the darkness of these difficult times. Hear the good news and be encouraged.

snippet.title: Hope Revealed: Purpose
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship | Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

Throughout this very difficult year, the one word that has sustained us has been the word “hope.” It is the most precious of all human emotions, allowing our faith to believe that at any moment the God we serve will make Himself known, fulfilling our expectations. The season of Advent is that moment! It is our confirmation that God has heard our prayers and is giving us His only begotten Son, our Savior, who is Christ the Lord! Our hope has not been in vain. In these four weeks leading up to Christmas, our sermon series – Hope Revealed – will examine God’s promise, presence and purpose, culminating in the person of Jesus Christ!

snippet.title: The Mirror of Our Heart: A Sermon for Lent | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

Mirrors play an important role in our lives because they reflect how we see ourselves and how we are seen by those around us. But there is another mirror which radiates a reflection that only you and God can see, and it is the mirror of your heart! The Scriptures tell us that God doesn’t look at our outward appearance, but rather on our hearts (1Samuel 17:7), which means God has exclusive access to that inner-self, the real us that we protect and keep hidden. If this upcoming season of Lent is going to make a difference in our lives, then we must allow God to search us and know our hearts, and guide us in the path that leads to life.

We are called to a life filled with purpose and fearless faith – a life that matters. snippet.description:

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

A recent Pew Research Survey reveals that most Americans believe our society is increasingly abandoning the religious aspects of Christmas. This leads me to believe that even though we celebrate Christmas, we have forgotten to invite the “honored guest” to His own party. Christmas for most of us is simply an event, and not a way of life. This Christmas Eve re-discover how the “Spirit of Christmas” can bring us joy and happiness throughout the year. Who knows? Maybe this year we can make it happen!

snippet.description:

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

In a world that seems constantly to be in turmoil, it can be difficult to move beyond what we can see and even what we can “do” in any given situation. But God calls us to look beyond the seen . . . to the unseen; to trust that God is at work in all things. Through faith we are given the power of the Holy Spirit to move beyond our own strength, our grief, our fear and even our times of depression. Join us as we unpack what it means to move beyond the things that weigh heavy on our hearts in this world and embrace the kingdom to come.

snippet.title: The Storyteller: Parable of the Great Feast | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship 

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

Jesus was a remarkable storyteller. He possessed a superb ability to paint pictures with His words; weaving the truths of the Kingdom of God into stories that captured imaginations ... then and now. But many of these parables offer as much mystery as they do insight, especially in our modern-day world. In this sermon series we will probe the deeper meanings of Jesus’ parables as we seek to understand their significance for our own lives. Let’s allow the Storyteller to capture our hearts anew through His living Word.

snippet.title: Portrait of Jesus: His Soul | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship

Bishop Bob Hayes 

Join us as we take an in-depth look at the Man who is known more than any figure in all of human history. What was it about Him that has so captured our attention and influenced the course of civilization for over 2,000 years? More specifically, what was it about His hands, His mind, His heart, His face and His soul that fascinates us? In this series our goal is for the real Jesus to come out of the picture and meet us face to face, as living soul to living soul. Our desire is to know Him just as His disciples knew Him as Master, Savior, teacher and rabbi, and an ever-loving friend.

snippet.title: The Best of Times, The Worst of Times... |  Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

We live in an age of contradictions. For some, the road of gratitude and preparation that leads from Thanksgiving to Christmas can be a “spring of hope.” But for others, it can be a “winter of despair,” fueled by the stresses and strains of the most chaotic days of our lives. Believe it or not, God has a Word for us as we seek to find meaning and purpose in a season where we have everything, and yet, we have nothing.

snippet.title: Songs of a Lifetime: The Hymns of Fannie Crosby | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Traditional Worship

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

“Jesus loves me this I know...” Can you finish the line? As children, our hearts become stamped with lessons about Jesus and about hope, love, and grace through the songs we sing. snippet.title: Entrusted to be Renewed | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
This year we celebrate 40 years of ministry and mission to the greater Woodlands community. How  fitting that our stewardship theme for 2018 is “Entrusted” as we focus on how God has blessed us and has enabled our church to be a blessing to others – here and around the world. I believe if we take a good, long look at how God has been faithful to us by evidence of His mercy and grace, then we can respond in a way that acknowledges God’s gifts through our gifts. We have been entrusted with much and to whom much is given, much is expected. Join us as we celebrate what God has done, what He is doing, and look forward to what He will do.

Featuring Bishop Bob Hayes

snippet.description:
Jesus wanted to go deeper because he cares. He wants us to understand who we are and who God is. So He asked questions. snippet.title: Hidden Figures: The Ethiopian Eunuch — A Teachable Spirit | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
The story of God’s plan of salvation has been told through the words and actions of countless great men and women of God whose names are held up as role models — leaders like Moses, Paul and Peter. But what about Lydia, Simeon or Naaman? Hebrews 11 reminds us there are countless stories of the men and women who persevered for their faith and spread the Gospel without becoming famous and of whom we may not be aware. Today we’ll look at some of these “hidden figures” of the Bible: three mighty warriors who touched King David’s heart with an act of uncommon bravery that is still relevant in our time.

Sermon 8/06/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

Traditional Worship

snippet.title: The Way of Christ: Looking the Other Way | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
The Roman procurator known as Pontius Pilate will forever be remembered as the man who ordered the crucifixion of Christ. Though a man of unspeakable cruelty and violence, when he is presented with Jesus at his trial, Pilate realizes this man has done no wrong. He does everything he can to look the other way and evade any association with Jesus’ death, going to the extreme of washing his hands and declaring himself blameless of the blood of Christ. However, one question he puts before the crowd has haunted us for over 2000 years: “What shall we do with Jesus?” What will be our response?

Sermon 4/9/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

Traditional Worship

Web: http://www.thewoodlandsumc.org/
Facebook: http://fb.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Instagram: http://instagram.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Twitter: http://twitter.com/TheWoodlandsUMC

snippet.title: The Way of Christ: Fearful of The Way | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Fear is a two-sided coin: one side can render us helpless and timid, while the other side can be a great motivator, inspiring us to uncommon boldness. The sermon for today focuses on Joseph of Arimathea, a distant follower of Jesus who lived on the fringes and in the shadows of discipleship because he was fearful of The Way. His story reminds us that we are “more than conquerors” of our fears when we accept Jesus as our Lord and Savior.

Sermon 4/2/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

Traditional Worship

Web: http://www.thewoodlandsumc.org/
Facebook: http://fb.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Instagram: http://instagram.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Twitter: http://twitter.com/TheWoodlandsUMC

snippet.title: The Way of Christ: Challenged Along the Way | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
From the beginning of Jesus’ ministry to the very end, He was challenged, criticized, and tested by a variety of foes representing both the political and religious establishment of His time. They perceived Him to be a threat to the status quo, and everything He did or said was questioned and pronounced unlawful, especially by the Pharisees and Scribes. However, Jesus not only de ed their opposition, but He ushered in a new order where the greatest would be the least, and the exalted would be humbled. Today’s sermon asks the question “What can we learn from Jesus as we confront our modern-day challenges?”

Sermon 3/12/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

Traditional Worship

Web: http://www.thewoodlandsumc.org/
Facebook: http://fb.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Instagram: http://instagram.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Twitter: http://twitter.com/TheWoodlandsUMC

snippet.title: No Charge! | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
This coming Ash Wednesday marks the beginning of Lent, the traditional 40-day period of fasting, prayer, penitence and self-examination practiced by Christians throughout the world. It is truly one of the “holiest” seasons of the liturgical year; but like so many other seasons, it often comes and goes without changing us inwardly. In order for us to make this Lenten season di erent from all the others, we will view Lent this year through the lens of the cross, acknowledging the fact that Christ did something for us that we cannot fathom, let alone repay! Today’s message invites us to draw near to God, knowing that if we sincerely try, God will draw near to us.

Sermon 2/26/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

Traditional Worship

Web: http://www.thewoodlandsumc.org/
Facebook: http://fb.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Instagram: http://instagram.com/TheWoodlandsUMC
Twitter: http://twitter.com/TheWoodlandsUMC

snippet.title: Membership Has Its Privileges | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Throughout the Gospels Jesus is constantly reminding His followers that there is a “cost” involved with discipleship. So often we get so focused on the sacrifices we have to make and often lose sight of what we will receive in return for putting Jesus first and foremost in our lives. In fact, being a disciple of Jesus gives us certain privileges that far exceed anything we could gain or profit from in today’s world. Our message today seeks to remind us that if we are earnestly looking for life, we must be willing to lose it for the sake of Christ.

Sermon 2/19/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

snippet.title: Will You Grow?: Presence | Bishop Bob Hayes
snippet.description:
Trees grow. Children grow. Every part of creation grows in strength and purpose. As followers of Christ, it’s important to grow not only physically but also spiritually. In 2 Peter we are told to “grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ,” because it is in learning about Him that we develop and mature. If where we are is not where we want to be, we can each grow by sharing our stories, joining a study or changing the habits of our prayer life. We invite you to join us for this new series as we grow together in our prayers, presence, gifts, service and witness.

Sermon 1/15/17 with Bishop Bob Hayes

snippet.title: Ignite: Our Hope for the Future
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen

Hey neighbor. Light breaks through darkness. As we enter a new year and look to a brighter tomorrow, we need that light to shine bright. We know it is the light of Christ, the power of the Holy Spirit that ignites within us, equipping us to reflect our faith and God’s grace. Once we experience this spark of light, we are inspired to share it with others and to create something bold and new. In our stewardship series, we’ll learn how God’s light ignites our passion for ministry, our spirit of generosity and our reach to the world so we can have hope for the future.

Web: https://www.thewoodlandsumc.org/woodforest
Church Online: https://woodforest.online.church/

snippet.title: Our Lord’s Prayer: Give Us This Day Our Daily Bread
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Mark Sorensen

The Lord’s Prayer has been recited by individuals and groups of Christians all over the world for a couple thousand years. Whether it is worship, on a retreat, or as a family prayer before bedtime, the words Jesus taught His earliest followers to pray have been uttered countless times by countless persons. The “Our Father,” as some have called it, was likely one of the first prayers you ever heard, and possibly the first scripture you were taught to memorize. But, why do we pray it? Why did Jesus teach it to His disciples? What do we mean when we pray it anyway? Glad you asked! And, glad you’re here to unpack it with us each week through Easter.

snippet.title: Growing Together: Vision 2022
snippet.description:
State of the Church | Rev. Mark Sorensen

Everything that has life grows. From trees to animals to children to you and me — we all grow. This year, 2022, is our time to grow together with a renewed focus and vision by choosing an intentional path. Jesus has invited us to follow Him on a life-long journey to grow in maturity, love our neighbors, share our faith, and, ultimately, become more like Him. I’m ready to have the abundant life Jesus offers in
John 10:10, aren’t you? Let’s find it by growing together!

snippet.title: Seeking God in Everyday Life: Lessons from Moses’ Encounter
snippet.description:
In this message, we explore three important lessons from Moses’ encounter with the burning bush. Moses was just going about his everyday life when he witnessed something extraordinary. God showed up in an unexpected way, and Moses listened. 

Just like with Moses, God invites us to seek Him and be ready for those “holy distractions” in our lives. When we seek God with all our hearts, we will find Him. 

Join us as we dive into the importance of seeking God, recognizing His presence, and sharing His story with others.

snippet.title: Exodus 1-2: The Story of Moses and God’s Plan for Life
snippet.description:
In today’s message, we dive into the powerful story of Exodus chapters 1 and 2. We explore how Moses’ life was saved and how God used him to deliver His people from slavery. This story reminds us of God’s love and His plan for every life, no matter the circumstances. 

Join us as we reflect on the importance of life, God’s guidance, and how His love can guide us through difficult times. 

This message is especially relevant as we approach challenging conversations in our society. Let’s learn together how to love others as God loves us.

snippet.title: Why Youth Leadership Matters: A Fresh Perspective on Faith
snippet.description:
In this inspiring message, Pastor Brent challenges a common misconception in the church: that youth leadership is a lesser role. 

Join us as we hear from Evan, a passionate young pastor, who shares his journey of faith and how the next generation is crucial to the future of the church. Evan reminds us that most people make a decision to follow Jesus before they turn 14, highlighting the importance of nurturing young believers. 

Don't miss this powerful sermon that encourages everyone, young and old, to stay spiritually awake and expectant for God's new work in their lives.

snippet.title: Finding Peace in Silence: A Journey Through Acts 28
snippet.description:
In this message, we explore the final chapter of Acts, discovering how silence and reflection can bring us closer to God. Pastor Brent guides us through the practice of Lectio Divina – an ancient way of praying with Scripture – to help us open our hearts and minds to the Lord. 

As we journey with Paul to the end of Acts, we learn the importance of listening to God, embracing His word, and understanding the role of the Church in God’s plan. Whether you’re facing storms in your life or simply seeking a deeper connection with God, this message offers hope and encouragement. 

Join us as we learn to see with new eyes, hear with new ears, and soften our hearts to the voice of the Holy Spirit.

snippet.title: Finding Peace in Life's Storms
snippet.description:
Life can often feel like a storm or a roller coaster with its ups and downs. Whether it’s marital challenges, job loss, or personal struggles, Jesus reassures us that despite the inevitable troubles of this world, He has already overcome it.

We invite you to join us on this journey, finding strength in community and faith. Let’s embrace the storms together, knowing that with God, we will reach our destination safely.

Highlights:

Scripture Reading: Reflect on Acts 27 and its relevance to our lives today.

Moments of Silence: Experience the power of stillness in connecting with God.

Life’s Roller Coaster: Hear relatable stories and find encouragement for your own journey.

Faith and Resilience: Learn how faith can help us navigate the hardest times.

Don’t forget to like, share, and subscribe for more uplifting messages.

snippet.title: Journeying Through Acts: Faith, Perseverance, and Hope
snippet.description:
As we continue our series on Acts, we're looking at Paul's unwavering commitment to spreading the Gospel, even when faced with imprisonment and persecution. His resolve to appeal to Caesar rather than taking the easier route back to Jerusalem is a testament to his faith and dedication.

We'll also reflect on the challenges of sharing our faith, drawing inspiration from the parable of the sower in Mark 4. This parable reminds us that while not every seed we plant will grow, our efforts are never in vain. Whether the seed falls on rocky ground, among thorns, or fertile soil, our job is to continue planting and trusting God to bring the increase.

Sharing our faith can be difficult, and it's natural to feel discouraged when our efforts don't seem to bear fruit. However, we must remember that God can work through every situation. Just as the farmer in the parable doesn't give up, we too must keep sowing seeds of hope, love, and faith.

Thank you for being part of our church family. We look forward to seeing you next week as we continue to explore the incredible stories and lessons from the book of Acts.

snippet.title: Finding Strength in Desperation | Acts 25
snippet.description:
In today’s message, Thomas explores Acts 25, providing rich context from previous chapters (Acts 22-24) to illuminate Paul’s trials and steadfast faith. Despite being imprisoned for two years, Paul’s dedication to his divine calling to go to Rome never wavered. Through Paul’s story, we learn about choosing desperate faith over comfort, and how such faith can transform lives and entire empires.

Thomas also draws a powerful parallel with the story of Shadrach, Meshach, and Abednego, highlighting how their desperate faith amidst trials led to miraculous deliverance and recognition of God’s power.

Join us as we reflect on the importance of maintaining a desperate faith, even in the face of challenges. Let's embrace the call to be unwavering in our commitment to God, knowing that through our desperation, true transformation can occur.

snippet.title: Faith, Conviction, and the Power of the Holy Spirit
snippet.description:
Have you ever found yourself quick to point out others' faults while overlooking your own? In this message, Pastor Brent encourages us to hold God's word close and consider its personal implications before deflecting it onto others. As we journey through the final chapters of Acts, we're invited to listen deeply, allowing God's truth to transform us from within.

Join us as we explore the trials of Paul, the dynamics of his defense, and the profound lessons we can learn about faith, conviction, and the power of the Holy Spirit. May this sermon inspire you to seek more of Him and less of us in our daily walk.

Key Points:
*Understanding the context and significance of Acts 24
*The importance of self-reflection and personal conviction
*How God's grace and righteousness are gifts, not earned by works
*The impact of societal echo chambers on our perception of truth
*Encouragement to embody kindness, gentleness, and thoughtfulness as the body of Christ

Don't forget to subscribe for more weekly sermons and spiritual insights. May you be blessed and encouraged as you listen and reflect on God's word.

snippet.title: Trusting God's Plan Even When We Can't See It
snippet.description:
Today we're diving into the theme of trusting in God's plan, even when we can't see it. Reflecting on Acts 23, we are reminded that God is always working for our good, orchestrating His perfect plan in our lives.

Whether you’re familiar with the story of Paul or hearing it for the first time, today’s message is a powerful reminder that God's plan for us is always better than our own. Join us in embracing this truth and finding peace in the knowledge that He is always at work, even in the unseen.

Remember, God loves you and has a wonderful plan for your life. Let’s walk this journey together, trusting in His wisdom and grace.

🙏 If you found this message encouraging, please like, share, and subscribe to our channel. God bless you!

snippet.title: The Power of Testimony | Acts 22
snippet.description:
In today’s message, we're diving into the testimony of Paul from Acts 22, exploring how his profound encounter with Jesus turned him from a persecutor of Christians to one of the greatest evangelists in history. Just as Paul's story is told multiple times in the book of Acts, emphasizing its importance, we believe that every testimony holds immense value. Your story, too, has the power to inspire and bring hope to others.

Join us as we reflect on the goodness of God and the hope we find in Jesus, even in a world that often feels hopeless. Let's be encouraged to share our own testimonies boldly, knowing that our experiences with God's grace can touch hearts and change lives.

Scripture Reference:
Acts 21-22

Prayer:
We thank you, Lord, for your presence and goodness that fills our hearts with hope. May we be emboldened to share our testimonies and spread your love. Amen.

Don't forget to like, subscribe, and hit the notification bell to stay updated with our latest messages and events. We’re so glad you’re part of our community!

snippet.title: Surprised by the Spirit | Acts 20
snippet.description:
Today we're diving into Acts chapter 20, exploring the journey of the Apostle Paul and the lessons for our lives today. In today's message, Pastor Cabe dives into the story of Paul's travels and encounters in Acts 20, highlighting the importance of being open to the surprise of the Spirit in our lives. This message is not just about historical context but about how we can apply these lessons of faith and community in our modern lives.

Join us in exploring how the Spirit moves among us, awakening hearts and bringing new life!

snippet.title: Living a Sprit Led Life
snippet.description: Explore the essence of living a Spirit-led life with our latest message, where we dive into the significance of the Holy Spirit's guidance in our daily lives. Learn how to embrace change and new responsibilities within your spiritual community by trusting in God's direction. This video offers insights into the biblical narrative of the Exodus and the early church's reliance on the Holy Spirit, providing a blueprint for our own journeys. Discover practical steps to discern the Holy Spirit's voice and cultivate a closer relationship with God. Join us as we explore how to dedicate each day to the Spirit, create a heart open to God, and commit to obedience, anchoring our identity in Christ for a fulfilling Spirit-led life.

snippet.title: Acts 16 - The Power of Transformation
snippet.description: Could an earthquake ever signify hope and transformation? Explore the transformative journey of Paul and Silas in Philippi in Acts 16 as they navigate through divine encounters, spiritual warfare, and miraculous deliverance in this week's message. Witness how their unwavering faith and the power of worship lead to an earthquake that not only frees them but also opens the heart of their jailer to the gospel. This narrative from the book of Acts serves as a testament to the early church's impact and the enduring message of mercy, forgiveness, and hope. Discover the essence of the church as a force for cultural change and personal transformation. Join us in revisiting this pivotal moment in church history and find inspiration to extend mercy and seek reconciliation in your own life. Don't miss this powerful story of faith, hope, and the transformative power of the gospel.

snippet.title: Embracing the Spirit of Unity
snippet.description:
Explore the message of Acts 15 in our latest sermon, 'Embracing the Spirit of Unity.' Discover how the early church navigated the inclusion of Gentiles, the role of tradition, and the essence of salvation. Learn from Peter's wisdom that grace, not the law, is the path to salvation, and witness the Jerusalem Council's decision to foster unity without imposing unnecessary burdens. This sermon is a must-watch for anyone seeking to understand the power of the Holy Spirit in creating unity amidst diversity. Join us in reflecting on how to embrace diversity within the body of Christ and commit to love and charity in all things. Don't forget to like, share, and subscribe for more inspiring messages. 

#Acts15 #EarlyChurch #UnityInDiversity #HolySpirit #Grace #Salvation #ChristianUnity #GospelMessage #ChurchHistory #BibleStudy

snippet.title: Pentecost and the Holy Spirit
snippet.description:
Join us as we explore the power of the Holy Spirit in this Pentecost reflection. Witness the extraordinary descent of the Holy Spirit upon the early worshippers and understand its significance for our faith today. Discover how the Holy Spirit creates a welcoming space for all believers and learn about the Apostle Paul's dramatic transformation. We'll look at the Book of Acts and see how the church in Antioch models a vibrant, Spirit-led community. This sermon will inspire you to rekindle your spiritual fire and live in harmony with the Holy Spirit's guidance. Don't miss out on this powerful message—subscribe and share this message with others.

 #pentecost #spiritualgrowth HolySpirit #ChurchGrowth #ApostlePaul #SpiritualFire #ChristianFaith #Transformation #EarlyChurch #Worship #FaithCommunity

snippet.title: How To Live an Authentic Faith
snippet.description: Explore the transformative power of Christ's love with our latest message. Dive into Paul's timeless message to the Ephesians and discover how to live out your faith with authenticity. This sermon unpacks the importance of being known for our faith and love, rather than just rules or achievements. Learn how Paul's prayer for the church can strengthen your heart and grasp the vastness of Christ's love. Whether you're seeking spiritual growth, understanding of the Gospel, or ways to embody an authentic faith in Jesus, this sermon offers insights for a life transformed by faith. Don't miss out on this powerful message—perfect for those searching for Christian living, spiritual transformation, or the essence of Paul's teachings.

snippet.title: A New Creation in Christ
snippet.description:
In this week's message, we'll dive into the Apostle Paul's teachings and learn how accepting Jesus into your life leads to becoming a new creation, where Christ lives within you. Explore the struggle between living by the flesh and by the Spirit, and find out how to embrace the fruits of the Spirit in your daily life. This inspiring message will guide you to experience God's love deeply and allow it to transform your life.

 #GodsLove #NewCreation #ApostlePaul #SpiritualTransformation #ChristianLiving #ChurchSermon #LoveOfChrist #FruitsOfTheSpirit #BibleTeaching #FaithJourney #TransformedByLove

snippet.title: How to Love Like Jesus Did
snippet.description: Join us as we explore the depth and transformative power of God's love. Discover how love goes beyond feelings and becomes an action that reflects Christ's love through us to others. This message will bring to life Galatians 2:20, encouraging us to live by faith in Jesus and to share His love with the world. Whether you're looking to deepen your faith or understand how to better embody Christ's love in your daily life, this sermon will guide you on your spiritual journey. Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more uplifting messages.

snippet.title: The Power of God's Love: Unity and Reconciliation
snippet.description: In today's message we'll explore the transformative power of God's love and the Christian calling to unity and reconciliation. Discover how we can impact the world by embodying the love and unity that Jesus prayed for in John 17 and how Paul's prayer in Ephesians 3 can guide us to be rooted in love. This message challenges us to consider our true desire for a relationship with Jesus and to become ambassadors of reconciliation, as described in 2 Corinthians 5. Whether you're seeking inspiration, spiritual growth, or a deeper understanding of your faith, this sermon offers valuable insights into living as a new creation in Christ.

snippet.title: How to Experience the Love of God
snippet.description: Discover the power of the Holy Spirit and learn how to experience the love of God in a profound and daily way. We'll go through the teachings from Ephesians 3 and 1 Corinthians 13, revealing the challenges and beauty of living a life rooted in divine love. This message is not just for those seeking spiritual growth but for anyone looking to understand the depth of God's love. Whether you're struggling with faith, seeking comfort, or looking to deepen your relationship with Jesus, this message offers a powerful prayer for strength and understanding. Don't miss this opportunity to transform your life with the love of Christ.

snippet.title: Experiencing the Risen Christ Every Day
snippet.description: What if you could experience the risen Christ right here right now? Discover how the Apostle Paul's message in 1 Corinthians 15 challenges us to live with the risen Christ at the forefront of our faith. Experience the story of the disciples on the road to Emmaus and learn how to recognize Jesus in every aspect of our lives. Witness the transformative power of the Holy Spirit through the life of Paul and be encouraged to pray fervently for one another. This sermon will reignite your passion for Christ and deepen your understanding of His love. Don't forget to like, comment, and subscribe for more uplifting messages.

snippet.title: The Love Language of Service
snippet.description: Today we're talking about the love language of acts of service and its biblical significance during Palm Sunday. Learn from the example of Mary's anointing of Jesus and how to serve others with a pure heart, just as Jesus washed His disciples' feet. This message will inspire you to worship God with complete devotion and to serve others without seeking anything in return.

snippet.title: The Five Love Languages: Physical Touch
snippet.description:
As part of our series on the five love languages, we're talking about the transformative power of physical touch. Learn how Jesus used touch to heal, comfort, and bless, and how we can incorporate this love language into our lives in a positive and respectful way. Whether you're seeking to deepen your relationships or understand the impact of physical touch, this sermon offers biblical wisdom and practical advice. Don't forget to like, subscribe, and share this video! 

#lovelanguages #PhysicalTouch #ChristianLiving #JesusHealing #BiblicalTeaching #ChurchSermon #FaithInAction #SpiritualGrowth #Oxytocin #HumanConnection

snippet.title: The Five Love Languages and Our Relationships
snippet.description: Today we're continuing our series exploring the five love languages from a biblical perspective. In this message, Pastor Brent explores Gary Chapman's Love Languages, revealing how understanding these languages can transform relationships and deepen connections with God. From understanding the five love languages to exploring the significance of stewardship, this message offers insights into building stronger relationships and enriching our spiritual lives. Join us on this transformative journey as we learn to love more deeply and live more authentically.

snippet.title: Quality Time with God
snippet.description: In this message, Bishop Hayes shares powerful insights on the importance of finding quality time with God. Drawing from Psalms and personal reflections, we'll highlight the significance of prioritizing spiritual connection amidst life's hectic routines. Discover how to carve out moments of silence, listening, and prayer to enrich your relationship with God. Join us as we explore the transformative impact of embracing quality time with the Divine. Don't miss out on this uplifting message that promises to inspire and guide you on your spiritual journey.

snippet.title: The Power of Words in our Lives | Luann Riley
snippet.description: In today's message we're exploring the profound power of words in our lives. We'll dive into the timeless wisdom of Dr. Gary Chapman's "The Five Love Languages" and focus on the language of love: words of affirmation. Discover how verbal compliments, appreciation, and encouragement not only strengthen relationships but also nourish the soul. From insightful anecdotes to scientific insights, learn how positive words can transform our brains and uplift our spirits. Whether you're seeking to deepen your understanding of love or grow in your relationship with God, this message offers practical wisdom and inspiration for everyone.

snippet.title: What We Value: Part 2
snippet.description: As we continue to explore our core values in this series, What We Value, we'll unravel the layers of biblical wisdom intertwined with personal stories, highlighting the importance of living faithfully, loving compassionately, and embracing integrity and accountability in our daily lives. Discover how these timeless values resonate with the challenges and triumphs we encounter in our journey of faith.

snippet.title: Lent and the Essence of Love
snippet.description: In this message we're exploring the essence of love and faith as we explore the profound connections between Ash Wednesday, Valentine's Day, and Lent. Join us as we reflect on the significance of baptisms, the power of prayer, and the challenges of living out our faith in a world filled with distractions.

snippet.title: What We Value: Part 1
snippet.description: Today we're talking about what we value as a church and the importance of breaking free from life's routines and embracing a new rhythm that aligns with faith. We'll explore the significance of personal consecration to the Lord and the impact it can have on our daily lives. Join us in conversations about family, stewardship, and the core values shaping our church community.

snippet.title: Are You Growing?
snippet.description: Are you growing? Not just in the superficial sense, but in the areas of life that truly matter. The sermon takes you on a journey through the themes of generosity, guidance, gratitude, and now, growth. Discover insightful reflections on how we can grow both spiritually and in everyday life as individuals and as the church. We'll look at practical ways to embrace growth, build meaningful relationships, and live a life aligned with God and His purposes. If you're wanting to become more generous, guided, grateful, and learn more about how God can help you do this, this video is for you.

snippet.title: The Secret to Contentment
snippet.description: Discover the secret to true contentment in this powerful message from Philippians 4:13. Learn how gratitude plays a key role in finding fulfillment, and be inspired to live a generous and purposeful life. Don't miss out on this transformative journey!

snippet.title: Navigating the Journey of Faith | Guided Church
snippet.description: When we're navigating the journey of faith, it's important to have a clear guide. This week we're talking about being a guided church, the importance of having a clear guide in life, finding inspiration in biblical teachings, and embracing a life of generosity. Dive into the discussion on being led by a higher purpose and allowing the Lord to be your shepherd as we explore what it truly means to be a guided church in the year ahead.

snippet.title: Is it More Blessed to Give Than to Receive?
snippet.description: Join us as Pastor Brent explores the age-old question: Is it truly more blessed to give than to receive? Drawing inspiration from Acts 20:35, where Paul quotes Jesus, Pastor Brent dives into the profound impact of generosity on our lives. Discover the Greek word "Makários," meaning happy, and how living a life of generosity can lead to true happiness. Explore the correlation between the condition of our hearts and our financial choices, and how Jesus emphasized this in Matthew 6:21 and learn the scientific benefits of generosity, including increased happiness, lowered stress, improved relationships, and an extended life. Don't miss real-life stories of transformed lives through generosity and the exciting giving challenge ahead. Join us in the journey of discovering the joy and blessings that come from living a life of giving.

snippet.title: The Lord is My Shepherd: Psalm 23
snippet.description: As it says in Psalm 23, "The Lord is my Shepherd." But what does that mean? Discover the deep connection between rest, mental health, and the guidance of the Good Shepherd. Learn how the shepherd's presence guarantees abundance, healing, and a year-long journey of faith. As we close 2023, let's dwell in the house of the Lord, acknowledging His pursuit, kindness, and the assurance that we lack nothing in His presence.

snippet.title: A Joyful Christmas Celebration - Youth/Children Led Service
snippet.description: Get ready for a joyful Christmas celebration led by our youth and children! This service is not just for adults and we invite our young friends to participate actively and experience the joy of Christmas. Discover the wonderful gift we've received this Christmas season and explore the joy that only Jesus can bring into our lives. Get ready to be inspired and uplifted!

snippet.title: The Wonder of It All: Peace
snippet.description: For some of us, Christmas can be anything but peaceful. However, there is hope! Learn how the journey towards peace involves grappling with grief, forgiveness, and understanding the true meaning of Shalom. We'll look at the timeless message that amidst life's troubles, we can find a deep and lasting peace in Jesus. Don't miss this insightful exploration of The Wonder of Christ, and discover the peace that surpasses all understanding.

snippet.title: The Wonder of It All: Loving Others
snippet.description: Today we're continuing on our journey of waiting and anticipation during the season of Advent. Discover how the Holy Spirit empowers us not just to come together but to go out into the world and spread love. As we prepare for Christmas, let's extend the love we've received to those who are waiting.

snippet.title: Waiting in Hope - Advent
snippet.description: What does it look like to wait in hope? We will be approaching the next several Sundays through the eyes of a child. I invite you to open your heart and mind to the possibly unexpected ways that God will reveal hope, love, joy and peace to you. Whether you are a member of our church, an invited guest or a curious visitor, my prayer is you will join us in the wonder of Jesus’ arrival to our community, especially in this Christmas season.

snippet.title: He Holds The Future | Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
During our journey from Ash Wednesday to Easter, Christians are invited to take
intentional steps from death into life. We begin with a healthy awareness of our
humanity, and its frailty, along with our sin and the consequences of our sinful
behavior. Then we look forward to the wonderful celebration of the new life we are
given through the life, death and resurrection of Jesus at Easter. Because Jesus lives,
we, His followers, are made alive as well. We will spend our Sundays between now
and Easter uncovering exactly what we receive because He lives.

Front Porch Message | June 18, 2020
The Elephant in the Room: Forgiving Me
Hope Revealed: Peace Brings Hope | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker 

For many of us, the holidays could not come at a better time. We have been isolated, lonely, nervous, anxious and troubled by much of what 2020 has brought our way. As a result of this pandemic and a tense political cycle, there is a greater sense of hopelessness in the air than we have felt in a long time. Yet, as people of faith, we know that our desperate search for hope leads us back to a little manger in Bethlehem where God’s peace, joy and love arrived. In the birth of Jesus, we find hope revealed!

snippet.title: Ignite: Our Generosity
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker  

Hey neighbor. Light breaks through darkness. As we enter a new year and look to a brighter tomorrow, we need that light to shine bright. We know it is the light of Christ, the power of the Holy Spirit that ignites within us, equipping us to reflect our faith and God’s grace. Once we experience this spark of light, we are inspired to share it with others and to create something bold and new. In our stewardship series, we’ll learn how God’s light ignites our passion for ministry, our spirit of generosity and our reach to the world so we can have hope for the future.

snippet.title: What Can I Do?
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker with Dr. John Hull 

With so many needs in this world, where does a person start if they want to help? Obviously, the first step is to feel drawn to serve others. If you’re drawn, or feel “called by God,” to enter into the pains and needs of others, the next best step is to identify the particular needs that seem to resonate most with your gifts or passions. And then, the fun begins as you uncover the opportunities all around you to use your gifts to meet the needs in your own “backyard.” This morning, Dr. John Hull joins me as we discuss those places where God has been welcoming our church into ministry, hoping that you might find your way into one of those or even into a ministry of your own. Glad you’re here!

snippet.title: Our Lord’s Prayer: Our Father In Heaven, Hallowed Be Thy Name
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

The Lord’s Prayer has been recited by individuals and groups of Christians all over the world for a couple thousand years. Whether it is worship, on a retreat, or as a family prayer before bedtime, the words Jesus taught His earliest followers to pray have been uttered countless times by countless persons. The “Our Father,” as some have called it, was likely one of the first prayers you ever heard, and possibly the first scripture you were taught to memorize. But, why do we pray it? Why did Jesus teach it to His disciples? What do we mean when we pray it anyway? Glad you asked! And, glad you’re here to unpack it with us each week through Easter.

snippet.title: Come Together: We Need Each Other
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

After more than a year of being told that we should stay at home away from others, many of us have settled into the unfamiliarity of loneliness and isolation. Even the church building has become a place where we have been encouraged to beware of getting too close to others. In fact, the church has always existed to be more than simply the place you go to on a Sunday morning for worship. The Church exists to be the people of God who live life together. Let’s uncover the many opportunities that we have to live this life together in Christian community.

snippet.title: Ordinary Time: Finding God Every Day
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Featuring Brent Parker

In Tish Warren’s Liturgy of the Ordinary, we find the invitation to “become aware of God’s presence in surprising ways” as we walk through the ordinary parts of our daily lives. Throughout this series, we will figuratively walk through the everyday stuff of waking up and making our beds, of checking emails and gathering around our dinner tables at the end of a day, and then looking for the opportunities to
find God “hiding” within the ordinariness of it all. Our hope is that each of us will find a new rhythm that seeks to make our ordinary life more extra-ordinary. Let’s start this morning.

snippet.title: Are You Listening? What is Prayer and Why We Should Do It | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

Prayer is one of the most intimate acts of faith for those who believe. Not only are we talking to God, but we are hearing from Him too. What we say to God often expresses our deepest longings. We ask things of God, say things to God, and bring the needs of others to God, all in the hopes that He will respond to us with help and with greater understanding of the mysteries of life. In this series, we will take the common
themes of our prayers and unpack what the Scriptures reveal about how God has answered the prayers of His people.

snippet.title: Searching for Christmas: Searching for More Love | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

More. We want more! But what is it that we really want more of? At this time of year, with advertisements and commercials aplenty, we could easily be lured into wanting more of the stuff that we already have — newer or bigger and better versions. Yet, most of us have lived long enough to recognize that this never has, and never will, satisfy the deepest longings of our hearts. What we really are looking
for, far more than anything else, is more joy, hope, love and peace in our lives. Between now and Christmas, our church family will be digging into God’s word to see how the coming of Jesus can bring with it these things that we so deeply need.

snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

Hey neighbor! We are so glad you dropped by. As we worship, we gather as a community of friends and neighbors in our love for the Lord. Together, we will worship, pray and hear God’s Word as He speaks into our lives at this moment in time. We pray that you sense the presence of God’s Spirit as you join us this morning. Welcome!

snippet.title: Minute Message
Growing Together: We Are Sowers | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

Everything that has life grows. From trees to animals to children to you and me — we all grow. This year, 2022, is our time to grow together with a renewed focus and vision by choosing an intentional path. Jesus has invited us to follow Him on a life-long journey to grow in maturity, love our neighbors, share our faith, and, ultimately, become more like Him. I’m ready to have the abundant life Jesus offers in John 10:10, aren’t you? Let’s find it by growing together!

snippet.title: The Way of Jesus | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

Hey neighbor! We are so glad you dropped by. We are in the midst of a 3-week “deep dive” into Jesus’ words from John 14:6: “I am the way and the truth and the life. No one comes to the Father except through me.” I hope that you will find your time with us this morning to be a source of encouragement and that both your heart and mind are filled with the knowledge of God’s love for you. Please be sure to let us know you visited by stopping at the First Timer table on your way out. Welcome!

snippet.title: Christoform: Made for This | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

From the moment we began a relationship with Jesus, we have been on a journey of shaping our lives into the image of Christ. From the way we think and act, to the way we love others, each day is an opportunity to align our lives to the ways and purposes of Jesus. During the 40 days of Lent, between Ash Wednesday and Easter, we will be focusing our attention on living A Jesus-Shaped Life. Join us as we consider the obedience, relationships, courage, justice, and mission of Jesus.

snippet.title: Domino Effect: Jesus Christ Ascended | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Thomas Lake

Have you ever poured out dominoes, lined them up in formation and experienced the joy of watching them fall down by simply tipping the first one over? Maybe you accidentally tipped a domino over and watched your hard work topple prematurely. For the Sundays between Easter and Memorial Day weekend, we are going to unpack how God sent His Holy Spirit to accomplish a very different “domino effect” as we walk through the book of Colossians. We will see how the Holy Spirit works to exponentially grow God’s Kingdom, and we will recommit ourselves to being one of the “dominoes” in the line.


Web: https://www.twmc.org/woodforest
Church Online: https://woodforest.online.church/

snippet.title: Jesus Christ, Our Method | The Church at Woodforest
snippet.description:
Woodforest Worship | Brent Parker

Good morning, neighbor! I’m glad you are here to worship God with our church family, and I trust they have already made you feel welcome. Whether you are a member of our church, an invited guest or a curious visitor, my prayer is you will find an unexplainable joy welling up in your spirit as you realize God has also arrived to meet with you here. We love having children with us in worship. We invite them forward at offering time, and then, before the sermon, they are invited to join Children’s Church. If your child (5th grade and younger) would like to attend Children’s Church, get them checked in before service. Please be sure to stop by our First Timer table or come and say hi to me on your way out. God bless you and thanks for coming!

Web: https://www.twmc.org/woodforest

snippet.title: A Walk Through Romans: Romans 1
snippet.description:
Join us as we embark on a journey through the book of Romans, exploring each chapter and uncovering what Paul had to say to the early church that is still relevant to us today. In this first chapter, we discuss the importance of community and being a part of the church, and how it can strengthen us as a collective force. We also set some ground rules for our study and ask for patience as we navigate this thick, theologically dense book that has informed much of Christendom. Let's dive into the first chapter of Romans together and discover what it means for us today.

Key takeaways:

- Being part of a Christian community is important for our faith
- The book of Romans is a complex but important book that has shaped Christian theology
- We should be patient with ourselves and each other as we explore this book together
- We should form our own theology based on the word of God, rather than simply accepting what someone else tells us to believe.

snippet.title: Discovering God's Love: Exploring Romans 5
snippet.description:
Join us as we continue our journey through the Book of Romans as we explore the teachings of Paul in Romans Chapter 5. Discover the surprising message that goes beyond rules and emphasizes God's goodness, love, and how it makes us righteous. Learn how suffering can lead to perseverance and hope, and find encouragement in God's unwavering love for all of us.

snippet.title: Romans 6: The Amazing Story of God's Love and Our Choices
snippet.description: Join us as we continue our journey through Romans in Romans chapter 6 as we explore the incredible story of God's love and the choices we make in life. Discover how God's grace and forgiveness can transform our hearts and bring us hope even in difficult times. Dive into the story of Adam and Eve, their decision, and its consequences, and learn how Jesus came to reconcile us with God and offer us a new way of living. Find out the two different stories we can choose from and the amazing freedom found in following Jesus.

snippet.title: Romans 7 - The Two Ways of Living: Adam vs. Jesus
snippet.description: In this message, we're going through Romans 7 and looking at two different ways of living: the Adam life and the Jesus life. These two ways of living are opposite and cannot be mixed or switched conveniently. The way of Jesus is about love and downward mobility, rather than striving to be good or righteous by our own efforts. Join us as we continue exploring this powerful way of living that can transform our lives!

snippet.title: Minute Message 6.8.23
Romans 9 - Meeting with Jesus at Church
snippet.description: Are you on a search for the right church? In this inspiring message, Pastor Brent reminds us that finding the right fit is all about meeting with Jesus. It's not about the music, the preacher, or the programs—it's about encountering the Lord and fulfilling our deep longing for Him. Join us as we explore Romans 9 and discover the amazing love and grace of God. Don't miss out on this important part of the journey!

snippet.title: Romans 10: Understanding God's Love and Grace
snippet.description: Join us as we continue our insightful study on the book of Romans as we look at Romans 10. In this week's chapter, we dive into the importance of understanding that God's love cannot be earned by following rules. Pastor Brent shares Paul's message to the believers in Rome and how it still resonates with us today. Discover the transformative power of accepting Jesus and His fulfillment of our deepest needs. Don't miss out on this enriching journey through the Scriptures!

snippet.title: Understanding Romans 9-11: God's Mercy and Grace
snippet.description: Welcome to our church's journey through the book of Romans! In this video, we dive into chapters 9, 10, and 11, exploring the themes of God's mercy, grace, and the inclusion of both Jews and Gentiles in His plan. Join us as we uncover the foundational truths of our faith and discover the depth of God's wisdom and knowledge. Don't miss out on the good stuff God has in store for you through daily readings and reflections. Get ready to be inspired and curious about what the Word of God has to say!

snippet.title: Living Sacrifice: Unity, Prayer, and Sacrificial Living | Romans 12
snippet.description: Join us for an inspiring sermon delivered by Thomas Lake, the Youth Shepherd at The Church at Woodforest. In this powerful message, Thomas shares his personal journey and highlights passages from Romans 12 about the importance of unity, prayer, and living sacrificially in the body of Christ.  Learn what it means to be a Living Sacrifice in today's world and how it can transform lives. Don't miss this transformative message!

snippet.title: Love and Sacrifice: Exploring Romans 12-13
snippet.description: Join us as we dive deep into the book of Romans, focusing on chapters 12 and 13. Uncover the profound meaning behind living a sacrificial life and embracing the commandment to love our neighbors. We'll also discuss the importance of surrendering to God's authority and walking in the light of Christ. Don't miss this opportunity to experience the life-changing impact of God's Word!

snippet.title: Loving One Another: Unity Over Disputable Matters | Romans 14
snippet.description: Hey there, friends! Welcome to our church gathering! Today, we're diving into Romans Chapter 14, where we learn about the importance of unity and love among believers. It's like this: we may have some playful differences, just like when we talk about colleges, but what really matters is how we treat and care for one another. In this message, we explore how we can focus on the main thing - loving one another - and let go of arguments over disputable matters. Let's come together, find unity, and be inspired by God's love! If you're new here, no worries! You can catch up on what we've been studying, or you can join us on this journey. Don't forget to hit that "like" button, subscribe to our channel, and share this message with others. Thank you for being a part of our church family! God bless you all!

snippet.title: Romans 16 | Generational Faith
snippet.description:
Join us for the conclusion of our 16-week journey through the Book of Romans! As we wrap up this powerful series, we'll discover the significance of passing on the gospel message and building strong relationships in the way of Jesus. Don't miss this inspiring message that will deepen your understanding of faith and encourage you to make it your own!

snippet.title: How Prayer Helps Us Grow Spiritually
snippet.description:
Join us for a heartfelt message about the power of prayer and how it helps us grow spiritually. In this message, we explore the idea that prayer is not about saying the right words, but about connecting with God and experiencing His overwhelming love. Pastor Brent Parker shares his personal journey of understanding prayer, and how even when our plans don't align with God's, He always leads us where we need to be. Whether you're seeking a word from the Lord, looking for a sense of community, or simply curious about the nature of prayer, this message is for you. Let's come together to discover the joy of meeting with Jesus and finding solace in His presence.

#prayer #spiritualgrowth #powerofprayer #onlinechurch

snippet.title: Acts: Acts 2
snippet.description:
Welcome back to our journey through the book of Acts! 📖 Today, we're diving into Acts chapter 2 and exploring the incredible power of the Holy Spirit. 

In this video, Pastor Brent shares the story of Pentecost, where the Holy Spirit came upon the disciples and something truly extraordinary happened. 🕊️ You'll also learn about how the Spirit can make a real difference in your life today.

So, grab your Bible, a comfy seat, and let's learn together! 🤗
